title: shrimp in chili sauce
directions: In medium saucepan, saute onion, garlic and parsley in stock 2 to 3 minutes.
Add shrimp and continue to cook until shrimp just turn pink (about 4 to 8 minutes).
In small bowl combine taco sauce, chili powder and cumin.
Add to shrimp and heat through.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Cook until done about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: captain crunch surprise
directions: Melt chips in double boiler or microwave.
Add the rest of the ingredients and pour into a baking pan.
Let set for 20 minutes.

title: copper carrots
directions: Cook carrots in water until tender.
Heat remaining ingredients and pour over drained, warm carrots.
Store in refrigerator.
(Keeps for several weeks.)

title: easy barbecue beef brisket
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Place meat in baking dish.
Do not add any water.
Sprinkle soup mix over meat, coating well, then sprinkle rest in pan.
Add brown sugar on top of meat.
Pour 1/2 bottle barbecue sauce over all (any flavor will do).
Cover tightly with foil and bake for 4 to 5 hours or until meat sticks tender.
Slice across the grain of the meat and pour sauce over all when serving.
Serves 4.

title: barbecued baked beans
directions: Cook ground beef, sausage and onion; drain.
Combine all other ingredients.
Add to meat and onion in large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat for 1 to 2 hours.

title: cornish pasties
directions: Make pastry from lard, flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and cold water, being careful not to make mixture too moist.
It should hold together well enough to leave the sides of the bowl as mixed. Divide into four sections.
Roll each out as for pie, 1/4-inch thick, keeping as round as possible.
Place on one-half of circle, a layer of thinly sliced potatoes and onions.
Cover with beef, cut into medium sized pieces.
Top with butter, salt and pepper to taste.
Fold unfilled half of crust over filling and seal by pinching with fingers or pressing with tines of forks to make a half moon.
Cut a small hole in the center of each.
Bake about 30 minutes in a quick oven, approximately 400°.

title: fresh cranberry salad
directions: Wash and stem cranberries.
Chop until the pieces are very small.
Add sugar and set overnight in refrigerator.
Next day, mix Jell-O with only 2 cups of water.
Let cool until cold.
Add berries, crushed pineapple and pecans.
Will freeze well.

title: strawberry ice cream and oreo cookie cheesecake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, ice cream, strawberries, cut in half, and Oreo cookies (save 2 strawberries and 4 Oreos for garnish).
Mix it for 3 minutes.
Fill the pie shell and place it in the freezer for 4 hours.
Cut in 8 portions, decorate with whipped cream, sliced strawberries, Oreos and the strawberry coulis.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch sheet cake pan.
Spread pie filling on bottom of pan.
Pour pineapple on top of pie filling.
Sprinkle cake mix on top of pineapple.
Pour melted margarine on top of cake mix.
Sprinkle coconut on top of margarine and nuts on top of coconut.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool completely before serving.

title: nobby apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg.
Sift together flour, salt, soda, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add to creamed mixture. Stir in apples and nuts.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan which has been greased and floured.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: quick coffee bread
directions: Grease Bundt or tube pan and arrange dinner rolls in pan. Sprinkle pudding over rolls.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over rolls.
Place in cold oven overnight; remove.
Heat oven to 350° and bake 25 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: crisp mexican cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix sugar, shortening, margarine, vanilla, eggs and dry gelatin.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.

title: marinated pea salad
directions: Chill for 24 hours.
Keeps well in refrigerator for days.

title: welsh rabbit on toast
directions: Combine all ingredients in double boiler or a 2 to 3-quart heavy saucepan, except egg.
Do not boil.
Stir often.
Remove from heat and stir in beaten egg.
Pour over toast.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, oil and cinnamon; beat well, then add flour and mix well.
Stir in grated carrots.
Grease and flour three 8-inch pans or two 9-inch pans.
Pour in batter.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: quick tuna casserole
directions: Line casserole dish with finely crushed potato chips.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into dish.
Cover top with large potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until chips are browned.

title: pizza bread
directions: Thaw frozen bread dough.
Roll out dough as thin as possible. Layer pepperoni, then layer cheese.
Roll like jelly roll.
Place on greased cookie sheet and let rise to double size.
Bake according to frozen bread package directions.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together thoroughly.
Add eggs and beat well.
Mix in bananas and sour milk.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt, then add to bananas and milk mixture.
Mix well. Put into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer cooked and cut chicken in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Combine soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Melt butter; add crushed crackers and top casserole. Bake at 325° until heated thoroughly, about 40 minutes.

title: tadpole in a hole
directions: Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish or pan with shortening.
Beat egg in mixing bowl.
Add undrained corn and half of cheese to egg; mix with wooden spoon.
Add dry muffin mix.
Stir until the dry ingredients are wet (the batter will be thick).
Spoon batter into baking dish.
Arrange sausage links on top of batter.
Bake in oven at 400° about 30 minutes or until top is golden.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: creole sweet pepper balls
directions: Mix ingredients well, using hands.
Form into 1-inch balls. Deep fry in oil, turning to make sure even browning.

title: crawfish pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add onion, celery and green pepper.
Cook until onions are transparent and wilted.
Add crawfish tails and mix well.
Cook 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: orange blossom cooler
directions: Mix together.
Makes 5 quarts or 40 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage; drain grease.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put bread in pan.
Top with cheese and sausage.
Beat eggs with remaining ingredients and pour over other ingredients already in pan.
Leave overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.
A great way to use leftover ham.

title: onion rings
directions: Mix together milk, flour, egg, baking powder and salt.
Dip onion slice rings or other vegetables into batter and fry in hot oil.
Drain and serve.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a large baking pan.
In a blender or food processor, whirl bread into fine crumbs and set aside.
In a medium frying pan, heat oil over medium heat.
Add onion and cook until tender, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and set aside.
In a large bowl, whisk eggs with milk, salt, basil and pepper.
Add bread crumbs, onion, spinach, turkey and lemon juice and mix well. Turn mixture out into baking pan and form it into a 9 x 5-inch loaf.
Brush with ketchup and bake for 30 minutes.
After loaf has baked for 30 minutes, baste with butter and continue to bake, basting occasionally, until well browned and cooked through, 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: grated apple pie
directions: Peel, core and grate apples to fill unbaked pie crust.
Melt margarine and sugar.
Add beaten egg.
Pour over apples.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon sugar.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: 5 minute fudge
directions: Mix in a saucepan the milk, sugar and salt over medium heat. Mix ingredients and bring to a boil; cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
(Time when mixture starts to bubble around edge of pan.)
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows, vanilla and chocolate pieces.
Stir vigorously for 1 minute or until marshmallows melt. Pour into an 8-inch square buttered pan.
Garnish with nuts. Cool.
Cut in squares.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: salted nut squares(tastes like payday candy bars)
directions: Place half of the peanuts in an ungreased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking pan; set aside.
In a saucepan, melt butter and peanut butter chips over low heat.
Add milk and marshmallows; cook and stir until melted.
Pour over peanuts.
Sprinkle remaining peanuts on top.
Cover and refrigerate.
Cut into small bars.
Does not have to be refrigerated after cutting into bars.

title: breast of chicken magnifique
directions: Use large skillet.
Brown chicken in magarine; remove.
Brown mushrooms.
Stir in soup, garlic and seasoning; add chicken. Cover and cook over low heat 45 minutes.
Stir now and then. Blend in cream; heat slowly.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In an ungreased baking pan (13 x 9-inch), put chicken thighs on top of dry rice.
Mix together mushroom soup and orange juice. Pour over chicken and rice.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix over the top.
Cover with foil and bake 2 hours at 325°.
It is not necessary to check while baking.
Serves 8.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: Brown hamburg and drain.
Layer in crock-pot: onion, hamburg, potatoes, carrots, celery, mushroom soup and tomato soup.
Rinse each can with 1-inch water and put in crock-pot.
Cover and cook 6 to 7 hours on low.
Stir occasionally.

title: snazzy egg bake
directions: Grease 9 x 13 pan.
Press hash browns between paper towels to remove excess moisture.
Press hash browns in pan.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake in 425° preheated oven until lightly brown 15-20 minutes.
Layer cheeses and ham on top of hash browns.
Beat eggs, half and half and salt.
Pour into pan over ham and cheeses. Bake 30-40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: avocado-orange salad
directions: Arrange on flat plates the lettuce, oranges and avocado.
Top with dressing and pepper.

title: mocha cheesecake
directions: Crust:
In large mixing bowl, stir together flour, powdered sugar, cocoa powder and baking soda.
With a pastry blender or fork, cut in butter until crumbly; press flour mixture into bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together. Blend in dry ingredients. Pour 1/2 of the batter into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan; cover with cheese and green chilies. Pour remaining batter over top of cheese. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes. Easy to double: Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan, same amount of time.

title: quick pizza for kids
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Roll out each biscuit or mash with hands. Spread on pizza sauce, then meat, then cheese.
Bake until cheese melts and is bubbly and biscuits are browned.
Good, fun and easy.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add all ingredients, except sour cream.
Pour half in dish and refrigerate until firm (1 1/2 hours).
Cover with sour cream, then layer with remaining Jell-O. Refrigerate until firm.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour and nutmeg into butter; add eggs and beat until smooth.
Add rhubarb.
Pour into unbaked pie shell; top with strips of pastry and bake in hot oven ten minutes.
Reduce heat and bake until filling thickens, about 30 minutes.

title: louisiana beans
directions: Add water and all ingredients except sausage and simmer for 3 hours.
Fry the hot sausage; drain.
Add to the beans and cook 1 hour longer.

title: easy pudding pie
directions: *French vanilla is very good.

title: homemade granola
directions: Combine all of the ingredients, except the last two, in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then combine the oil and honey, pouring over the other ingredients.
Bake for about 20 minutes in a 250° oven. Cool before putting into Ziploc bags.
Makes about 12 cups.

title: chicken rice salad
directions: Cook rice in chicken broth.
Mix oil and vinegar together and pour over hot rice.
Add mayonnaise and stir.
Add all other ingredients and toss gently.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve chilled.

title: apple cake for a crowd
directions: *Best with Rome, golden Delicious or any baking apple.
Not Macs!!

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Make a hole in the center and pour all liquid in the hole.
Mix and bake in two loaf pans at 325° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: dirty rice
directions: Mix all ingredients in a casserole dish and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Great with shish kebob.
I would try some grated carrots and add parsley.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix together.
Grease cookie sheet, cover with wax paper and then grease wax paper.
Pour batter onto wax paper and spread to edges.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle clean linen towel with powdered sugar.
As soon as you remove pumpkin roll from oven turn it upside-down on the linen towel.
Leave wax paper on and roll up, starting at short end.
Set aside until completely cool, unroll, remove wax paper and then spread the filling after they have been mixed together.
Roll cake with filling, cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate.
Slice to serve.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Sift flour and measure, then sift flour, soda and spices together.
Add flour mixture to butter and sugar; add buttermilk.
Mix well.
Fold in beaten eggs; add jam, preserves and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in a 350° oven until done.

title: tropical cheese spread
directions: Combine all the ingredients in the work bowl of a food processor; process until well blended and smooth.
Transfer the spread to a serving or storage container and cover.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Keeps refrigerated in an airtight container for up to 1 week.

title: one-step lasagna
directions: Spread about 1/2 cup of spaghetti sauce in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Layer a third each of noodles, cottage cheese, remaining sauce and Parmesan; repeat twice.
Pour water around sides of pan. Cover tightly with foil and bake in preheated 350° oven for one hour.
Remove foil and continue to bake for 15 minutes longer or until noodles are tender.

title: south georgia "caviar"
directions: In a large bowl, combine all of the ingredients and stir gently to blend. Refrigerate overnight. Serve with corn or tortilla chips.

title: broccoli ginger stir-fry
directions: Heat large skillet or wok over medium-high heat until hot. Add oil and heat until it ripples.
Add broccoli, garlic, soy sauce and ginger root.
Stir-fry for 2 to 4 minutes or until broccoli is crisp-tender.
Serves 8 (1/2 cup each).

title: irish enchiladas
directions: Fry hamburger with dry onions.
Stir in enchilada sauce. Combine with remaining ingredients and pour into baking pan or casserole.
Bake at 325° until cheese melts (about 20 to 30 minutes).
Spoon out or cut into squares for serving.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Bake pie shells and set aside to cool.
Combine 1 1/2 cups sugar, cornstarch, milk, egg yolks and butter.
Cook until thick. Add coconut and vanilla.
Pour into pie shells.
Cover with meringue, made with 3 egg whites and 6 tablespoons sugar.
Put into hot oven at 400°.
Let meringue brown lightly.
Turn oven off and let pies sit in oven with door closed for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin or squash bread
directions: Combine nutmeg, cinnamon, salt, pumpkin and sugar; mix all together.
Add oil, eggs and water; beat well.
Sift flour and soda; add to mixture.
Add nuts, if desired.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Place peanut butter, dry milk and sugar in a bowl.
Add vanilla and water; blend well.
Stir in cereal and nuts or raisins.
Shape into 12 balls.
Store cookies in a container and refrigerate.

title: pete's arizona green burrito
directions: Brown beef in heavy Dutch oven or skillet.
Lightly brown onions; drain fat, but keep the brown flavor by deglazing skillet or using the Dutch oven.
Add chilies and garlic to beef and onions, along with 3 cups water.
Simmer over low heat for 3 hours.
Careful, don't let it boil dry (meat should fall apart).

title: kentucky bourbon sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add drained potatoes and remaining ingredients except marshmallows. Mash and beat until smooth.
Butter a 2-quart shallow baking dish. Pour mixture into dish.
Bake, uncovered, until hot.
Add marshmallows and put under broiler until golden and melted.

title: grandma nichols "meal in one"
directions: Place meat in roaster.
Slice onion and pepper.
Place on top of meat.
Pour tomatoes on top of meat.
Bake at 350° until meat is done. Add roni or rice and enjoy.

title: 1-2-3 rhubarb delight
directions: For the bottom layer:
Start with recipe for shortcake on Bisquick package.
To it add 1/4 cup margarine and to 1 egg add enough milk to make 1/2 cup of liquid and add.
Spread the mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan or baking dish.

title: sour cream sugar cookies
directions: Sprinkle with sugar before baking. Cool dough before rolling, it will handle better.
Mix as usual.
Roll to 1/4-inch thickness and cut as desired. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or golden brown.

title: deer meat loaf
directions: *One half pound pork sausage can be substituted for 1/2 pound venison for a more moist loaf.

title: sugar plum bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter, sugar and eggs. Sift together soda and flour. Add to mix alternately with buttermilk and lemon juice. Mix in orange slices, nuts and dates. Pour into greased mini bread pans. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or less. Very good!

title: delicious baked beans
directions: Cut up in small pieces 1/2 pound bacon.
Dump cut up bacon with all your onion into skillet and cook on medium-high until onion and bacon are cooked (about 5 minutes).
Set aside.
Drain all juice from canned beans and put beans in a long baking pan.
Dump bacon, onion and all drippings into beans.
Dump remaining 5 ingredients in order as given; stir well.
Slice remaining 1/2 pound bacon into one inch pieces.
Lay on top of beans, 1 piece at a time.
Bake at 375° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours (depending on how hot your oven is), until beans have baked down and bacon is crispy brown.
Feeds 10 to 15 people.

title: chicken and water chestnut casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts in water with a few celery tops. Cut chicken in large pieces. Combine all except stuffing mix and butter. Place in lightly buttered 9 x 13 pan.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add strawberries, bananas, pineapple and nuts.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish and chill.
When firm, spread on sour cream and gently spoon on the remaining jello mixture.
Return to refrigerator and chill until firm.

title: shorty's chicken
directions: Mix salsa and barbecue sauce together.
Pour over chicken. Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: canned boiled peanuts
directions: Fill quart jar with raw green peanuts.
Add salt.
Cover with water.
Seal.
Pressure cook for 1 hour at 10 to 15 pounds pressure.

title: butterfinger delight
directions: Mix your crumbs and oleo to make crust.
Save 1/4 of crumbs for topping.
Mix pudding, milk and ice cream together and put on top of crust.
Let chill for 1 hour.
Put Cool Whip on top of that.
Crush Butterfingers and mix with remaining crumbs and sprinkle on top.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix together and chill. Shape as desired and roll into chopped pecans or walnuts.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, stuffing, eggs and soup.
Add chicken broth.
Put in a large baking dish.
Melt margarine and pour over mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: First Layer:
In bottom of large pan, crumble up Doritos and spread generously.

title: just cookies
directions: Mix, then spoon on wax paper to cool.

title: cooked play dough(appropriate for even the littlest kids)
directions: Mix all ingredients in a medium size pot.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly with a metal spoon.
After about 5 minutes, the dough will become harder to stir and will gather on the spoon.
Dump the dough onto waxed paper; allow it to cool somewhat and knead about 10 times until smooth.
Store play dough in a tightly sealed container.
It will keep for up to 2 weeks.

title: italian or chili pie
directions: Press biscuits into 10 3/4 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Brown ground beef and add tomato sauce.
Spread over biscuits.
Sprinkle with grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: creamed chicken
directions: This recipe was served over noodles with applesauce on the side.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Place apples in 2-quart casserole.
Combine sugar and flour and toss with apple slices.
Add margarine, cover and microwave on High for 7 minutes or until apples are tender.
Add cinnamon and nutmeg.
Pour into pie crust and bake as regular apple pie.

title: scalloped potatoes supreme
directions: Blend soup and milk.
Arrange alternate layers of potatoes, onion and mushroom sauce, ending with sauce.
Cover with cheese, dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Remove cover and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer until browned.

title: chocolate fruit cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, butter, milk, cocoa and vanilla, then add flour.
Mix well, then add all remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Combine Cheddar cheese, eggs, salt, oregano, pepper, hamburger, onions and bread crumbs.
Stuff shells and lay in a pan.
Top with spaghetti sauce and American cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: church cole slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, water, pepper, onion and salt; let stand 1 hour. Then drain and add vinegar, oil, sugar and celery seed.
This will keep well.

title: nacho meat sauce
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet and then drain.
Mix remaining ingredients well and place into crock-pot on low for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Stir regularly.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese and mix until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients, except pecans.
Make into ball and then roll in crushed pecans.

title: critter crackers
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large roasting pan.
Pour butter evenly over mixture, tossing gently to coat.
Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool; store in an airtight container.
Yields 14 cups.

title: baked cranberry sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch baking dish, which has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Much better after frozen.
Makes a pretty gift for a neighbor if spooned into a pretty container.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries in water.
When soft, add sugar and cook 5 minutes.
Pour mixture over cherry Jell-O until dissolved.
Chill. When partially set, add celery, nutmeats and salt.
Serves 6.

title: tiny tuna puffs
directions: Prepare cream puff mix and bake according to package directions for bite size puffs.
Cool and split.
Let the onion stand in the lemon juice for 5 minutes. Combine it with tuna, salad dressing, curry powder and water chestnuts, adding salt and pepper to taste.
Fill the cream puffs. To serve, heat them on a jelly roll pan or other shallow pan in a hot oven at 400° for about 3 minutes or until the filling is hot through.
Makes about 60.

title: chicken and dumplings(aunt edna's)
directions: Add more broth, or a little water if needed

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Place onion in blender and chop.
Add sugar, mustard, salt and vinegar.
Blend well.
Add salad oil a small amount at a time, blending well after each addition.
Pour into a jar; add poppy seed.
Mix well.
Refrigerate.
Shake well.
Great served over fresh spinach and fresh strawberries.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Boil eggplant 10 minutes; cool, peel and chop eggplant.
In a large skillet saute onion, bell pepper and eggplant 15 minutes, then fold in meat, rice and spices.
Spray a 1 1/2-quart baking dish, put the mixture in dish.
Dot with margarine.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: cocktail sausages
directions: Blend together cranberry sauce, mustard and lemon juice in medium saucepan.
Heat on medium until hot.
Add cocktail sausages and cook until sausages are hot.
(This tastes like barbecue sauce!)

title: lime sticks
directions: Peel cucumbers; slice and seed them.
Use 7 1/2 pounds cucumber sticks.
Mix lime and water; pour over cucumbers.
Let stand cold for 24 hours.
Rinse 3 different times.
Cool waters; let stand in ice for 3 hours.
Pour off; drain real good.
Mix vinegar, sugar and pickling spice.
Heat until dissolved.
Let get cold; pour over pickles.
Let stand cold 12 hours.
Put on stove; boil hard for 30 minutes.
While cooking, add turmeric and food coloring.
Pack tight in jars and seal.
Makes 10 pints.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break spaghetti into 2-inch pieces and cook as directed on box.
Strain spaghetti.
Mix Italian dressing and spaghetti together.
Chop tomatoes, cucumbers, green peppers and purple onion; mix with spaghetti.
Marinate mixture overnight.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a mixing bowl; set aside.
Using a wooden spoon, beat together eggs, sugar, oil and thawed strawberries.
Beat well.
Add to dry ingredients.
Beat all ingredients together and bake in greased and floured loaf pans for about 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325° to 350°.
Makes two loaves.

title: chicken turnovers
directions: Prepare pastry by mixing together margarine, flour and cream cheese.
Chill.
Roll thin and cut into 2-inch rounds.
Put dab of chicken mixed with mushroom soup on rounds and fold over. Press edges with a fork and prick pastry.
Sprinkle with paprika before baking.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Yields about 200 small turnovers.
These turnovers may be frozen before or after baking

title: best nachos ever
directions: Mix rice and beans together; spread along the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Sprinkle mixture with Jack cheese.
Cover with tortilla chips.
Sprinkle chips with Cheddar cheese.
Top cheese with olives.
Bake in oven at 350° until all is heated.
Mash avocados and serve with salsa.
Can use refried beans instead of black beans (optional).

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems.
Dip caps in melted butter and place upside-down in a shallow baking pan.
Finely chop 1/4 cup of the mushroom stems and saute with the green onions in remaining butter, adding more butter, if necessary.
Add water or wine.
Lightly stir in stuffing.
Spoon mixture into caps.
Bake at 350° until hot, about 10 minutes.
Makes about 18.

title: beef patties diane
directions: Shape beef into 4 oval patties about 3/4 inch thick.
Melt butter over medium heat; add patties and brown until done as you like them.
Remove.
Add parsley, chives and brandy.
Simmer 1 minute.
Add broth and Worcestershire sauce.
Salt and pepper to taste and pour over steaks.

title: date walnut crisp
directions: Put dates; cut in small pieces.
Chop nuts.
Cream sugars and shortening.
Add flavorings.
Beat in eggs; add dates and nuts. Add dry ingredients.
Makes a stiff dough.
Shape in balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: tutti fruitti
directions: Blend pudding in with pineapple, oranges and fruit cocktail (use juice also).
Chill.
Just before serving, slice in bananas. Top with Cool Whip.

title: crazy salad
directions: Cook macaroni shells following package directions.
Drain well.
Cool to room temperature.

title: "can't stop" cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add dry ingredients.
Fold in corn flakes and nuts.
Roll into balls and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
These cookies are quick and easy and everyone loves them!

title: brunch bites
directions: Mix all ingredients; spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake until golden brown in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Makes approximately 50 squares.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Chill dough and roll into balls.
Roll each ball into mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Place on cookie sheet two inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Early in day or day ahead:
Trim any fat from round steak and cut meat crosswise into strips about 1/2-inch thick.
In medium bowl for marinade, combine soy sauce, bouillon cube, ginger, garlic powder and one cup boiling water; stir in meat strips.
Cover and refrigerate, stirring occasionally.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Boil sugar, butter, syrup, salt and vanilla for 5 minutes. Remove from heat; add soda and pour over popped corn in a large roasting pan, coating well.
Cook in oven at 250° for 1 hour. Stir every 20 minutes.
Store in airtight containers.
Add peanuts to popcorn if desired.

title: new england dinner
directions: Put roast into Dutch oven to which 2 teaspoons oil have been added.
Brown on both sides.
Cover with the water.
Add the salt, pepper and bay leaves.
Simmer until fork-tender.
Add the quartered potatoes, carrots cut into 2-inch pieces and use small onions (whole).
Cut celery in 2-inch pieces.
Cover and cook for 20 minutes longer.
Cut cabbage in eighths.
Lay around on top and simmer about 20 minutes more or until fork-tender.
Do not overcook.
Take meat and all vegetables out and put on platter. Thicken gravy slightly with cornstarch.
Pour over all and enjoy.

title: ambrosia mold
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve liquid.
Add cold water to juice to equal 1 cup.
Stir boiling water into jello in large bowl until completely dissolved.
Stir in measured liquid.
Refrigerate for 1 1/4 hours, until slightly thickened.
Stir in Cool Whip with wire whisk until smooth.
Refrigerate for 10 minutes.
Stir in oranges, pineapple, marshmallows and coconut.
Spoon into a 6-cup mold. Refrigerate for 4 hours.
Unmold.

title: whole cauliflower au gratin
directions: Core cauliflower and cook head down in salt water until tender, about 10 minutes. A small amount of lemon in water keeps head white.
Drain well.
Heat butter; add bread crumbs and onion. Cook until crumbs are toasted. Add cheese.
Place cauliflower in casserole and put crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: In large heavy pan, lightly brown beef and onion in oil.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, water, parsley, salt, sugar, garlic powder, pepper and oregano.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, about 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook lasagne as directed.
Drain.
In 13 x 9 baking pan, spread about 1 cup sauce. Alternate layers of lasagne, sauce, cottage cheese, Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes, until lightly browned and bubbling.
Allow to stand for 15 minutes.
Cut in squares to serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: marinated pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni 7 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Drain and rinse well with cold water.
Add marinade to macaroni; mix well and keep in fridge overnight.
Next day, add 1 or 2 diced cucumbers, 1 small diced onion, 1 green, red or yellow diced pepper and a few stalks diced celery.
Mix and enjoy and keep in container with cover in fridge.
Will keep 1 to 2 weeks.

title: velvet cream cake
directions: Reserve 1 cup dry frosting mix.
Add 2 cups frosting mix to 1 1/2 cups whipping cream and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Stir and refrigerate.
Mix and bake cake according to directions, making 2 layers.
Split cooled cake layers to make 4 layers.
Whip frosting and cream mixture until thick.
Fill cake layers, using 1/3 of cream mixture on each layer.
Blend remaining dry frosting mixture with 2 or 3 tablespoons hot water and 1 tablespoon corn syrup. Pour over top of cake and let drizzle down sides.
Place cake in freezer an hour or so to set cream filling, then refrigerate cake until last delicious slice is eaten.

title: butterfinger bars
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Melt the chocolate chips and peanut butter and spread over the bars. Cool and cut into bars.

title: apple nut bread
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs with mixer.
Add flour, baking soda, salt and vanilla.
Mix with a spoon.
Add apples and nuts. Bake in loaf pans at 350° for 60 minutes.
Makes 2 to 3 loaves.

title: chocolate pecan pie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, stir together flour and 2 tablespoons brown sugar.
Cut in 1/2 cup butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs; press onto bottom and about 1-inch up sides of 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set.
With back of spoon, lightly press crust into corners and against sides of pan.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Steam zucchini and onion for five minutes.
Combine soup, sour cream, mayonnaise and carrots.
Add to zucchini and onion.

title: meat balls and green peppers
directions: Combine milk and bread crumbs in mixing bowl.
Add ground beef, salt, pepper and celery salt.
Mix thoroughly and shape into 12 balls.
Roll in flour.
Fry in skillet with oleo until brown. Add green peppers and onions.
Brown lightly.
Add boiling water and beef cubes.
Cover.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Brown and drain ground beef in a large frying pan. Add sour cream, chicken soup and green chilies. Simmer on low heat. Mix cheese and onion together. Layer in large dish the beef mix, then tortillas, cheese and onion mixture. Repeat layers, ending with cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. May cover with foil. Top with lettuce and tomatoes and green pepper.

title: lemon loaf bread
directions: Mix shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and lemon rind.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to shortening mixture, along with milk.
Mix together well.
Put in loaf pan. Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.
While baking mix lemon juice and powdered sugar.
When loaf is done, spoon lemon juice mixture over loaf while hot.
Cool in pan.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Can be served in a hollowed out loaf of bread also.

title: pea casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cracker crumbs.
Place in casserole.
Cover with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: breakfast donuts
directions: In mixing bowl, cream 1/3 cup butter with 1/2 cup sugar; beat in egg.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg together.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients into butter and sugar mixture.
Fill greased muffin cups 3/4 full of batter.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, until golden.
In small bowl, mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Immediately after baking, roll donuts in melted butter and then in sugar/cinnamon mixture.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake as directed;
cool
and slice horizontally to make four layers.
In large bowl, combine coconut, sour cream, sugars, pineapple and
vanilla.
Reserve
cups of this mixture. Fill cake
layers
with remainder.
Add Cool Whip to the reserved mixture and frost sides and top of cake.
Refrigerate at least
24 hours
before
serving.
Will
keep in the refrigerator several days.

title: french toast
directions: Mix well.
Dip slices of bread into mixture and cook in hot, sprayed skillet.
Serve, topped with syrup, fruit or powdered sugar.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix all ingredients, except soup.
Shape into a loaf and chill overnight.
Cut into 1/4 to 1/2-inch slices.
Roll in flour; brown both sides.
Put in baking dish.
Make gravy with drippings adding one can of cream of mushroom soup; pour over meat.
Bake 2 hours at 250°.

title: dreamy pumpkin pie
directions: Combine in saucepan sugar, gelatine, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg.
Add yolks and milk and cook, stirring constantly until slightly thick. Add pumpkin and nuts.
Chill, stirring often. Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Add 1/3 cup sugar, then fold chilled pumpkin into egg whites.
Put into crust.
Garnish with whipped cream and coconut to serve.

title: cinnamon logs
directions: Stack slices of bread together.
Cut off crusts and divide into three equal strips.
Brush with melted butter and roll in the mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Place on a cookie sheet in 350° oven until sugar has melted (about 5 minutes).
Arrange on plate and serve hot.

title: chipped beef cheese ball
directions: Grate chipped beef.
Mix other ingredients and put most of beef in center of cream cheese that has been formed into a ball.
Roll ball in rest of beef.

title: city club salad dressing
directions: Mix sugar, honey and seasonings.
Gradually add oil and vinegar alternately, beating with a blender.
Perfect topping for fruit, especially grapefruit and avocado.

title: mama's peanut butter fudge
directions: Put sugar, butter and milk in an electric skillet set at 280°. Bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Turn off heat.
Add marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour into a buttered 8-inch pan and let cool.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: vegetable skillet supper
directions: Fry bacon in skillet until crisp.
Remove.
Drain on paper towel.
Crumble.
Saute ground beef and onion in 2 tablespoons of bacon fat until meat is well browned.
Add tomatoes, water, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, potatoes, green pepper, cabbage, celery and bacon.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Boil until thick the margarine, milk and sugar.
Add marshmallows.
When melted add cracker crumbs, pecans and coconut. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: millionaires
directions: Unwrap caramels and melt over double boiler, adding the 2 tablespoons of milk.
After caramels have melted completely, add pecan pieces.
Drop by tablespoon onto wax paper.
Over double boiler, melt chocolate chips and Gulfwax.
After chocolate has melted, drop the caramel clusters into chocolate and put back on wax paper.
Let set for at least 1 hour.

title: crawfish stuffed bell pepper
directions: In food processor, grind crawfish tails, onion, 1/2 bell pepper, garlic and stale bread.
Mix together in large bowl and add eggs, parsley, salt and pepper and bread crumbs.
Mix together well.
Clean and hull about 4 to 6 bell peppers, then parboil. Then stuff crawfish mixture in bell pepper.
Top with a little bread crumbs and dot with a little margarine.
Bake in 375° oven for about 25 to 35 minutes.

title: sour cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with sour cream.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Roll dough 1/2 to 1/4-inch thick on floured cloth.
Cut with large biscuit cutter.
Place on greased cookie sheet and sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Bake in a 410° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Place cookie sheet on top rack of oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Bake smaller cookies 7 to 8 minutes.
Place cookie sheet on top rack of oven to prevent the cookies from becoming too brown.
They are best rather pale and soft.
Check frequently to prevent overcooking.

title: chicken blue grass
directions: Dip chicken in flour; pound flat.
Wrap in ham and cheese slices.
Place in baking dish.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: all occasion cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients and mix well.
Add oil, eggs, pineapple and 1/2 cup coconut.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until tests done.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix tapioca pudding mix and strawberry juice; bring to a boil. Turn down heat and let simmer until thickens.
Cool.
Add strawberries.

title: cranberry cake
directions: Put cranberries in bottom of a well-greased pie pan.
Combine 1/2 cup of sugar and 1/2 cup pecans and sprinkle over cranberries. Add 1 cup of sugar and beaten eggs.
Add flour and melted fats. Mix well and pour over cranberries; stir slightly.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: anadama bread
directions: Bring salted water to boil in saucepan.
Add cornmeal, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in molasses and shortening.
Cook to lukewarm.
Mix yeast with 1/4 cup water and let stand 5 minutes.
Blend yeast into cornmeal mixture, then mix in flour first with a spoon, then by hand.
Dough will be sticky. Knead and let rise until double (1 1/2 hours).
Punch down and turn into greased loaf pan.
Let rise until double (about 1 hour). Brush top with melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes. Makes 1 loaf.
May be frozen.

title: win schulers bar cheese
directions: Put all ingredients into top of double boiler and melt.
Pour into container and refrigerate.

title: buttered fresh asparagus with lemon zest
directions: Clean and cook asparagus.
Meantime, melt butter and add the juice of 1/2 the lemon and the zest of the whole lemon, reserving some for garnish.
Arrange asparagus in serving dish and pour butter mixture over.
Garnish with more zest.
I have found the best way to cook asparagus is in an electric percolator.
Tie the asparagus in a bundle with enough cord to hang on the outside. The stalks are in the water and the heads steam.
When it is done, just pull them out with the string.

title: peaches jean
directions: Arrange drained peaches in casserole dish.
Place rounded teaspoonful of mincemeat in center of peach half.
Spoon peach syrup over halves.
Heat at 250° to 275° until warm.

title: anna's favorite kit kat bars
directions: Place 1 layer of Club crackers in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix first 5 ingredients together and bring to boil and boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour 1/2 of mixture over crackers, cover with another layer of crackers.
Pour the rest of mixture over second layer and cover with another layer club crackers. Melt chips and peanut butter and pour over all.
Cool and cut. Yield depends on sizes cut.

title: fruit dip
directions: In small bowl, mix cream cheese, sugars, syrup and sour cream. Mix until smooth.
Chill.
Good with fresh fruit.

title: brown edge cookies(makes 3 dozen)
directions: Cream butter and mix well with sugar.
Add unbeaten egg whites. Add flour gradually.
Add vanilla.
Drop batter by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven until edges are brown (about 10 minutes, checking after 5 minutes).
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar while still hot.

title: pumpkin nut cookies(this is a good cookie for trick or treaters.)
directions: In a bowl, cream well the shortening and sugar.
Add the egg and pumpkin; mix well.
Sift into bowl the flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and ginger; mix well.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet and bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat water to boiling.
Remove from heat. Stir in rice.
Cover; let stand for 5 minutes.
Blend eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Gradually stir in milk.
Mix in rice and raisins.
Pour into ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake for about 70 minutes, until knife comes out clean.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together by hand.
Form into balls the size of walnuts.
Place on greased (lightly) cookie sheet, leaving room for balls to spread.
Cook at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Yields 100 balls.

title: german chocolate cream cheese cake
directions: Mix cake mix, egg, butter and nuts together then pat out in cake pan.
Mix confectioners sugar, eggs and cream cheese; pour over cake mix.
Bake for 1 hour on 300° or until golden brown.

title: pistachio fruit dream
directions: Mix fruit cocktail with pudding.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Top with maraschino cherries and chill in refrigerator. Can add 1 cup miniature marshmallows.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Mix together soup (no water), chili, onions and sour cream. Soften tortillas.
Place mixed cheeses and 1 tablespoon of sauce inside tortillas.
Roll up and secure with a toothpick. Put in baking dish.
After all the tortillas have been filled, pour the remainder of the sauce over the top.
Cover with remainder of the cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: lemon broiled fish
directions: Combine margarine and
ReaLemon. In medium bowl, combine bread crumbs, parsley and 1/4 cup of the ReaLemon mixture.
Add paprika to remaining ReaLemon mixture. Dip fish into paprika mixture. Broil until fish flakes with fork.
Top with bread crumb mixture. Return to broiler.
Heat through.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pickled beets
directions: Bring ingredients to a boil, then shut off.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Keep refrigerated until serving time.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a huge bowl.
Add beaten eggs, oil and buttermilk; stir well.

title: western beans
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Combine remaining ingredients. Cook in oven at 350° until done.
Makes a large amount.
Freezes well.

title: boiled custard
directions: Beat eggs with mixer; mix 2 tablespoons flour and 1/2 cup sugar and mix well.
Put sugar and flour in eggs and 1/3 teaspoon salt. Add 1 cup cold milk to this.
Put 3 cups milk in double boiler and let it get hot.
Then add mixture to hot milk.
Cook until coats spoon.

title: curried baked cauliflower
directions: Cook broken cauliflower in water until almost done; drain. Stir undiluted soup, cheese, mayo and curry powder.
Add cauliflower and mix.
Put into a 2-quart buttered casserole.
Toss bread crumbs with butter; sprinkle on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: triple layer tennessee jam cake
directions: Beat the first 6 ingredients at low speed with an electric mixer for 1 minute.
Scrape down sides, and beat at medium speed 2 more minutes until well blended, stopping to scrape down sides, if needed.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9- inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 23 minutes or until cakes are light brown and spring back when lightly pressed with your fingers.
Cool in pans on wire racks for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans; cool completely on wire racks.
Place one layer on a serving platter. Spread with 1/2 c. blackberry jam, leaving 1/2 inch border.
Spread a smooth, thin layer of warm Quick Caramel Icing over jam.	Repeat layers.
Top with third cake layer.
Spread top and sides of cake with remaining icing, working quickly before the frosting hardens. (If frosting becomes to hard to spread, place it over low heat for 1 minute, stirring constantly.)
Let cake cool 10 minutes.

title: holiday fruit cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs together.
Stir in milk.
Sift together flour, salt and soda; stir into creamed mixture.
Add pecans, cherries and dates.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and pudding; stir well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: tomato salad
directions: Chop and seed the tomatoes, green pepper and onion.
Mix oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Mix all ingredients.
Place in Tupperware bowl with lid.
Place in refrigerator for a couple hours before serving.

title: old fashioned corn pudding
directions: Grease a 6-cup baking dish.
Saute onion in butter.
Add corn. Mix flour with 1/2 cup half and half.
Add remaining ingredients, including eggs.
Stir in corn mixture.
Pour into baking dish. Put baking dish in shallow pan on oven rack.
Add water to pan to come halfway up the sides of baking casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until firm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: english pea casserole
directions: In bottom of a greased 1-quart casserole dish, put half of the peas, then half of the sliced eggs, half of pimiento and half of the cheese.
Repeat, using the rest of each of these four ingredients.
Dilute the soup according to the directions on the can for making a sauce.
Pour over the layers in the casserole dish.
Sprinkle the bread crumbs over the top.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Combine syrup, sugar and margarine and cook until it comes to a boil.
Add cream of tartar and soda.
Remove from heat.
Pour over popped corn and bake about 1 hour at 200°, stirring every 15 minutes to coat popcorn well.

title: hot pepper franks
directions: Bring to boil catsup, vinegar, sugar, oil, salt and garlic. Add hot peppers and weiners.
Cook 10 minutes after it starts to boil.

title: molded chicken salad
directions: Dissolve Knox gelatine and 1/4 cup cold water over hot water. Mix dissolved gelatine, chicken, celery, mayonnaise, cream and almonds together and chill until firm, using either a 9 x 9-inch pan or 2-quart casserole.
When set, dissolve jello in 2 cups of boiling water.
Add relish and pour over top of chicken.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini in half lengthwise.
Hollow out, chop and fry with garlic and onion to taste.
Drain.
Add to cooked ground beef, egg, bread crumbs, cheese and salt and pepper to taste; mix well.
Pack into zucchini shells.
Spoon about 1/4 cup tomato sauce over each zucchini.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes (cover for last 10 minutes).

title: caramel oatmeal cookie bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine oats, flour, brown sugar, soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in margarine, mixing well, until blended.
Reserve 1 cup; press rest onto bottom of pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown; cool 10 minutes.
Top with nuts and chips to within 1/4 of pan edges.

title: cucumber rings
directions: Combine cream cheese, chives, parsley, mayo, paprika and lemon juice.
With apple corer, scoop out insides of cucumber.
Fill with cheese mixture.
Refrigerate.
Slice 1/4 inch thick.
Makes 24 rings.

title: chocolate torte
directions: Melt butter.
Mix in a bowl, butter, pecans and flour.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° until light brown (10 minutes).
Cool 15 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and cool.
Whip Milnot until stiff.
Cream the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Combine everything until well mixed.
Pour into crust; sprinkle with a few crumbs or top with cherry or blueberry topping.
Cover and chill 24 hours.

title: black bottom pie
directions: Beat egg, 1/2 cup sugar and 1/8 teapooon salt with wire whisk. Add cream cheese and beat well.
With wooden spoon, stir in chocolate chips and refrigerate at least 1/2 hour.
Sift together dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add liquids and beat well by hand.
In paper lined muffin tins, put batter in each, filling 1/3 full.
Place 1 heaping teaspoonful of the refrigerated cheese mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: maureen's broccoli salad
directions: Combine ingredients in large salad bowl.

title: q me quick
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers.
Cut onion into rings.
Mix together slaw dressing and add about 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/2 cup apple cider vinegar.
Taste for your own tart or sweetness desired.
Mix with cucumbers and onion.
Let chill for at least 1 hour so flavor mixes.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Cut up into small pieces.
Mix together chicken soup, mushroom soup and Ro-Tel.
Pour over chicken in casserole dish.
Crush tortilla chips on top of soup mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Combine salad dressing, Parmesan and milk; mix well.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Chill well. Serve on lettuce.

title: blackberry jello dessert
directions: Mix Jell-O as directed, using blueberry juice to Jell-O as part of water for mixing Jell-O.
Add blueberries, nuts and pineapple.
Refrigerate until congealed.

title: brown rice stuffing
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Heat corn oil in frypan.
Add onions and cook until translucent.
Add sunflower seeds and cook 1 minute to brown.
Add rest of ingredients.
Stir and simmer about 15 minutes.
Add cooled rice and toss to mix well.

title: chicken lickin' good pork chops(crock-pot)
directions: Moisten pork chops with water.
Sprinkle seasoned salt, garlic and pepper lightly over each side of pork chops.
Roll in flour. Heat oil in pan and brown chops on both sides.
Place diluted cream of chicken soup in crock-pot, then add pork chops.
Cover and cook 6 to 8 hours on low or 4 hours on high.
Meat comes out very tender and makes great gravy for mashed potatoes!

title: linguine salad
directions: *Don't try to use a substitute seasoning.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Chop fine the tomato, pepper, cucumber and onion.
Mix all ingredients.
Make it several days ahead.
Stir every day.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until firm in the middle (30 minutes).

title: super venison roast
directions: Combine salt and water to cover steak.
Let soak for 2 hours. Drain; rinse and pat dry.
Combine seasoned salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Sprinkle on both sides of roast.
Sprinkle with soy sauce.
Place onion slices on top of roast and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of flour.
Place pats of margarine on onions.
Wrap roast twice in heavy aluminum foil.
Place in roasting pan; add 1 quart water.
Cover and bake at 350° for 4 to 5 hours.
Add water to roasting pan if necessary, but do not open foil.
Remove roast from pan.
Carefully open foil and measure liquid.
Combine
1 1/2 tablespoons flour and 2 tablespoons water for each cup of liquid.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and pick chicken.
Boil broccoli.
Put broccoli, then chicken in casserole dish.
Mix 2 soups and mayo.
Pour mixture over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: To make spread, mix together softened cream cheese with all other ingredients except boiled ham.
Spread mixture on ham.
Roll up longwise and cut in 3/4-inch slices.
Secure with toothpick.

title: impossible vegetable pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease pie plate (10-inch). Cook broccoli or cauliflower
in
salted
water for 5 minutes; drain. Mix broccoli, onion,
green
pepper
and cheese in pie plate. Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 1 minute with beater. Pour into pie plate.

title: pumpkin nut bars
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl; add next 2 ingredients.
Beat on medium speed of electric mixer 1 minute or until smooth.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan; bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool; sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into bars to serve.
Yields about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, pour and spread pie filling or applesauce; next, pour and spread complete can of pineapple.
Make sure bottom of pan is covered, then sprinkle cake mix over mixture evenly.
Take the butter and dot the top of the cake mix until all butter is used.
Sprinkle with pecans (optional); cook approximately 30 minutes or until top is golden brown and cake is crunchy.
May be topped with Cool Whip.

title: pork tenderloin
directions: Place meat in a deep dish. Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Baste often.

title: muskingum chocolate dew cake
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients together several times.
Mix cold water and mayonnaise well.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add vanilla. Pour into 2 (8-inch) cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Test with a toothpick.

title: pina colada slush
directions: Mix, freeze and add sweet or sour to each glass.

title: apricot balls
directions: Mix apricots and raisins in a bowl, sprinkle cream and Amaretto over them and let stand overnight.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Blend well and roll into balls.
Roll in sugar. Makes 3 dozen.

title: beer batter for seafood
directions: Mix in bowl flour and baking soda. Add beer a little at a time to make a pancake like batter. Coat seafood in batter and pan fry or deep fry till done.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix and put in casserole.
Lay slices of Monterey cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: frozen bread caramel rolls
directions: Thaw but do not permit to rise the 2 loaves of frozen bread. Break 1 loaf up in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt butter, then add brown sugar, pudding mix, milk and cinnamon.
Mix all together.
Then pour half over broken bread.
Break second loaf on top of first and let rise for approximately 1 hour.
Bake at 300° for approximately 25 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes, then turn out on wax paper.

title: sugar-free banana cream pie
directions: Slice bananas into cooled pie shell.
Prepare pie filling as directed for pie, using 2 1/2 cups cold milk.
Fold in 1/2 cup of the whipped topping.
Garnish with banana slices on top, if desired.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni. Mix dry dressing mix with 1/2 cup water. Mix all ingredients together and toss. Make at least 8 hours before serving.

title: beans and hot dogs
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a 2-quart dish in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix apple pie filling and cinnamon; set aside.
Beat together the flour, granulated sugar, salt, baking powder, milk, margarine and eggs on low speed for 30 seconds.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Pour 1/2 batter in pan (about 2 cups).
Spoon 1/2 pie filling over batter.
Repeat with remaining batter and pie filling.
Sprinkle brown sugar and nuts over mixture.
Drizzle melted butter.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: 4 hour beef stew
directions: Combine beef and vegetables in a casserole.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix tomato sauce and water with tapioca.
Pour over beef and mix.
Cover and bake at 275° for 4 hours.

title: najuaua's orange chipolet ribs
directions: Wash ribs well.
Put salt, pepper, Five Spice, Dale's and Italian dressing on meat to marinate.
Wrap in foil and put in refrigerator overnight.
Heat grill or smoker.
Place meat on grill for 3 to 4 hours.
Add soaked wood chips.
Close lid and cook, turning every hour.

title: potato candy
directions: Peel the potato and boil until tender.
Mash the potato; add enough powdered sugar until it is rollable.
Roll out the potato/sugar mixture to about 1/4-inch thick.
Spread thin layer of peanut butter on the rolled out mixture.
Then make a jelly roll. Chill and then cut into about 1/8 to 1/4-inch slices.
Makes a very flavorful swirled candy.

title: italian bread
directions: Finely chop onions and peppers.
Put in a jar.
Add 1 tablespoon vinegar and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Let sit in refrigerator overnight.
Brown meats together; season with salt and pepper (garlic salt is good).
Roll bread dough out in a circle.
Sprinkle meat over bread.
Then onions and peppers and then grated cheese.
Roll like a jelly roll.
Let sit on a cookie sheet for 30 minutes.
Brush with melted butter and bake for 30 minutes (until brown) at 350°.

title: dream whip cheese cake
directions: Whip the Dream Whip.
Add softened cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Then whip it again.
Spoon onto a crust.
Add any topping. Chill.

title: hamburger summer sausage
directions: Mix well, cover and refrigerate.
Take out once a day and mix well for 3 days.
The fourth day form into rolls and lay on broiler pan rack.
Bake for 12 hours at 140° to 150°, turning once during baking.
Hamburger works better than ground round, as you need the fat.

title: rice krispie treats
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat. Add rice cereal.
Stir until well coated.
Spray a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with cooking spray.
Using a buttered spatula or waxed paper, press mixture evenly into pan.
Cut squares when cool.
Makes 24 treats, 2 x 2-inches.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in casserole dish.
Crumble Ritz crackers on top.
Pour melted margarine over cracker crumbs.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Saute beef, onions and peppers.
Add rest of ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise and mustard in large bowl.
Stir in envelopes of Spring Vegetable recipe blend, water chestnuts and green onions.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
To serve, stir well and spoon into hollowed bread rounds. Arrange bread cubes, crackers or fresh vegetable pieces around bread for dipping.

title: bow wow biscuits
directions: In a large bowl or food processor container, combine flour, wheat germ, dry milk, salt, garlic powder and brown sugar.
Cut in or process drippings into mixture until mixture is crumbly.
Add egg and broth, through a feeder tube with machine running if a processor is used, and mix thoroughly.
Add ice water as needed to form mixture into a ball.
If processor is used, add water through feeder tube with machine running, just until mixture leaves the side of the bowl and starts forming a ball.
Pat out dough on floured surface to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with cookie cutters and place on cookie sheet lined with foil and lightly oiled.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until quite hard and brown at edges. Makes about 18 large biscuits.

title: bologna stew
directions: Chop onion.
Cut 5 potatoes into large wedges and 5 potatoes into small pieces.
Place all ingredients into a large boiler and add about 2 quarts of water or until ingredients are covered.
Add salt, pepper, soy sauce and hot sauce to taste.
Cook on high heat until the potatoes and onions are tender.
Simmer until stew thickens.

title: party mix
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Melt butter in shallow pan.
Stir in sauce and salt.
Add Chex and nuts.
Stir until all is covered.
Bake 15 minutes.
Remove and stir occasionally for 1 hour.
Pour onto a paper towel and cool.
Store in a closed container.

title: white clam sauce
directions: *This is the most important ingredient.

title: peanut butter and jelly cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: walnut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix brown sugar and flour in a saucepan.
Add corn syrup, butter and salt.
Warm these ingredients over low heat until the butter melts.
In large bowl, beat the eggs and vanilla.
Stir in and add sugar mixture to the eggs.
Pour all ingredients into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes on the low oven rack.

title: ham chowder
directions: Put 2 quarts water in large soup kettle.
Add onion and ham to water and boil 1/2 hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until potatoes are tender, then mash with back of spoon about half of the potatoes to help thicken broth.
Add half and half and serve hot.
Good with fresh bread.

title: english pea salad
directions: In medium bowl, mix peas, cheese, olives, cashews, bacon and onions.
In small bowl, blend sour cream, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Add to peas; mix and coat gently and chill.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook green pepper, onion and rice in oil until lightly browned, stirring constantly.
Dissolve bouillon cube in hot water; add to rice mixture along with tomato sauce, tomatoes and meat.
Mix and bring to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 10 minutes.

title: cool and creamy
directions: First Layer:
Combine flour, margarine and nuts.
Press evenly into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly golden brown.
Cool.

title: microwave pickles(bread and butter)
directions: Thinly slice unpeeled cucumber and onion.
Place in microwavable bowl.
In another bowl, mix sugar, vinegar, turmeric, salt and mustard seed.
Pour this mixture over cucumbers and onions.
Microwave for 8 minutes, stirring a couple of times. Pour into sterilized fruit jars and seal.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix, heat and serve hot.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast	in
cup
lukewarm water.
In large bowl put Crisco.
Add egg, sugar and salt.
Blend well.	Add 1 cup cold water
and yeast mixture.
Add flour until mixture is like biscuit
dough.
Turn

bowl
and
knead.
After kneading, place in
greased bowl in refrigerator.
Set out and let rise before baking at 350° until brown.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Line large Pyrex baking dish with graham crackers.
Top with half of whipped topping and vanilla instant pudding mixture.
Add another layer of graham crackers and remainder of whipped topping/vanilla instant pudding mixture.
Top with another layer of graham crackers.

title: apple crumble
directions: Place sliced apples in greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Blend remaining ingredients until mixture is crumbly. Spread over apples. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Combine flour, oatmeal, brown sugar and margarine in bowl until crumbly.
Press into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Combine pumpkin, cinnamon, evaporated milk, eggs and sugar.
Beat well and pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: tasty dried beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Melt butter in a saucepan. Add onion and green pepper. Cook until tender, about 5 minutes.
Cut dried beef into small pieces. Add to onion mixture and continue cooking until brown. Stir in soup, milk, pepper and paprika.
Heat to boiling.
Combine macaroni with beef sauce.
Put in casserole. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar and corn syrup together in microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Add peanuts and microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla and microwave on High for 1 minute.
Add baking soda and stir until light and foamy.
Quickly pour on buttered cookie sheet.
Cool.
Break into small pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: easy made chili
directions: In large skillet, saute ground beef and onion, stirring frequently until meat is tender. Drain off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve topped with shredded cheese, chopped chili peppers, and sliced green onions, as desired.

title: banofee pie
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar, ginger and melted butter until well blended. Press mixture into a 9-inch pie plate. Cool in refrigerator.

title: basic divinity
directions: In heavy, 2-quart saucepan, stir together the sugar, corn syrup, water and salt.
Cook over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Avoid splashing the syrup on sides of pan.
Cook, without stirring, to hard ball stage.
Remove from heat immediately.

title: mother quinn's fruitcake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add 1/2 cup sweet cream.
Line pan with greased paper and bake in slow oven 4 hours.

title: vegetable wreath
directions: You will also need 1 styrofoam wreath or tree for base.

title: floating island(isla flotante)
directions: Beat egg yolks with the 4 tablespoons of sugar; add cornstarch.
Heat the milk and add the yolk mixture, stirring well.
Cook until it thickens.
Pour in a bowl and add the vanilla.
Place in refrigerator.
In a large pot (the ocean), mix sugar, corn syrup and water and then boil until it reaches the "thread stage".
Beat with a mixer 4 egg whites until peak forms. Slowly add the syrup, beating well.
Grease a baking dish with margarine and bake at 275° to 300° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate.
Serve in a bowl on top of your meringue (Island).

title: pecan waffles
directions: Preheat waffle iron.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt. Set aside (use medium bowl).
In large mixing bowl, beat egg yolks, milk and salad oil.
Gradually add flour mixture, a little at a time.
In small bowl, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form when beater is raised.
With rubber scraper, fold egg whites into batter mixture.
Stir in pecans.

title: baked cheese
directions: Layer ingredients as follows:
Cream cheese, chili or refried beans, Monterey Jack (shredded), Monterey Jack with hot peppers, shredded.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Mix butter with sugar.
Add flour.
Mix with hands.
Chill. Roll out 1/2-inch.
Cut and bake on ungreased sheet at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Tops will not brown.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Place fruit in 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 the sugar mixed with the cinnamon over fruit.
Melt butter slightly.
Mix in cream cheese, vanilla and rest of sugar.
Beat in egg, then buttermilk baking mix.
Spread mixture evenly over fruit.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: apple butter
directions: Wash and core apples; cut into eighths.
Into blender container put 1/3 cup cider and 4 to 5 pieces of apple.
Blend on liquify for 5 seconds.
Open container and add approximately 1/3 of the apple pieces.
Blend on liquify for 30 seconds.
Empty container into saucepan.
Repeat twice more using 1/3 cup cider and 1/3 of the apple pieces each time.
When all apples are blended, add sugar and spices, then cook mixture over low heat, approximately 45 minutes or until thick, stirring occasionally. Pour immediately into sterilized jars and seal.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat, pepper and onion.
When done, add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
A short time before casserole is done, sprinkle potato chips on top and return to oven for at least ten minutes.

title: mixed pickles or chow chow
directions: Chop the tomatoes, onions, cabbage and peppers up fine.
Mix well.
Cover with good cider vinegar and add spices.
(If spice is fine powder, just add to the mixture.
If not, you might want to put them in a small cloth sack.)
Cook very slowly until done over very low heat.
Stir a lot to prevent scorching.

title: stay out of the sun egyptian tomato dip
directions: In a blender, mix tomato sauce, garbanzo beans and yogurt until smooth.
Pour into a small bowl.
Stir in garlic, onion, parsley, horseradish, cumin, curry powder and paprika.
Cover and refrigerate 8 to 24 hours to allow flavors to blend and acquire that great Middle Eastern flavor!
Serve with crisp vegetables.

directions: Preheat
oven

Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.

and boiling water.
Add and blend well. Pour into prepared pans and bake for about 35 minutes or until done.
Frost with My Mother's Caramel Icing.

title: chinese rice casserole
directions: Cut steak or pork into small cubes and brown in oil in a skillet.
Drain pimentos and mushrooms.
Add to steak.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cover skillet or put into casserole dish and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: marie choplin's corned beef mold("the best")
directions: Stir lemon Jell-O into 1 cup of boiling water until dissolved. Remove from stove and let mixture cool. Mix with the remaining ingredients and pour into a mold. Refrigerate overnight.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Put potatoes in saucepan; add carrots.
Add boiling water to barely cover.
Add salt; cover and cook about 10 minutes.
Add green beans; cover and cook 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms and continue cooking about 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add margarine; season to taste with salt and pepper.
Makes 4 servings.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt butter and chocolate chips.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Add slowly the Rice Chex.
Coat well.
Put powdered sugar in a brown grocery sack.
Add mixture; shake well to coat.
Put out on wax paper to dry.

title: cherry rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix well.
Press into 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: spiked kielbasa
directions: Cut kielbasa in 2 1/2 inch pieces on the diagonal; place in large skillet with beer.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
In small bowl stir together sugar, cornstarch, mustard and horseradish.
Add to skillet; bring to boil for 1 minute, until thickened.
Makes 6 to 8 servings, 475 calories for 6 servings.

title: pork chops in gravy
directions: Rub pork chops with salt and pepper. Place in heated skillet with tightly fitting lid. Melt enough butter in pan to keep chops from sticking; brown chops quickly. Combine soup and water pour over chops. When mixture returns to boil, reduce heat to very low. Simmer slowly for 1 hour or until chops are tender. Serve with rice or potatoes.

title: baby hot browns
directions: Arrange bread slices on a lightly greased baking sheet. Broil 6 inches from heat for 3-4 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients, except grated cheese and peppers. Pour 1/2 of mixture in large oiled pan.
Cover generously with sliced hot banana peppers.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese. Add remaining batter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Let set 10 to 15 minutes before cutting.
Delicious hot or cold.
Can be baked in large iron skillet or long oblong cake pan.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put cut-up peaches in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix sugar and flour together and spread over peaches.
Melt butter and pour over peaches.
Then put pie crust over peaches and put butter over crust.
Bake at 350° until crust gets brown.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Mix well butter and sugar.
Alternate and add the eggs and flour, beating as added.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Layer cooked rice and chopped chicken.
Mix pimentos, onion, beans and water chestnuts.
Mix soups for top layer; dot with butter, salt and pepper.
Bake in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
When bubbly, top with 2 cans dried onion rings.
Toast onions.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Add melted butter, vanilla, buttermilk and eggs.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Serves 12-16.

title: pineapple bars supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Measure about 2 Tbsp. crushed pineapple for frosting; set aside.
Combine sugar, flour, baking soda and salt in a mixing bowl.
Add oil, eggs, pineapple, vanilla and lemon extract.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour batter into a well greased and floured 17 x 11 jelly roll pan.
Bake for 25 or 30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Remove from oven and immediately frost with Coconutty Cream Cheese Frosting.
Cool completely.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into buttered casserole.
Cover with topping.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about one hour.
Yields two loaves.

title: bull shot
directions: In a 4 cup glass measure, stir together all ingredients. Cover with vented plastic wrap. Microwave on High for 3 minutes or until boiling.
Makes about 2 cups or servings.

title: hot fruit casserole
directions: Cook orange slices in small amount of water until tender; save juice from this cooking to add to casserole.
Drain all fruit except applesauce in a colander for 1 hour.
Put drained fruit in casserole dish.
Add a dash of salt, applesauce, brown sugar and brandy.
Mix gently.
Sprinkle top of casserole with brown sugar. (I cover the top with a thin layer of brown sugar.)
Put orange slices on top.
Dot with butter.
Cook 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.

title: pink punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid by package directions.
Add pineapple juice and Hawaiian Punch.
Freeze about half to slush.
Add bottle of ginger ale when ready to serve.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Mix together.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with crackers or cocktail bread.
Can be doubled or tripled.

title: cheddar broccoli strata
directions: Butter baking dish; spread half of bread cubes on bottom. Alternate layers of broccoli, cheese and bread ending with cheese. In bowl combine eggs, milk, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, salt and onion.
Pour mixture over other ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate for 6 hours or overnight.

title: monroe pizza
directions: Saute sausage until brown and pour off excess drippings.
Set aside sausage.
Saute hamburger and add sausage.
Add garlic salt, Worcestershire sauce and oregano.
Mix well.
Add Velveeta cheese and stir until melted.
Spread on rye bread and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
These can be frozen.

title: sour cream drop cookies
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add well beaten egg. Cream and then add the dry ingredients which have been mixed and sifted together.
Drop from the tip of a spoon on a buttered sheet an inch apart.
Garnish each with a raisin.
Place on bottom shelf of a 425° oven.
Immediately turn to off and bake in oven 10 minutes.
`We use this recipe for Christmas cookies.
By putting nuts or cherries on then you have to judge the heat and time.

title: peter paul mound cake
directions: Make cake as usual, adding 1 stick of butter.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Let cool.
Combine next 4 ingredients and melt together.
Pour over cake.
Melt together 1 stick of butter and chocolate chips.
Pour over coconut mixture.
Sprinkle slivered almonds over chocolate.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream butter, peanut butter, sugars, egg and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients; blend into creamed mixture.
Shape in 1-inch balls; roll in granulated sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Crisscross with fork tines.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from sheet.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into an oiled casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with cheese, if you prefer.

title: sour cream waffles(gjetost)
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking soda and cardamom into large bowl. Add cheese and toss to separate and prevent lumping.
To second bowl, beat egg yolks well.
Beat in sour cream.
Fold in flour mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into batter, half at a time, then lightly fold in butter.
Pour 1/2 cup batter onto hot waffle iron.
Bake until steaming stops, 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve hot with sugar, berries and whipped cream.
Makes 6 waffles.

title: chow mein hot dish
directions: Saute onions and celery.
Brown hamburger.
Mix everything together in a large roaster.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Cook broccoli according to package.
Cook rice and add to broccoli.
Heat soup and Cheez Whiz to pour over rice and broccoli.
Heat for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: muffin biscuits
directions: Mix together all ingredients in bowl.
Fill greased muffin tins half full.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Makes 12 biscuits.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt butter; saute onion.
Add rice and consomme.
Pour into casserole.
Cook for about 45 minutes at 350° until rice takes up soup.

title: broccoli-corn casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put in 1 1/2-quart container.

title: party salmon puffs
directions: Drain salmon; flake.
Combine salmon, cheese, olives and onion.
On lightly floured surface, roll out one sheet pastry to 12-inch square.
Cut into 16 (3-inch) squares.
Place rounded teaspoonful of salmon mixture on half of each square.
Fold pastry over and seal with a fork.
Prick tops with fork; brush with egg. Repeat with remaining pastry sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 32 puffs.

title: poop cake
