directions: Pinch cake up into small pieces.
Mix pudding as directed and pour over cake pieces.
Put Cool Whip over pudding.
Mix glaze and strawberries together and put over Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: inexpensive fruitcake
directions: Simmer gently for 20 minutes the raisins, dates, sugar, water and shortening.
Cool.
Sift together and stir in dry ingredients. Mix in nuts.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake for approximately 1 1/2 hours in a 350° oven.

title: hot pepper jelly mold
directions: Whip cream cheese until smooth; add jelly mix. Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup cold milk; add 1/2 cup boiling milk to gelatin. Stir until dissolved, then add to cream cheese and pour into oiled 3 1/2-cup mold. Chill.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: In a large pan, cook onions and celery in oil for 10 minutes. Add bean sprouts, chicken and bouillon to frypan.
Simmer 5 minutes. Add soy sauce, salt and pepper. Combine cornstarch and water; stir into mixture.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: garden stew
directions: Peel and chop potatoes and carrots.
Peel and slice onion.
Put the water, stock cubes and tomato paste into the frying pan.
Do not cover.
Turn heat to medium-high.
Stir until cubes dissolve. Add the vegetables, salt and pepper.
Stir again.
When the stew starts to boil, put lid on the frying pan and turn temperature down.
Cook gently for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: In a separate bowl, sift together flour, salt and soda.
In a large bowl, cream the shortening and sugars.
Mix in eggs, water, bananas and vanilla.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Grease 2 small loaf pans; pour in batter. Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs on high speed 5 minutes.
Gradually stir in sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Grease and flour long cookie sheet.
Spread mixture about 1-inch thick.
Bak at 375° for 15 minutes or less.
Sprinkle dish towel with powdered sugar and flip cake onto towel.
Sprinkle cake with powdered sugar. Starting at narrow end, roll the towel and cake together.
Cool, then unroll for filling.
Spread filling over unrolled cake.
Roll up cake and chill before serving.
Can be wrapped in foil and frozen.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan.
Cover and saute onion for 5 minutes.
Add carrots and cook 10 minutes, then add zucchini and cook 5 minutes.
Add peas and cook 2 to 3 minutes longer.
In another large saucepan, cook vermicelli until al dente.
Drain, then add to vegetable mixture together with mint.
Mix well and serve.
Serves 4.

title: baked potatoes
directions: Roll potatoes in butter, then crumbs.
Bake in covered dish at 425° for 45 minutes.

title: japanese shrimp soup
directions: In 2-quart saucepan bring ginger and 3 cups water to boil on moderate high heat.
Add shrimp and let stand 2 minutes.
Drain and rinse shrimp in cold water; rinse pan.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Cream the margarine.
Add sugar; mix well. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing after each.
Add remaining ingredients (vinegar and coconut last) and mix well.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells and bake slowly at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Cook 8 ounces of spaghetti according to the package directions. Meanwhile, bring 4 cups water to a boil in a large pot.
Add salt, green peas, celery and carrot.
Cook 2 minutes.
Stir in broccoli; cook about 3 minutes until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Drain in a colander immediately.
Heat olive oil in a large skillet over moderate heat.
Stir in garlic, basil and parsley.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Turn off heat and gently mix in drained, cooked vegetables.
Cover skillet and remove from heat.
Drain spaghetti in colander.
Melt butter in the large pot.
Add cream and Parmesan cheese.
Stir 2 to 3 minutes, until cheese is melted.
Add to spaghetti and toss to coat with sauce.
Add about half the vegetables; toss gently to mix.
Top with remaining vegetables.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: A pound of patience you must find

title: mom's easy 5 can soup
directions: Mix all ingredients and heat thoroughly.
Add water and other ingredients to your taste.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Cook rice until tender.
Rinse; drain.
Cook onions and celery in the butter until soft.
Add basil, marjoram, parsley, salt and pepper.
Stir in pineapple.
Add chicken-rice.
Correct the seasoning as needed.

title: surprise meringue
directions: Beat egg whites, salt and cream of tartar.
Add vanilla and beat until soft peaks form.
Add sugar gradually.
Continue beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts. Cover baking sheet with plain brown paper.
Drop from teaspoon and bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: marcia's banana bread deluxe
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs and banana; blend thoroughly.
Stir together flour and baking soda; add to banana mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Stir in nuts, chocolate chips and cherries.
Divide batter into 3 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: golden cream soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine potatoes, water, celery, carrots, onions, parsley, bouillon cube and seasonings.
Mix well.
Let vegetables cook until nearly done.
Gradually add milk to flour, mixing well.
Add milk mixture to vegetables and cook until thickened.
Add cheese and stir until melted.

title: western casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Stir in corn, beans, soup, cheese, milk, onions and chili powder.
Bring to a boil.
Put boiling mixture into a 2-quart casserole. Bake at 400°, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Place biscuits on top.
Return to oven; bake until biscuits are done and golden brown.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Blend well the first 3 ingredients.
Pour sauce over cauliflower and bacon.
Let set overnight or at least 3 hours. Add lettuce 1/2 hour before serving.

title: mama's old fashioned light fruit cake
directions: Line baking pans with aluminum foil.
Use two 9x5x3 inch loaf pans, or a 10x4 inch tube pan or 4 pound size coffee cans.
Have nuts and fruit ready.
Save some to decorate top of cake.
Use a little flour to dredge the fruit and nuts.

title: punch
directions: Boil water and sugar.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pineapple juice, orange juice, lemon juice and bananas.
Pour into clean milk cartons or plastic freezer boxes; freeze.

title: goulash
directions: Simmer hamburger meat until done and drain off grease.
Add all other ingredients, except macaroni, and simmer 20 minutes. Boil macaroni 10 minutes; drain off water.
Stir in all ingredients and serve hot.

title: ants on a branch
directions: Wash celery stick and cut in 2 pieces.
Spread peanut butter in the crevice of the celery (approximately 1 teaspoon).
Place 5 or 6 raisins in the peanut butter.

title: twice baked yams
directions: Bake yams until done.
Cut thin slice off of top and scoop pulp into bowl.
Whip pulp with butter and brown sugar to taste. Refill yam shells.
Top with chopped pecans and a sprinkle of cinnamon.

title: vegetable wild rice
directions: In a saucepan, place rice mix, contents of seasoning packet and water as directed on package.
Bring to a boil.
Add carrots. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until rice is tender and water is absorbed.
Meanwhile, in a skillet, saute squash, peppers and onion in oil until crisp-tender.
Stir into rice mixture.

title: ice cream kolacky(a czechoslovakian pastry)
directions: Cream ice cream and margarine together.
Beat in flour by cupfuls.
Roll out dough and cut into 1-inch squares.
Put about 1/2 teaspoon of Solo brand apricot, cherry, raspberry or prune fruit filling in the middle of each square.
Fold 2 end corners and press together.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat egg yolks until light and thick.
Blend in lime juice, then milk, stirring until mixture thickens.
If desired, add 2 drops green food coloring.
Pour mixture into pie crust.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff.
Gradually beat in sugar, beating until glossy peaks form.
Spread egg whites over surface of pie to edge of crust.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 20 minutes.
Chill before serving.
(In place of meringue.
Bake filling for 20 minutes at 350°.
Top chilled pie with 6 ounce container of thawed Cool Whip.
Sprinkle top with green sugar.)

title: walnut-raisin pie
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well.
Add the raisins, walnuts and vanilla and mix together evenly. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 375° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in bowl.
Blend thoroughly with hands. Shape into ball.
Roll in English walnuts.
Chill.

title: graham walnut cake(old italian recipe)
directions: Cream butter and sugar at room temperature.
Add beaten egg yolks to butter and sugar.
Put graham cracker crumbs and chopped walnuts in a separate bowl.
Add baking powder.
Alternate mixing crumb-nut mixture and milk to butter and sugar mixture.
Then fold in well beaten egg whites.
Add vanilla.
Grease and flour an angel or Bundt pan.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pie filling in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with pineapple.
Sprinkle with cake mix.
Melt oleo and pour over top. Cover with nuts and coconut.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: karo pecan pie
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar and syrup.
Add pecans, oleo, vanilla and salt and mix well.
Heat pie crust just enough to set.
Pour ingredients into crust.
Cook at 400° for 5 minutes.
Lower heat to 325° and cook for another 45 to 50 minutes.

title: gator tail
directions: Marinate cubed gator tail in a mixture of buttermilk and beer for 1 hour or overnight.
(Refrigerate.)
Drain; coat with seasoned flour.
Fry in deep fat over medium heat 10 minutes.
Drain and serve.

title: sausage & cheese balls
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl; mix well. Shape into small balls. Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 400 degrees until brown. Serve warm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all except 3/4 cup stuffing mix.
Place in a greased casserole.
Top with reserved stuffing.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tamale pie
directions: In medium skillet, brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Stir in salsa, tomato paste and cumin.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9-inch baking pan. Prepare muffin mix; stir in cheese and chilies. Spoon over meat mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until brown in 350° oven.
Serves 6.

title: ann's cocoa cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix all dry ingredients with milk, oil and eggs.
Add hot water and beat on high for 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Put ingredients in double boiler and melt.
Place on buttered plate.

title: molded cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Set aside to cool.
In another bowl, combine cucumber, onion and cottage cheese (or if desired, puree cucumber, onion and cottage cheese in blender).

title: westville's own gingerbread
directions: Sift together first 6 ingredients.
Mix together and add the remaining ingredients.

title: holiday cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries, sugar, pineapple and marshmallows.
Let stand for a short time.
Add cream that is beaten stiff.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Cut butter into flour. Then add milk. Mix well. Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in half long way.
Place in 9 in. x 13 in. x 2 in. pan.
Add 1/4 in. water in bottom of pan and cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 400° for one hour.
Remove and hull potato inside out of skin.
Mix potato inside with remaining ingredients. Place mixture back into potato skins.
Sprinkle with bacon bits. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Put oleo, sugar, salt, cocoa and milk in iron skillet, bring to boil and boil 2 to 3 minutes.
Take off stove and add vanilla, and peanut butter,
stir well.
Add 1 cup at a time of oats.
Drop on waxed paper or foil with tablespoon.

title: veal piccata
directions: Pound veal with wooden mallet until very thin (1/8-inch). Dredge lightly in flour; shake off excess.
Melt 3 tablespoon margarine in skillet.
Place garlic in skillet until golden brown, discard.
Place veal in skillet; cook quickly, just until brown, about 1 to 2 minutes each side.
Remove to serving dish.
Add remaining margarine, wine and lemon juice to pan, simmer 3 minutes, scraping bottom of pan to loosen drippings.
Pour over veal, garnish with lemon slices.

title: taco pie
directions: Press crescent rolls into 9 inch pie plate or a quiche pan to form a crust. Brown hamburger and add taco mix (no liquid)
and drained ripe olives.
Pour warm hamburger mixture into shell; top with sour cream and generous amount of grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown, about 25 minutes.
Top with chopped lettuce, tomatoes, green onions, or other toppings, plus taco sauce and broken Dorito chips to complete the pie.
Serves 3-4.

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Mix hamburg, salt and pepper.
Add egg, cracker crumbs and onion.
Form into meat balls.
Place in baking pan.

title: buttermilk chicken
directions: Soak chicken breasts 30 minutes in the buttermilk.
Pour off buttermilk and then roll chicken breasts in flour.
Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Bake 25 minutes, both sides, at 350° and then pour cream of mushroom soup and buttermilk over chicken.
Bake another 25 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Combine pudding mix with milk in a mixer bowl.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping.

title: glorified rice
directions: Mix ingredients. Chill. Serve as a dessert or salad.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Saute bell pepper and onion in butter. Blend in soup, Ro-Tel and deboned shredded chicken breasts. Layer tortillas and mix approximately 3 times and top with cheese. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: lou's chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken that has been pulled apart and placed in buttered casserole. Pour coarsely, crushed cheese crackers into melted oleo.
Add poppy seed.
Spread over chicken and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Crackers will be brown and crunchy.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer all ingredients.
Pour over meat and bake for about 1 hour.

title: cinnamon jawbreaker candy
directions: Stir sugar into the water until dissolved; add syrup.
Do not stir.
When mixture cracks (hard crack), remove from heat.
Add cinnamon flavoring; add red food coloring. Stir quickly, outside! Pour onto greased cookie sheets.
Cool, crack and dust with powdered sugar.

title: a-b-c casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with chopped onion.
Drain off fat.
Peel and slice potatoes.
In large casserole, begin covering bottom with part of cooked hamburger-onion mixture.

Follow with a layer of raw potatoes, sprinkle parsley, salt and pepper on potatoes. Spoon on 1/2 of can of vegetable soup, add a layer of hamburger, then more sliced potatoes and then rest of vegetable soup.
Put last of hamburger on top and pour mushroom soup over all.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°, until potatoes are tender.
Frozen vegetables may be added with vegetable soup.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine sour cream and half the dressing mix.
Add chicken, 1 cup cheese and olives.
Spoon onto tortillas and roll up.
Place seam side down.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Pour dressing over top.
Top with salsa.
Makes 6 servings.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix the cake mix and cook as directed in 2 round pans.
Crumble half of the cake in bottom of punch bowl.
Add 1 can pie filling, 1 can pineapple, 3 bananas and 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Take the rest of the cake and put over the Cool Whip.
Add 1 can cherry pie filling, large can crushed pineapple, 3 bananas and 8 ounce bowl Cool Whip. Refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: shamrock salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add salt, cold water and vinegar.
Cool until gelatin is the consistency of egg whites, stirring occasionally. Add vegetables.
Spoon into a 9-inch square pan. Chill until firm.

title: raisin bread - english style
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients and let rise for 1 hour. Then add next 5 ingredients.
In another bowl mix all the fruits with 3 cups of flour and then add last 4 spices.

title: cake-in-a-cone
directions: Make cake batter according to directions on package.
Fill ice cream cones half full with batter.
Set cones in muffin tin compartments.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Frost and decorate.
Serve same day because cones will become mushy.

title: chicken noodle casserole(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain. Mix soup, milk and salt; heat, stirring constantly.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Add remaining ingredients except 1/2 almonds and the crumbs.
Put mixture in casserole, top with crumbs and remaining almonds.
Bake at 400° about 30 minutes.

title: chocolate raisin bars
directions: Simmer raisins, water and 1 teaspoon soda for 10 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
In mixing bowl cream honey with butter until fluffy.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour, salt and 1/4 teaspoon soda; blend this, then add "raisin fluids," vanilla, rolled oats and 1/2 of the chocolate chips.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle remaining chips and nuts evenly on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars; makes 24.

title: crab meat casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Place in greased casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake in 325° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add sour cream last.
Pour into a greased casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 12 servings.

title: three bean hot dish
directions: Cut up bacon and fry lightly with ground beef.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: squirrel fricassee(4 servings)
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper on sheet of waxed paper and dredge meat pieces.
Brown in a large skillet in bacon drippings over low heat.
Add broth and simmer for 1 hour, or until tender. Add salt and pepper to taste, if necessary.
Serve with dumplings.

title: buttermilk pies
directions: Mix eggs and sugar with mixer.
Add flour, soft butter, buttermilk and lemon extract.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 350° until set.
Makes two 9-inch unbaked pie crusts.

title: potato and cheese soup
directions: In a large pot, saute onion and celery in margarine until translucent.
Add water and bring it to a full boil.

Add the potato and chicken bouillon and simmer until potatoes are cooked. Add all remaining ingredients and continue to cook at a simmer until the soup is heated through and you have a homogeneous mixture.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and add enough milk 3/4 the way to cover. Place in casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream the 3/4 cup sugar and the butter or margarine with a wooden spoon.
Beat in the egg and vanilla. In small bowl, stir together flour, salt, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Stir into butter mixture with wooden spoon until well mixed.
In the same small bowl, combine the 2 tablespoons sugar and the cinnamon.
Turn oven to 375°.
Grease a cookie sheet. Shape dough into 1-inch balls; roll each in the sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Put balls 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 36.

title: walnut crunch pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix walnuts and brown sugar in a small bowl.
Place 3/4 cup in bottom of pie shells.
Reserve remaining mixture for topping.

title: peanut butter syrup
directions: Add enough water to 1 cup sugar to dissolve, then bring mixture to a boil.
Add 1 tablespoon peanut butter or more to suit taste.
Recipe can be doubled and leftover frozen for future use.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Blend sugar and cream in large saucepan.
Bring to boil, using medium heat.
Stir constantly until mixture reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; add margarine, vanilla and peanut butter.
Spread onto greased platter.

title: mexican refried beans
directions: Put all together in a baking dish; mix well.
Smooth top and sprinkle Jack cheese on top.
Bake in oven at 400° until cheese is bubbly and melted well.
Let set 5 or 6 minutes before serving. This is the simple way for these beans.
If these ingredients are not available, if the refried are not, use canned pintos or red beans and mash real well, then fry beans until mushy in oil, then cool and add the rest.
To serve more than two, just increase everything!

title: cream cheese and walnut log
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except walnuts, until thoroughly mixed. Form into a log. Roll log in chopped walnuts. Chill for 15 minutes.

title: grilled salmon steaks
directions: Brush salmon steaks (both sides) with soy sauce generously and then olive oil.
Then use garlic salt and pepper to taste. Grill the salmon steaks 10 to 15 minutes total, turning once until fish flake with a fork.

title: cherry crunch cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add milk and vanilla; mix well.
Combine the flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in the pecans, dates and chopped cherries.
Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes. Shape dough into 1-inch balls; roll in cornflakes.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheets; press a cherry half into center of each.
Bake at 350° for 14 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Remove to wire racks to cool.
Yield:
5 1/2 dozen.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, butter and eggs until mixed.
Add syrup, vanilla and pecans.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Fill unbaked 9-inch pie shell with sliced peaches.
Cream sugar with margarine and add flour, egg and vanilla.
Spread over peaches and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Have mixture ready to spoon on peaches so they won't discolor.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt Butter in microwave.
Add and mix other ingredients.
Bake at 375 for about 1-1/2 to 2 hours.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all together and place in a greased 7 x 11 Pyrex dish. Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 400°. Serves 8 to 10.

title: breakfast cereal
directions: Mix together butter, brown sugar and oatmeal.
Mix with hands until there are no more lumps.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 275° for 25 minutes.
After it has been baked, add nuts.
Serve with milk. Store in a tight container.

title: chicken strips
directions: Cut chicken and peppers into strips.
Cut onion into rings. Coat a large pan or wok with oil.

title: pork chops
directions: Arrange pork chops on greased (or sprayed with nonstick cooking spray) baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top each chop with one slice onion and then one lemon slice.
Place 1 tablespoon brown sugar and 1 tablespoon catsup on each chop. Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake for 30 minutes more, basting occasionally.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Form ingredients into cakes and fry in shortening to a golden brown.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add vanilla, baking powder, crackers and milk. Mix well, then add eggs (well beaten).
Add coconut, pineapple and nuts. Bake in tube pan for 70 minutes at 325° or in 3 layer pans for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: the best baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: venison roast
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients, blending until smooth.
Spread mixture over venison and rub into meat thoroughly.
Put meat in roasting pan, arranging bacon strips on top of meat and fastening with toothpicks.
Dot meat with butter and pour water around, not on, meat.
Roast uncovered at 450° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream
shortening, sugars, eggs and peanut butter until light and
fluffy.
Stir flour into creamed mixture and blend well. Drop
by
teaspoon,
2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheet. Bake
in 375° oven 10 to 12 minutes until light brown. Remove from pan.

title: potato rolls
directions: Mix butter, potatoes, sugar and salt. Add warm milk. Add yeast, which has been soaked in lukewarm water.
Add beaten eggs and 1 cup flour. Beat well. Add remainder of flour and knead well. Let rise.
Work down and let rise again. Form into rolls as for Parker House rolls. When light, bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: raspberry cheesecake trifle
directions: Prepare and bake cake mix according to package directions. Cool; cut into 1-inch cubes.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix and roll in nuts.

title: kraut salad
directions: Drain and rinse kraut; let drain well.
Heat vinegar and sugar until sugar melts; add kraut.
Add onion, pepper and pimento.
Let stand in refrigerator for at least 24 hours.
Better if let set for 3 to 4 days before eating.
Will keep for 3 to 4 weeks in refrigerator.

title: tasty and tender round steak
directions: Trim excess fat from meat.
Cut in serving pieces.
Combine flour, mustard, salt and pepper.
Use to coat meat; reserve remaining flour mixture.
Melt Crisco in skillet.
Brown meat on both sides.
Push meat to one side and stir in reserved flour mixture.
Combine water and Worcestershire.
Stir into mixture. Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheesecake pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water. Set aside to cool. Cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth.

title: pumpkin custard pies
directions: Put pumpkin, beaten eggs and milk in a large bowl.
Put flour, spices and salt in a small bowl and mix with a little milk until smooth.
Add enough more milk to make it runny, then add it all to the pumpkin mixture.
Add the sugar and vanilla and stir well.
Put in pie shells and sprinkle nutmeg over the tops.
Bake in 450° oven for about 10 minutes, then reduce to 350° and bake for 30 to 35 minutes longer or until centers are firm.
Test by inserting blade of knife.
It should come out clean.

title: onion cheese bread
directions: Saute onion in 1 tablespoon butter.
Mix Bisquick, eggs and milk.
Add onion and half the cheese.
Pour mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Drizzle 4 tablespoons melted butter on top.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: italian beef sandwiches
directions: Bake roast at 325° for 40 minutes per pound.
Heat water and bouillon cubes until dissolved.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer for 15 minutes.
Slice beef thin; lay in a large pan and pour broth over meat.
Marinate 4 to 5 hours or overnight.
Heat, but do not boil before serving.
Serve on French bread or buns.

title: beef log
directions: Saute pepper, onion and mushrooms.
Unroll crescent rolls onto cookie sheet and pinch seams together.
Break beef into bite size pieces and place down center of roll sheet.
Top with peppers, onions, mushrooms, and cheese.
Fold sides of roll over filling.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Cover ribs with water in large saucepan.
Cover; simmer over medium-low heat for 1 hour.
In nonmetallic pan, mix remaining ingredients.
Drain ribs; place in sauce and coat each rib.
Let cool.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Grill until brown and heated through, about 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: german chocolate bundt cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into bundt pan.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Using solid shortening or margarine, grease either a 9 x 13-inch pan or if you like a thinner cake, use a cookie sheet.
In large bowl combine ingredients by hand.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat eggs well; add all ingredients together.
Beat well again.
(Chill for about an hour.)
Drink.
Blender works best!

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: purple lady salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in blueberries and pineapple.
Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg whites (approximately 30 minutes).
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts into thickened Jell-O.
Pour into 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm. Cut into squares to serve.

title: shrimp pilaf
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, cook bacon until crisp; remove from pan and set aside, reserving 1 tablespoon fat.
In same skillet, saute onion in fat until tender; stir in rice, broth, tomatoes, lemon juice and pepper; bring to boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 25 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir in shrimp and bacon; cook and stir until shrimp is cooked and pink, about 5 minutes.
Garnish with parsley if desired; makes 4 servings.

title: easy crock-pot stew
directions: Brown stew meat in 1 tablespoon oil.
Add carrots, potatoes, celery and onions.
Add soup and 3 cans water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 1 hour on high in crock-pot, then turn down heat and simmer until tender.

title: butterscotch pecan pie
directions: Combine
sugar,
flour and salt and stir in milk slowly. Cook over
boiling water until thickened, stirring constantly. Cover and
cook
minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Add mixture to
egg
yolks,
stirring
vigorously;
cook
1 minute longer. Add
butter, vanilla and pecans.
Cool.
Place filling into a 9 inch baked pastry shell.
Top with meringue.

title: sweet potato and apple casserole
directions: Cook sweet potatoes, remove skins and slice lengthwise.
Peel and slice apples.
Melt butter over low heat.
Add sugar, orange rind and nutmeg.

title: chicken pizza
directions: Sprinkle onion powder, garlic powder and oregano lightly over chicken pieces.
Put chicken in long baking dish.
Slice onion on top.
Spoon stewed tomatoes over chicken.
Sprinkle a little extra oregano.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana shortcake(bake off recipe)
directions: Bake cake or use the shortcake sponges.
Make sauce of the brown sugar and water, boiled for 1 or 2 minutes.
Place sliced bananas on the cake and pour sauce over them.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: apple muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased muffin pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chocolate munchies
directions: Combine ingredients and serve.

title: tomato swiss steak(microwave cooking)
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Place steak on cutting board. Pound half of the flour mixture into each side of steak with meat mallet or edge of saucer.
Cut meat into 4 pieces and place in 8-inch round or 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining flour mixture over meat.
Spread onions, green pepper and tomato paste over meat.
Pour in broth to cover meat.
Cover with wax paper. Cook on High for 5 minutes.
Cook on 60% Power (Bake) for about 10 minutes.
Rearrange meat.
Cook on 60% Power (Bake) 10 minutes or until tender.
Serves 4.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Cook spaghetti in broth; drain (save broth). Do not rinse. Chop and saute onions and peppers in oleo; add celery flakes, tomatoes and cheese. Cook until melted. Combine spaghetti, chicken, Worcestershire sauce, mushrooms and cheese mixture. Stir and cook until well heated. Use broth if needed to make moist.

title: cracker salad
directions: Crush crackers and put in
a large mixing bowl.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate in covered container for a couple of hours before serving.
Do not freeze.
Keeps well for several days refrigerated.

title: jerk pork
directions: Wash pork well.
Mix seasoning well into pork.
Sprinkle with soy sauce.
Leave covered overnight in refrigerator.
Cover and bake for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes or longer, basting occasionally.
For a dark color, add a little browning.

title: bavarian angel dessert(this recipe must be made one day ahead)
directions: In a double boiler, blend egg yolks, sugar and 3 cups milk until smooth (approximately 15 minutes).
Cool thoroughly.
In a separate bowl, fold whipped cream and whipped egg whites together. Combine both mixtures together.
Rub crumbs off angel food cake. Break cake in pieces into bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour above custard mixture over angel food cake.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: magic fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in bottom of baking dish.
Mix sugar, milk and flour.
Add baking powder.
Pour over melted butter.
Do not stir. Sprinkle sugar over top.
Bake 1 hour at 360° to 375°.

title: fireman pot luck
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in heavy duty foil.
Cook in grill on medium heat for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: haluski with cottage cheese
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Cook until almost done; drain.
In large skillet, brown onions in butter.
Add potatoes.
Continue browning and stirring until potatoes are done.
Cook noodles to desired tenderness, then fold in with cottage cheese.
Heat and cook 1 or 2 minutes longer.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk following directions on box.
Let set 5 minutes. Add sour cream and Cool Whip. Whip until fluffy.
Pour layer of pudding in bottom of a large bowl (clear glass bowl works well).
Add layers of vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding until used up. Crumble wafers and sprinkle over top. Chill at least 6 hours.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion, celery and carrot in olive oil until onions are transparent.
Add mushrooms to taste.
Separately, brown ground round.
Drain any grease.
Add cooking sherry.
Cook slowly until evaporated, then combine with first ingredients.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, tomato puree, Italian seasoning, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
May need a little water added.
Serve over spaghetti or favorite pasta.

title: crab ball
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, crab meat and lemon juice in a mixing bowl.
Form into a ball with hands.
Pour cocktail sauce over top and refrigerate until ready to eat.
Serve with your favorite snack crackers.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 9 or 10-inch pie plate. Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onions evenly over bottom of pie plate. Place remaining ingredients in blender.
Cover and blend on high speed for 1 minute.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Refrigerate any leftover quiche.

title: kool-aid pops(for the children)
directions: Mix sugar, Kool-Aid and jello.
Add hot water, stir until dissolved.
Add cold water.
Pour into paper cups.
Place in freezer.

title: chocolate french fudge
directions: In top of double boiler, melt the semi-sweet chocolate pieces; remove from heat.
Add the Eagle Brand milk, vanilla, chopped nuts and salt.
Stir until smooth.
Spread mixture evenly into wax paper lined 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Chill 2 hours, until firm. Remove from pan; cut into squares.
Makes 1 3/4 pounds fudge.

title: irish braised lamb
directions: Heat oil; barely brown lamb.
Transfer meat to casserole dish. Saute onion and tomato in oil lightly.
Add stock to mixture and spice as desired.
Add mixture to meat.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with potatoes and green beans.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon, soda, salt and cloves.
Stir in eggs, pumpkin and cooking oil until thoroughly combined.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except crescent rolls and eggs.
Roll crescent rolls into one large rectangle, pinching together perforated seams.
Put half of the salmon mixture on top of crescent roll.
Sprinkle with hard-boiled eggs.
Put remaining salmon mixture over eggs.
Bring sides of crescent roll up and over to form a loaf.
Pinch together and place on a baking pan that has been sprayed with cooking spray or on a preheated baking stone.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with creamed peas over slices of salmon loaf.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt margarine; mix with pretzels, sugar and pecans.
Pat into bottom of 2 x 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool.

title: gingersnap crust
directions: Blend thoroughly in a 9-inch pie pan.
Save 1/4 cup for topping.
Press remaining mixture firmly in an even layer against bottom and sides of pie pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes. Cool and fill.

title: hot rolls
directions: Bring milk, water and sugar to boil.
Add butter.
Soak yeast in warm water.
Add
cooled
milk
and
remaining
ingredients. Let rise; work down and let
rise
again.
Work out and let rise before baking at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: wonder salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cream cheese, ice cream and salad dressing.
Blend well.
Add bananas, pecans and pineapple. Takes about 3 hours to set.

title: plum cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sprinkle brown sugar over bottom of baking dish.
Place plums side up over sugar.
Stir together flour, sugar and cinnamon in small bowl.
Stir in egg until mix is crumbly.
Sprinkle over plums.
Pour melted butter over top. Place dish on foil.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: easy fudge frosting
directions: Microwave chocolate and butter in large microwavable bowl on High 1 minute or until butter is melted.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir in sugar, milk and vanilla until smooth. Let stand, if necessary, until of spreading consistency, spreading occasionally.
Spread quickly.
(Add 2 to 3 tablespoons additional milk if frosting becomes too thick.)
Makes about 2 1/2 cups or enough to frost tops and sides of 2 (8 to 9-inch) layer cakes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Arrange lettuce, celery, peppers and onion, then peas.
Seal with real mayonnaise; sprinkle with sugar.
Add cheese and bacon.

title: spotted pup
directions: Rinse rice.
In a 2 quart saucepan, bring water and salt to a boil. Add rice and cover pot.
Turn off heat.
After 20 minutes, add raisins and fluff rice with fork.
Cover again for a few minutes until raisins are softened.
Serve with milk or half and half, sugar and cinnamon if desired.
This is a great Sunday evening supper after a big mid day meal.
Also good for breakfast or any other time.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg, pumpkin and vanilla. Mix with dry ingredients.
Drop by spoon onto cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Cool before putting icing on.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: In 2-quart glass measure, pour all ingredients in.
Heat 4 minutes on High.
Stir until smooth.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes until thick.
Add 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Stir until smooth and glossy. Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: saucy apple swirl
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and applesauce with mixer.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together.
Grease a tube or Bundt pan with Crisco. Sprinkle pan with some of the sugar/cinnamon mixture.
Pour 1/2 the batter in the pan.
Pour the rest of the sugar/cinnamon mixture on that.
Then pour the remaining batter in the pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let set in pan 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Can add glaze made of confectioners sugar and milk (not necessary).

title: country potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 9 x 13-inch greased casserole. Crush corn flakes and sprinkle on top of potatoes. Spread 2 tablespoons melted margarine over flakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old-fashion biscuit pudding
directions: Soak crumbled biscuits in hot water for a few minutes.
Add sugar, butter, nutmeg, raisins, beaten eggs and milk, mixing after each addition.
Pour into 1-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° in a preheated oven for about 30 to 40 minutes or until browned.

title: potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together except crackers and butter.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with crackers and butter.
Bake 1 hour.

title: mashed potato mountain
directions: Boil potatoes for 20 to 25 minutes until tender.
Meanwhile, saute onion in 1 tablespoon butter until translucent.
Add warm milk to onion and heat thoroughly.
Remove from heat.
Keep warm. Drain potatoes; return pot briefly so potatoes can dry.
Mash potatoes.
Beat in milk-onion mixture.
Fold in 1 cup cheese. Season to taste.
Butter a 9-inch pie plate.
Form mashed potatoes into a mountain.
"Rake" with a fork so whole surface is grooved. Melt remaining 2 tablespoons butter; brush over mountain.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix by hand oil and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and buttermilk. Sift together flour, salt, soda, nutmeg, cinnamon and allspice. Add to mixture, then add apples and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: quick-as-a-wink pineapple pie
directions: Stir together undrained pineapple and dry pudding mix; set aside.
Prepare dessert topping per package directions.
Gently fold prepared topping into pineapple mixture.
Turn into baked pastry shell.
Cover with waxed paper or clear plastic wrap. Chill several hours or overnight.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients, except boiling water.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into 1 (13 x 9-inch) pan or 2 round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake is done.

title: yogurt
directions: In a deep saucepan, bring milk to a rolling boil, stirring occasionally.
Remove pan from heat; add evaporated milk.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve 2 tablespoons yogurt (starter from previous batch or from commercial type) in 1/2 cup of lukewarm milk, blending thoroughly.
Add this to remaining milk, stirring constantly.
Pour milk into 1-quart heavy bowl or individual glasses.
Cover with cloth, let stand in a warm place for 6 to 8 hours or until thick.
Chill before serving.

title: cherry cheese pastry shells
directions: Bake shells according to package directions.
In mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and extract with fork, removing circular top of each baked shell and set aside.
Remove any soft layers of pastry inside shells and discard.

title: quick herbal spirals
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter, herbs, salt and garlic. Remove crescent rolls from package without separating.
Seal 4 pieces together by sealing seams, making a square.
Repeat.
Roll out each square to a 9-inch square.
Spread on half the herb mixture and half the cheese.
Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Use a sharp knife and cut roll into 1/2-inch slices.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.

title: wanda squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender in a small amount of water. Mix stuffing with melted margarine.
Mix soup and sour cream. Layer stuffing, squash, soup, squash, soup then stuffing into a sprayed baking pan.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain fat.
Mix tomato sauce and seasoning mix with meat.
Line greased casserole dish with 1/2 of Doritos.
Put mixture on top of chips.
Mix soup with 1 tablespoon milk and pour over meat.
Add another layer of chips.
Cover with cheese.
Bake until cheese melts, about 15 minutes.

title: texan chinese chews
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar, beating well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to egg mixture, beating well.
Fold in dates and pecans.
Spread batter evenly into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 300° oven for 35 minutes.
Cut into 3 x 1-inch bars.
Remove to wire racks to cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar before serving. Yields about 3 dozen.

title: sauteed new potatoes
directions: Wash and cube enough potatoes for your group.
Place in an electric skillet.
Add broth halfway covering potatoes.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer 5 to 7 minutes, just until tender, but firm.
If necessary, drain excess broth.
Spray tops of potatoes with nonstick spray and sprinkle generously with seasoning.
Increase heat and saute until potatoes begin to brown.

title: fish batter
directions: Lightly coat fish with 3 tablespoons Bisquick.
Mix 1 cup Bisquick, salt, egg and ginger ale until smooth.
Dip fish into batter and fry.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain and add taco seasoning.
Line bottom of baking dish with refried beans.
Cover with the ground beef. Mix soup and tomato sauce; pour over ground beef layer.
Top with crushed corn chips.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Garnish with lettuce, cheese, tomatoes, salsa or anything that you like on tacos.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Spread thawed hash browns in bottom of dish.
Salt and pepper.
Put ham on top of potatoes.
Dot oleo on top of ham and potatoes.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Beat eggs with milk and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix cream of chicken with water in pan to be baked in.
Spread rice over mixture.
Lay chicken on top.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: cucumber-onion salad
directions: Peel cucumbers and score lengthwise with fork tines. In a large bowl, slice cucumbers and onion very thin and add salted ICE water to cover. Let stand 1 to 2 hours. Cook sugar and water until sugar is dissolved. Refrigerate until cool. Add vinegar, oil and celery seed to taste to sugar mixture and mix well. Drain and rinse cucumbers and onion. Pour sugar mixture over drained cucumbers and onion. Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: cheesy lime gelatin salad
directions: Bring to boil pineapple with juice, sugar and Jell-O.
Add cold water.
When partially set add shredded cheese.
Add whipped topping and chopped pecans.

title: southern steamed potatoes
directions: Prepare potatoes and onions by peeling and dicing.
Heat drippings.
Add peeled and diced vegetables.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and sugar.
Cook on medium heat in large skillet until tender.

title: chicken and artichoke casserole
directions: Cook chicken in boiling water to cover 15 minutes or until tender; drain well.
Let chicken cool.
Remove skin; bone chicken and cut meat and set aside.
Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain well and set aside.
Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.

Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened and bubbly. Add cheeses, garlic, salt and pepper; stir until cheeses melt. Combine reserved chicken, macaroni, cheese sauce, artichokes and sliced mushrooms.
Stir well.
Spoon into 2 (13 x 9 x 2-inch) baking dishes.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes or until heated through.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: orange glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Pare sweet potatoes; cut each lengthwise in half.
Arrange in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
In small saucepan, stir together sugar, cornstarch, salt and orange peel. Slowly stir orange juice into sugar mixture.
Add butter; cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Pour hot orange juice mixture over sweet potatoes in casserole.
Cover; bake 1 hour, basting occasionally.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: barbecued green beans
directions: Place green beans in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown bacon and remove from skillet.
Brown onion in bacon drippings.
Add to brown sugar and catsup.
Stir and pour over beans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple latkes
directions: Beat eggs, add liquid and blend.
Sift dry ingredients together and add liquid mix.
Add apples.
Heat 1/4 cup oil; drop by heaping tablespoonful.
Prick with fork; drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon or use syrup.

title: oatmeal peanut butter no bakes
directions: In a saucepan, melt margarine.
Add sugar and milk to melted margarine, stirring as needed, and bring to a rolling boil. Continue to boil for 1 to 2 minutes, until the bubbles are no longer glossy.
Add oatmeal and mix well.
Spoon onto a pan or wax paper to cool.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters and roll in the first cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Put half the biscuits in a Bundt pan.
Cook butter and second cinnamon
mixture with 2 teaspoons water.
Bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Pour half over the biscuits. Layering with nuts as you go, put the remaining biscuits in pan and pour the rest of the syrup over this.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool 5 minutes.
Then turn out on a plate.
Pull apart and enjoy.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in heated pineapple and strawberries.
Mix in buttermilk, Cool Whip and nuts.
Pour into mold and refrigerate until set.

title: fish stew mexican style
directions: Put everything, but fresh cilantro and seafood in a large pot and simmer until carrots and celery are tender.
Add seafood and simmer until cooked (about 10 minutes).
To serve, top with chopped cilantro; salt and pepper to taste.

title: can kraut
directions: Fill quart jars with chopped cabbage.
To each jar, add salt, sugar and vinegar.
Pour water over mixture to fill jars.
Seal.

title: red hot green olives
directions: Drain olives well.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over olives in the jar.
Re-cap and refrigerate.
Marinate for 3 days, turning jar daily so spices will permeate throughout.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix altogether and shape into ball.

title: debbie's great chicken casserole
directions: Place all ingredients in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir until well blended.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Uncover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sarah's sugar crisps
directions: In large saucepan, melt shortening over low heat.
Remove and let cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg; beat well.
Sift together remaining dry ingredients; add to first mixture.
Mix well and chill thoroughly (at least 2 hours).
Form into 1-inch balls; roll in sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheets 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen delightful cookies. Flatten with glass which has been greased and dipped in sugar before baking.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Combine
all ingredients together until smooth;
spread on cake and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: strawberry smoothie
directions: Wash and halve strawberries.
Add juice and blend on high speed.
Add crushed ice and blend again to mix thoroughly.

title: mandarin pork roast
directions: Roast meat uncovered until fork-tender.
Put remaining ingredients in saucepan, including the liquid from the fruit. Heat in saucepan, stirring until thickened, adding water if necessary.

title: reuben dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Keep warm; serve with Pinah's rye chips or rye crackers.

title: raisin scones
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder and sugar together.
Cut in shortening.
Add raisins.
Beat eggs slightly and add enough milk to make 3/4 cup total.
Stir into dry mixture.
Knead lightly on floured board.
Divide dough into fourths.
Pat each into circle. Cut each circle into 4 wedges.
Place on greased baking sheet. Brush top with milk and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until browned.
Makes 16.

title: lemon delight
directions: Layer 1:
Mix flour, margarine and walnuts in mixing bowl until blended.
Place in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch glass dish. Bake at 350° for about 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool.

title: caramel icing
directions: Heat until bubbly, cool slightly, beat in small amount of powdered sugar and soft butter, add vanilla.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter
and
sugar. Add eggs, beat. Add flour and mix well.
Set
in
refrigerator
about 1 hour.
Roll and cut. Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: bob's big blast ribs
directions: You will need 2 cups hickory or other wood chips.

title: hamburger and bean casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain well.
Add tomato soup and green beans.
Top with mashed potatoes and bake in casserole dish for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: coconut graham bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine.
Place in bottom of an 8-inch square pan.
Add in layers: graham cracker crumbs, coconut and chocolate bits.
Then pour condensed milk over all.
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: candied yams
directions: Peel and dice or coin cut potatoes.
Rinse.
Cook in water until potatoes are done.
Leave about 1/4 cup water in pan with potatoes.
Cook over medium heat until juice of potatoes is candied in appearance.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar, cream cheese and butter.
Add one egg at a time.
Add flour and vanilla.
Bake one hour at 250°.

title: crock-pot scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel, slice and layer potatoes, onions and Spam. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Spoon 1/2 of each can of soup on the layers. Repeat the last half of potatoes, onions and Spam; salt and pepper. Spoon remaining soups on this layer. Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours or on high 3 to 4 hours.

title: orange sherbet jello
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Cool slightly.
Add sherbet and stir until mixed and melted.
Add drained mandarin oranges. Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until set.
Makes 8 to 10 dessert servings.

title: nonfat pancakes
directions: *Place oats in blender.
Oats will turn into a powder.

title: raisin sauce for ham
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour.
Add mustard and stir.
Add liquid gradually while stirring.
When thick, add raisins and sherry.
If your raisins tend to be dry, soak in hot water for a bit and then drain very well.
Dry raisins can draw the moisture out of the sauce.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Saute first 5 items until meat browns.
Split peppers lengthwise; remove stems and membranes.
Boil 20 minutes.
Cook rice according to directions.
Combine meat and rice mixture, moistening with part of tomato juice.
Press into cooked pepper shells.
Place into baking pan.
Pour remaining tomato juice over all.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Cook chicken breasts and shred into small pieces.
Add salt and sage while hot.
Cut crescent rolls into 3 small ones per roll.
Place chicken in roll and roll it up around edges.
After all chicken is rolled up, dip into melted margarine, then dip into stuffing mix.
Coat well and place on baking sheet.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Beat eggs in bowl and add 1/2 cup oil, sour cream and corn meal.
Fold in cream-style corn.
Bake in preheated skillet with a little oil in it at 350° to 375° until brown.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly shortening, butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
For a softer cookie, add 1/2 cup flour.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook together onion and beef until brown.
Arrange meat mixture in casserole.
Put thick layer mashed potatoes.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake in preheated oven (350°) for 30 minutes.

title: holland rusk torte(hand me downs)
directions: Mix all ingredients and press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: baked zucchini
directions: Cut medium size zucchini in half lengthwise.
Score.
Sprinkle halves with garlic salt, onion salt and oregano.
Spread a thin layer of butter over the halves, then sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until tender.

title: pineapple bars
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg, milk and pineapple and mix well.
Add flour, baking powder and spices.
Make a soft dough.
If too soft, add a little more flour.
Roll out and cut into bars, 3 x 2 x 1/2-inches.
Fry in hot oil.
Ice with powdered sugar icing.

title: chicken or pork chops with rice
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a baking dish (8 x 11 1/2-inch) melt margarine and sprinkle with rice.
Place salted chicken pieces with skin side up or pork chops on top of rice.
Add beef broth and onion soup by pouring over meat.
Bake about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream sugar, melted butter and eggs.
Add applesauce and jam. Sift in another bowl flour, soda and spices. Save a small amount of flour and mix the raisins with the flour.
Add flour mixture and raisins.
Bake at 400°.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Butter a 9-inch pie plate.
Fill with sliced apples.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples.
In a bowl, cream margarine and sugar; add egg and flour.
Mix well.
Drop over apples and spread evenly.
Sprinkle with nuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: macaroni pizza
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as instructed on box.
Stir in egg and spread mixture on pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, sugar and lemon juice.
Mix with the other ingredients.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Cook ground beef on stove or in microwave; drain.
Combine beef, spaghetti sauce, water and wine.
Spread one-third of mixture into microwavable 12 x 8-inch dish (lightly greased).
Arrange 4 noodles on sauce.
Layer 1 cup cottage cheese and 1 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with meat sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with plastic wrap and fold back one corner. Microwave at 50% power for 32 to 35 minutes (turn dish after 15 minutes).
Uncover; sprinkle with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese and cook 2 minutes more.

title: almond quiche
directions: Cook onions with margarine until brown.
Mix eggs, cream, milk, flour, salt and nutmeg.
Put cheese and almonds in pie crust.
Pour egg mixture over cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Chop all ingredients for 15 seconds in blender and push ingredients into blades.
Repeat until smooth.
Makes 2 1/4 cups.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, salt and cocoa in a bowl and set aside.
In saucepan, heat milk until very warm; add beaten egg yolks, stirring constantly.
Gradually add dry ingredients (or take 1 cup of milk before it's warm and make a paste with dry ingredients), then add to warm milk, stirring until mixture is thick.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and oleo.
Pour into pie shell.

title: brownies
directions: Stir flour; measure and resift with salt.
Cream butter. Gradually blend in sugar and beaten eggs.
Beat until smooth and fluffy.
Add vanilla and stir in chocolate.
Add flour alternately with evaporated milk and water mixed together, stirring after each addition.
Add nuts, stirring.
Spread in 8-inch pan that bottom has been lined with wax paper and buttered.
Bake in 325° oven for 15 minutes.
Remove pan to cool.
Cut in pieces.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: crock-pot macaroni
directions: Grease crock-pot.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place cheese slices over mixture in crock-pot.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and cook 3 to 4 hours on low or 3 hours and 15 minutes on medium.

title: apple chip cake
directions: Combine in large bowl the oil, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, salt and soda together and add to first mixture.
Add nuts, apples and vanilla. Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil chicken until tender and debone. Cook vermicelli in chicken stock.
You may need to add a little water.
Saute onions, celery and bell pepper in margarine.
Chop cheese into chunks.
Mix all ingredients together, including cheese; microwave a couple of minutes until cheese is melted. Place into baking dish and bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: crunchy apple crisp
directions: Place apple slices in 2-quart (8 x 8-inch) glass baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients, except butter, in medium bowl.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Microwave for 12 to 16 minutes on High or until apples are tender.

title: hamburger steak
directions: Pinch bread into small pieces in mixing bowl.
Add enough milk to moisten while you dice onion.
Add ingredients together.
Make into patties the size you want and about 1/2-inch thick.
Fry in large pan (with just enough oil to cover bottom good) until brown.

title: cheesy meatballs
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients and blend well.
Shape into small balls.
Place in shallow pan and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: "cranberry-orange relish"
directions: Juice orange.
Grind cranberries and peel of orange.
Add sugar and orange juice; mix well.
Refrigerate several hours or up to 2 weeks.
Makes 3 cups.

title: ham and apple strata
directions: Spread bread with butter.
Arrange buttered slices in single layer in greased 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Layer half of cheese, then all of ham and apples (with sugar and cinnamon).
Top with remainder of cheese.
Beat together eggs, half and half, mustard powder and Worcestershire.
Pour over casserole.
Cover; refrigerate at least 6 hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350°
for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: classic chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling salted water; drain.
Melt butter; blend in flour, salt and dash of pepper.
Add chicken broth all at once, cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Stir in sherry and cream.
Place broccoli crosswise in 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add half of sauce.
Top with chicken.
To remaining sauce, add cheese and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with extra cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, then broil just until sauce is golden.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch pie crust.
Cover with other pie crust.
Cut slits in top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: sauteed squash and tomatoes
directions: Clean squash; slice into 1/2-inch thick diagonal slices.
In hot
butter in medium skillet, saute, stirring until golden, about 3 minutes.
Add squash and remaining ingredients; toss lightly to combine.
Cook, tightly covered, over medium heat for 10 to 15 minutes or until squash is tender.
Serves 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Pour soups and milk over chicken.
Add 2 cups of broth to one package of dressing mix.
Add sage and pour over chicken.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: crusty garlic bread sticks
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Unroll dough; separate into strips.
Twist strips.
Place 1-inch apart on large ungreased cookie sheets. Brush bread sticks with margarine; sprinkle with garlic powder. Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.

title: meat lovers calzone
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. On greased baking sheet, unroll dough and press into 12 x 12-inch square. Cut in half lengthwise. Spread 1/4 cup Ricotta cheese over each half, leaving a 3/4-inch edge. Top each half with 1/2 cup meat sauce. Fold dough over and seal by pressing edges with tines of a fork. Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown. Serves 6.

title: pistachio delight
directions: Mix flour and butter well.
Then add nuts.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Flour bottom crust with 1 teaspoon of flour and place floured side down in pan.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Bring margarine, cocoa, milk and salt to a boil, then add powdered sugar, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Mix together.
Pour over cake while still warm.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt butter over low heat in saucepan. Blend in flour and seasoning. Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth. Remove from heat.
Stir in milk. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add grated cheese; stir until melted.
Place half of the asparagus in baking dish. Top with half of the cheese sauce and potato chips. Repeat with another layer of asparagus, sauce and potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Beat eggs and flour and add other ingredients.
Fry like pancakes.
You might need to add additional flour.

title: pecan pie
directions: Lightly beat eggs; add sugar, syrup, salt, nutmeg, vanilla and oleo.
Mix well.
Add pecans and pour into crust.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: rolled sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and almond extract.
Mix together.
Stir in Bisquick to form a soft dough ball.
Chill 1 hour.
Heat oven to 400°.
Roll 1/4 of the dough at a time 1/8-inch thick on a floured board.
Cut into desired shapes. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle cookies with granulated sugar.
Bake until all edges are delicately browned, about 5 to 7 minutes.

title: apple squares
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle sugar over apples; set aside.
In a bowl, beat the egg.
Add oil, flour, soda, cinnamon and salt (sift flour and spices).
Blend oil and egg into apples.
Add flour mixture all at once.
Beat with wooden spoon until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Leave in pan.
When cool, sprinkle with 4x sugar.
Cut into 24 squares.
Enjoy.

title: meringue kisses
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Cover cookie sheets with aluminum foil. Beat egg whites, cream of tartar and salt in a small bowl until foamy.
Beat in sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Continue beating for 3 to 5 minutes or until becomes stiff and glossy.
Do not underbeat.
Fold in vanilla, food coloring and chocolate morsels. Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls about 1 inch apart onto foil.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until crisp and dry.
Cool completely on foil. Yields about 3 dozen.

title: pam's fudge pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cocoa.
Add margarine and beaten eggs, then add vanilla.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 325° oven for 35 to 40 minutes until firm.

title: 125 year old black walnut cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and baking powder alternately with milk, beginning with and ending with flour.
Add flavoring.
Stir in floured walnuts.
Bake in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: fish balls
directions: Drain liquid from fish.
Remove bones.
Flake fish.
Add rice, beaten eggs, salt, paprika, lemon juice, onion and parsley.
Stir with fork until well blended.
Form into bite size balls.
Roll in cornflake crumbs.
Deep-fry in oil at 375° until browned, about 3 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve warm, plain or with tartar sauce.
For a family main dish, make into patties and pan-fry.

title: rhubarb brunch cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, water, oil and eggs at low speed until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Pour into greased pan.
Top with rhubarb; sprinkle with sugar.
Pour cream on top. Bake for 1 1/4 hours.
Serve warm.
Store in refrigerator.

title: broccoli puff
directions: *Can substitute 2 packages frozen corn or chopped spinach for the broccoli.

title: lasagne
directions: Sprinkle beef with all seasonings and brown. Add diced green pepper and onion.
Simmer a few minutes, adding tomato sauce. Cook lasagne according to package.
Alternate layers of lasagne, beef mix, cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese, ending with beef mix.
Cook 20 minutes at 375°.
Add Mozzarella and bake 5 more minutes.
Freezes well, but will need to be thawed beforehand or baked longer.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix margarine, mustard, poppy seed, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Spread on rolls that have been sliced in half.
Add Swiss cheese and boiled ham, then put top on.
Bake in oven with foil over top at 325° until cheese melts.

title: homemade soap
directions: Dissolve the can of lye in the water, stirring to cool it. The tallow should be neither warm nor hard.
Very slowly pour the lye into the tallow in a thin steady stream, stirring it all continuously.
Then without stopping, add the glycerin, lavender and ammonia.
Beat until creamy and smooth.
Pour into small forms.
When hard, it is ready to use.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until tender.
Cut into large cubes to cook faster.
Remove from pan and drain.
Place in a large mixing bowl and mash until smooth (a hand mixer works great).
Add honey, brown sugar, molasses, raisins and blend well.
Now place sweet potatoes in a baking dish or pan and sprinkle walnuts on top. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs; beat until well blended.
Add flour and salt.
Mix well until batter is smooth and well blended.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a tube pan.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours.

title: applesauce-raisin bread
directions: Stir all ingredients until dry ones are wet.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove from pan to cool. Makes one loaf.

title: bundt coffee cake(best with no substitutions)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spray bundt pan with Pam and dust with confectioners sugar.
Mix together cake mix, sugar, oil, eggs, sour cream, almond and vanilla extract.
Blend well.
Pour half of the batter into the bundt pan.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon mixture over the batter and add the remaining batter.
Bake at 325° for one hour and 10 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Remove from pan and cool completely on wire rack.
Sprinkle cooled cake with confectioners sugar.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: gorp
directions: Mix together all ingredients in a large bowl.
Store in a plastic bag or a covered container.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottoms of 2 loaf pans (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Mix shortening and sugar in large bowl.
Add eggs, sweet potato and water.
Blend in flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder and vanilla.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into pans.
Bake until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, approximately 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Loosen sides of loaves from pans.
Remove from pans.
Cool completely before slicing.
To store, wrap and refrigerate no longer than 10 days.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown beef with onion and garlic.
Drain.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, basil, oregano and salt.
Simmer uncovered 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook lasagne noodles according to package instructions.
Mix cottage cheese, parsley, eggs and Mozzarella cheese.

title: julia's cookie recipe
directions: Shape dough into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Yield:
6 dozen.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add milk and flavoring, then add crackers, raisins and pecans.
Mix well.
Bake in well-greased cake pan for 1 hour or until done at 350°.

title: italian stuffed shells
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef and onion. Drain well. Stir in spaghetti sauce.
Simmer, uncovered, about 30 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
Let cool, then crumble.
Fix pudding according to directions on box and drain pineapple.
Layer 1/2 the cake crumbs in a punch bowl.
Then top with 1/2 pudding, pie filling, pineapple, bananas and Cool Whip. Repeat layers using remaining ingredients one layer at a time. Garnish with coconut, pecans and cherries if you desire.

title: puffy pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix flour, eggs, milk, and nutmeg together, leaving batter lumpy.
Melt butter in large frypan and add batter.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, return briefly to oven.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Cut in wedges.

title: mary's cucumber cheese dip
directions: Mix ingredients together, then add 1 cucumber, diced.
Can be made ahead, then add cucumber the day you are going to serve.
I always double the recipe because it goes fast!

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In a heavy 2-quart saucepan, combine the sugars, milk and marshmallows.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring until the sugars dissolve and marshmallows melt.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter.
Pour in a buttered 8-inch square baking pan. Cool.
When firm, cut into squares.
Yield: 3 dozen.

title: beef and noodles
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add tomato sauce and simmer 30 minutes.
Cook noodles separately.
Grate cheese and add to meat. Simmer until cheese melts.
Drain noodles and add to meat mixture.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Heat the pineapple. Add the sugar and lemon juice. Add gelatin dissolved in cold water.
Cool mixture until it begins to thicken. Add cheese, walnuts and whipped cream.
A few maraschino cherries may be added for color. Serves 8.
Good with ham.

title: french vegetable soup
directions: Fry hamburger in pot.
Add chicken broth, 1 quart water, 1 package onion soup mix and celery.
Boil all this for 20 minutes. Add tomatoes, vegetables and macaroni.
Boil 15 minutes longer.

title: "pina colada" cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 round pans, 8 or 9-inch, or 13 x 9 x 2-inches.

title: green chile-turkey enchiladas
directions: Mix and heat the soup and chiles.
Stir in sour cream and turkey.
Bring a little bit of oil to simmer.
Soak each tortilla in oil to soften; drain.
Spread a large spoonful of soup mixture on each tortilla.
Roll up and place in a baking dish.
Grate cheese over top.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute the squash, bell pepper, celery, onion, garlic salt, salt, pepper, Accent, bay leaf and nutmeg in oil over low heat. Cover pan and cook until tender. Remove bay leaf.
Add cornbread crumbs, eggs, sage and 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Put in casserole and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle remaining cheese over top and return to oven for 10 minutes. Serves 6 to 8. Freezes well.

title: english chutney
directions: Slice tomatoes, peppers, apples and onions.
Add salt, brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, and cloves and celery salt.
Cook the mixture for one hour then add vinegar.
Boil until thickness desired.
Put in jars while hot.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: To
Cook
by Microwave:
Arrange chicken in 2 1/2 quart shallow, oval casserole dish with meatier portions toward edge of dish.
Combine
remaining ingredients;
pour over chicken. Cover with wax paper.
Cook at High 18 to 20 minutes or until chicken is
done.
Let
stand, covered, for 5 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti, rice or noodles.

title: talarena
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper in shortening; drain.
Add tomatoes, garlic salt, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add cooked, unseasoned rice or macaroni and corn.
Mix well; pour into buttered 2 to 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: mama's egg custard pie
directions: Combine milk, eggs, sugar and nutmeg.
Beat well.
Pour into a deep unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: dick's special ham hocks and lima beans
directions: In a large pot, place the ham hocks and cover with 2 inches of water.
Cook at low heat for 3 to 5 hours.
Keep a watch to make sure the water doesn't boil off; when the meat will come off the bones, remove the ham hocks and let them cool.
Be sure and save the juice the ham hocks were cooked in.
Wash the dry lima beans and place them in a large cooking pot.
Pour the juice from the cooked ham hocks over the lima beans and cover them with 2 inches of juice.
Bring to a boil and turn down and simmer for 2 to 3 minutes.
Watch to be sure they are covered with the juice.
As they swell, you will need to add more juice.
Remove from heat and let them stand.
While they stand, remove the meat from the bones and cut the meat and rind into small pieces.

After the lima beans have set for 1 hour, add the diced onions and celery, seasoned salt, Mrs. Dash and the pepper and the cut up pieces of ham hock. Add more of the juice from the ham hocks or, if no more is available, add water to cover the lima beans with 2 inches of liquid.
Bring to a boil and turn down to simmer for about 2 to 3 hours.
You can tell when they are done by testing a lima bean. Towards the end of the cooking cycle, only allow the juice to cover the lima beans.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix and spread in bottom of pan.
Brown in oven at 350°.
Put in refrigerator.
Cool completely.

title: tasty taco potato casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Layer in a greased two-quart casserole dish 1/2 meat, potatoes, carrots, peppers and tomato. Mix soup, tomato sauce and taco seasoning together and spread 1/2 of this on the top.
Layer the 2nd half the same way.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle 1/2 cup of shredded cheese (taco flavored) on top.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: oven barbecued spareribs
directions: Place ribs in a single layer in large baking pans.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Drain, reserving 1/4 cup drippings.
Turn ribs; bake 30 minutes longer.
Meanwhile, in a saucepan, saute onions and celery in reserved drippings until tender.

title: corn pone
directions: Put water, meal and oleo in a heavy pot and cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Remove from stove and stir in all other ingredients until smooth.
Pour into a 14 x 10 x 2-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until golden brown and cracking.

title: barbecue stew
directions: Cook meat in salt water until tender.
Remove meat and put in a roasting pan.
Put potatoes, carrots and onions with meat. Combine remaining ingredients and heat; pour sauce over meat and cook until vegetables are tender.

title: tex mex chops
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, brown chops in oil 2 minutes on each side.
Add salsa and chilies to skillet.
Lower heat, cover and simmer gently 8 to 10 minutes.
Serves 4.
Serve with buttered corn and cucumber and red onion salad.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni; wash and drain.
Add vinegar; mix well.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to macaroni.
Mix well.
Chill before serving.
May want to try mixture with diced, cooked potatoes for potato salad.

title: pea salad
directions: I mix my salad dressing and Italian dressing together.
Mix all ingredients and chill (do not cook peas).

title: fresh peach pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Combine oil, sugar, eggs, and vanilla.
Blend until smooth.
Gradually add flour then fold in peaches, nuts, and coconut.
Cook for 1 hour the reduce heat to 300 degrees and cook another 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, peach juice and 4x sugar and pour over warm cake.

title: pork chops with creamy gravy
directions: About 30 Minutes Before Serving:
Into pie plate, pour 2 tablespoons milk. On waxed paper, combine 1/4 cup flour, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper. Dip pork chops in milk, then into flour mixture to coat well.

title: thai chicken fettuccine salad
directions: Combine picante sauce, peanut butter, honey, orange juice, soy sauce and ginger in a small saucepan.
Cook and stir over low heat until blended and smooth.
Reserve 1/4 cup picante sauce mixture.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Mix crushed vanilla wafers and 6 tablespoons melted margarine and place half of this mixture in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix the next 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into chocolate mixture.
Put half of chocolate mixture over cookie crumbs.
Slice ice cream and place a layer on top of chocolate layer.
(This step is easier if you let ice cream sit for a few minutes to the point that it starts melting.)
Layer remaining chocolate, then remaining cookie crumbs.
Freeze covered in plastic wrap or it will absorb freezer odors.
Best to make the day before.
