Also, let sit out a few minutes before serving or you will not be able to slice easily.

title: chinese wedding cake
directions: Prepare Jiffy cake mix as per package.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes (no longer) in 9 x 13-inch oblong pan; cool.
Mix cream cheese, pudding and milk.
Spread over cool cake.
Spread pineapple over cream mixture.
Spread Cool Whip over this.
Add coconut on top and refrigerate.

title: angel salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; cool.
Add pineapple, cheese, nuts and celery.
Chill until slightly jelled.
Fold in whipped cream.
Add coconut and marshmallows if desired.
Cool until firm.

title: brandi's no fat fruit dip
directions: Let cream cheese soften to room temperature. Use mixer to blend. Add large jar marshmallow cream. Store in the refrigerator until chilled.

title: apple pie bars
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Cut butter into flour mixture with pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in egg yolks (mixture will be crumbly).

title: confetti scalloped potatoes
directions: In a skillet, melt butter over medium heat; saute onions until tender.
Stir in potatoes, soup and milk.
Add cheese, green pepper, pimiento, pepper and 1/2 cup cracker crumbs.
Pour into a shallow casserole; top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Stir together dry ingredients.
Add eggs and milk.
Add shortening; stir.
A heavy iron skillet is ideal for baking and is best heated in oven.
Grease skillet well.
Pour in mixture and bake for 25 minutes at 400°.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine cheese, Bisquick and sau sage; form into balls.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Makes 72 balls.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Slice top off potatoes lengthwise.
Scoop out potato with teaspoon, leaving some potato around skin.
Add eggs, milk and margarine and mix with mixer.
Add Cheddar cheese and onions and mix by hand.
Spoon back into skins and wrap separately in foil and freeze.
Take out of freezer (desired amount) and bake at 350° to 400° for 40 minutes to 1 hour.

title: zucchini saute
directions: Melt margarine in skillet; add zucchini, green pepper and onion.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Cook until ___.

title: powdered sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Put in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Make into balls; flatten with fork.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix together.
Add to first mixture and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 35 or 40 minutes.

title: beef noodle soup
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add all ingredients and water.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours.
Adjust seasonings to taste.
Soup can be frozen.

title: tuna log
directions: Combine all ingredients except parsley.
Shape into a log or ball.
Roll ball in parsley on wax paper.
Chill.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Shred
chipped
beef into bottom of 12-inch shallow greased
casserole.
Wrap
a
half slice of bacon around each breast.
Place	the
breast
on
top
of the beef. Sprinkle with pepper.
Blend
the
soup with sour cream and mushrooms and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake for 2 1/2 hours. No salt is	needed	because
of chipped beef.
Uncover last 1/2 hour.

title: minnesota baked beans
directions: Drain 3 cans of beans and put into a 3 or 4-quart casserole. Add pork and beans with juices.
Dice and fry bacon until crisp. Remove bacon.
Drain grease.
Save.
Add few tablespoons of grease to skillet.
Saute diced onion until transparent.
Return bacon grease to skillet.
Add garlic powder, salt, dry mustard, vinegar and brown sugar.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Mixture will turn syrupy. Pour over beans and bacon in casserole.
I use up to 1 cup of bacon grease to make syrup.
This may sound greasy (but it isn't) and it is oh sooo good and different for a special barbecue or picnic. Best served hot.
Make day before for flavors to mix.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: date pecan balls
directions: In heavy saucepan, put butter, sugar, dates and pecans in order listed.
Cover and heat over medium heat; stir occasionally until mixture bubbles well (10 to 15 minutes).
Remove from heat and cool 5 minutes.
Add Rice Krispies and stir gently with wooden spoon, mixing well.

title: white chili
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces and brown with garlic, cumin and, if desired, peppers.
Add sherry; cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Add salsa and beans and simmer 10 minutes.
Add Monterey Jack cheese and stir until melted.
Serves 6.
Enjoy.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Brown onion, pepper and garlic in butter.
Let simmer until pepper is tender.
Add tomatoes and seasonings; boil 10 minutes longer.
Serve over rice.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Quickly dip tortillas in hot oil, just to soften and make pliable.
Drain on paper towel and blot to remove any excess oil. Set aside.
Combine whipped cream cheese, mayonnaise, mustard, garlic powder and hot pepper sauce, mixing well.
Spread cream cheese mixture on each tortilla.
Arrange layers of ham or turkey, cheese slices and lettuce on each tortilla, as desired. Roll up tightly as a jelly roll.
Wrap securely in plastic wrap. Chill overnight.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine. Add rice. Place boneless chicken breasts on top of rice. Pour soups and water over chicken. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: easy beef and macaroni
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain off liquid.
Add Miracle Whip and macaroni.
Heat and stir.
Top with grated cheese.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind apple, orange and cranberries in blender or food processor.
Add sugar.
In another bowl, dissolve jello in 3/4 cup boiling water.
Let cool.
Add pineapple and the ground fruit to the jello.
Refrigerate 48 hours before serving.

title: saucepan brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together in saucepan.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar, flour, baking powder, vanilla and nuts. Add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Spread in greased pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: french vanilla ice cream
directions: Cook milk, eggs, sugar and salt over low heat, stirring frequently to keep mixture from burning.
When cooked mixture coats a wooden spoon, remove from heat.
Add cream and vanilla. Cool mixture, then freeze using electric ice cream maker or hand cranked ice cream maker.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and bell pepper in skillet.
Drain good.
Add the next 6 ingredients, mixing well.
Line large casserole dish with flour tortillas (overlapping).
Spread 1/2 of mixture over tortillas.
Grate Longhorn cheese and sprinkle over meat.
Repeat layers, except for cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° until bubbly, then use the rest of cheese on top and bake until cheese is melted.
Serve hot.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans; set aside.
Mix berries, eggs and oil.
In second bowl, mix the flour, sugar, cinnamon, soda, salt and nuts.
Add berry mixture to flour mixture; stir just until blended.
Pour into pans.
Bake for 1 hour, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Makes 2 loaves.
Bake at 350°.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Beat eggs and add to dry ingredients.
Beat in vanilla.
Sprinkle coconut over bottom of crust.
Pour egg mixture over.
Bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: rhubarb fruit crisp
directions: Place rhubarb in the bottom of an ungreased 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle the jello over rhubarb.
Mix together remaining ingredients and spoon over jello.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cheese dip for nachos
directions: Heat together in heavy pan on low heat until cheese melts. Takes about an hour; easy to stick. Serve with nacho chips or potato chips. Also good as a topping for baked potatoes or in taco salad.

title: chocolatey fresh apple cake
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 60 to 65 minutes.

title: holiday buffet chicken
directions: Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with ham slices. Place chicken breasts on ham.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Preheat oven and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: kahlua
directions: Mix sugar with hot water until dissolved. Add other ingredients and pour in 1/2 gallon bottle. Age for at least 2 weeks.
(The longer it is aged, the better it will taste.)
When ready to serve, remove vanilla bean.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: In saucepan, heat pineapple juice, flour, vinegar, sugar and egg until thickened.
Mix in crushed pineapple and marshmallows. Place in covered container and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, add apples, peanuts and Cool Whip.	 Chill until serving time.

title: beet relish
directions: Chop beets and cabbage fine. Add the rest of the ingredients and cover with vinegar. It is then ready to serve.

title: hot ole dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan with a fork.
Add chili, hot chiles, then shredded Cheddar cheese on top. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook the bacon and crumble; refrigerate.
Combine the mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Just before serving, combine the remaining ingredients.
Pour the dressing over the salad with the crumbled bacon and mix well. Serve chilled.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Put out potatoes to thaw some and then mix all ingredients together.
Pour in greased casserole dish.
Top with Paprika and more grated cheese, then more paprika.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, stirring with a wire whisk to remove the large lumps.

title: pistachio oreo dessert
directions: Crush Oreos in blender or processor (3 to 5 cookies at a time).
Pour crumbs in bowl; mix in margarine.
Put 2/3 of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan; press firmly.
Mix pudding, milk, ice cream and Cool Whip together.
Pour over crumbs.
Top with remaining Oreo crumbs.
Place in freezer until ready to serve (can be refrigerated).

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Slice onions and pull apart.
Saute onions in 3/4 stick butter until soft.
Crush crackers into crumbs.
Remove onions from pan. Add remaining butter.
Place the cracker crumbs in the pan until coated with butter.
Layer onions, crumbs and cheese in a casserole dish. Finish with crumbs on top. Sprinkle milk over top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, eggs, oil and oranges with juice.
Pour into 2 (8-inch) well-greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool cake completely.
Drain pineapple.
Mix together pineapple and pudding.
Fold in whipped topping until blended well.
Frost cake and refrigerate.
(Freezes well.)

title: cocktail sauce for shrimp
directions: Mix all ingredients in advance and refrigerate.
Keeps for weeks.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix all except potatoes over low heat until melted.
Put in 2-quart baking dish.
Pour melted ingredients over potatoes.
Cook at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Chop chicken fine.
Add soup and sour cream.
Mix well and pour into a well-greased casserole.
Melt butter and mix with crackers.
Spread crumbs on chicken mixture and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: jane's hot crab-artichoke dip
directions: Saute pepper in oil over medium heat.
Mix in pepper, artichoke hearts, mayonnaise, green onions, pimento, Parmesan cheese, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, jalapenos and celery salt.
Stir in crab and spoon into a buttered casserole dish. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order in a 9 x 13 casserole dish. Cover and refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix milk, lime juice and egg yolks.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 3 tablespoons sugar and dash of vanilla.
Cover top of pie and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
May be served with whipped cream.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients; work together until smooth.
Shape into a roll and wrap in waxed paper.
Slice with a sharp knife in the same manner as refrigerator cookies; place on a buttered cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes, or until lightly browned.
The wafers may, prior to baking, be brushed with egg white and sprinkled with poppy seed, sesame seed, celery seed or more grated cheese.
Remove from oven; cool on racks.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes with skins on.
Peel when cool and shred.
Mix and refrigerate overnight.
Mix butter and corn flakes and put on top before putting in oven.

title: sour cream pickles and cucumbers
directions: Slice cucumber and onion, mix with remaining ingredients and marinate at least 1 hour.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef with salt.
Drain fat.
Add garlic salt and pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and spaghetti sauce mix.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Line baked cool pie shell with berries, reserving one cup of fresh berries for glaze.
Simmer 1 cup berries and water in saucepan.
In dish, mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add to hot fruit and water.
Cook until clear, stirring constantly.
Add lemon juice.
Top with whipped cream.
May use fresh peaches or blueberries.

title: shoe peg vegetable salad
directions: Mix vegetables in bowl.
Combine vinegar and corn syrup.
Stir into vegetables.
Add sweetener and chill well.
Makes 12 servings, using 1/2 cup corn syrup.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin until light and fluffy. Then in another bowl, combine all dry ingredients. Add pumpkin mixture; mix thoroughly. Put into ungreased 15 x 9 x 1-inch pan (or spray with Pam, if desired). Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Cool and frost.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine milk and egg yolks at low speed.
Slowly add juice until well blended.
Pour into 1 large graham cracker crust or 2 (9-inch) crusts.
Cover with Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: egg custard
directions: Scald milk; pour over eggs, sugar, salt, vanilla and nutmeg. Mix well and pour in crust.
Bake at 425 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 2 hours at 300°.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, sour cream and eggs; pour 1/2 of batter into a greased and floured 13x9 inch pan.
Mix brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts and sprinkle on top of batter.
Then pour remaining batter on top of batter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30-40 minutes.

title: bruschetta garlic bread
directions: Toast bread until lightly browned on both sides under a broiler.
Rub top with garlic.
Return slices to broiling tray. Sprinkle olive oil over bread slices.
Top with tomato slices and pepper.
Broil close to flame for 1 minute and serve at once.

title: cracker stuffing
directions: Saute mushrooms and onions in olive oil.
Mix crackers and eggs; add onions and mushrooms to crackers.
Add 3 tablespoons oil or margarine.
Add a little water if it is too dry.
Enjoy!

title: volcano bread dip
directions: Hollow out bread, making it like a bowl, saving bread pieces for
"dippers."
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour dip into bread bowl.

title: boiled peanuts
directions: Wash peanuts.
Put in large kettle and cover with water.
Add salt; bring to a boil and simmer about 5 1/2 hours, until peanuts are tender but still firm.
Taste and see if they are salty enough.
Drain.
Peanuts are good hot, warm or chilled.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat together eggs, milk, sugar and spices.
Add the bread and let set to soak.
Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: diabetic vegetable soup
directions: Saute ground chuck in oil; add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 35 to 45 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: crock-pot roast
directions: Put roast in crock-pot.
Add soup mix and mushroom soup.
Cook on low 10 to 12 hours.

title: po boys
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot or pressure cooker. Simmer for about 1 hour in pot or for about 15 minutes in pressure cooker.
Spread bread with mixture of 2 parts mayonnaise to 1 part mustard.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Set pineapple chunks aside. Combine brown sugar, cornstarch and salt in a large saucepan. Add pineapple juice, vinegar and soy sauce, stirring until well blended.
Bring to a boil over high heat, stirring constantly. Reduce heat to medium and cook until mixture thickens.
Remove form heat and add chicken, pineapple chunks, celery, green pepper and onion.
Continue to cook over medium heat 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add pimiento and cook 1 additional minute.
Serve chicken mixture over rice.
Yields 5 servings.
Serving size: 3/4 cup chicken mixture with 1/2 cup rice.
(Low cholesterol recipe.)

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Saute together the turkey, green pepper, onion, chili powder, garlic and oregano.
Add cheese, tomato sauce and rice.
Mix together; put in baking dish.
Top with 1 ounce grated cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix ingredients with salt, pepper and salad oil.
Spoon into pan and bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Serve at room temperature.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine.
Mix with cereal.
Put in brown bag with powdered sugar and shake.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Tear up lettuce and place in the bottom of your salad bowl, then add each of the items as indicated in that order.
(You may add more of any of the items.)
Spread a layer of mayo on top of ingredients, then top with shredded cheese.
Refrigerate.

title: pot roast
directions: Make a paste of the ingredients, except roast and vegetables. Sear meat on stove for 20 minutes.
In 13 x 9-inch pan, layer 1/2 sauce, meat, vegetables and remaining sauce.
Bake at 375° for about two hours, covered.
Can also be made in crock-pot.

title: bran bread
directions: Stir together flour, bran, baking soda and salt.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring just until evenly mixed.
Pour into buttered 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes until loaf tests done in center.
I make 5 small loaves and freeze.

title: banana pudding
directions: Layer the bottom of a large casserole with wafers.
Cover with sliced bananas, alternating wafers and bananas until full.

title: beef tips on rice
directions: Partially freeze steak. Slice diagonally across the grain into 2 x 1/4-inch strips. Saute steak and onion in butter until steak is brown. Add flour. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Add chicken soup and next 4 ingredients, stirring until blended. Cover and cook over low heat 30 minutes or until beef is tender. Serve over rice. Yields 4 servings.

title: cinnamon apple pizza
directions: Set cinnamon roll icing aside.
Separate dough into individual rolls.
Roll each out into a 4 in. circle.
Arrange on a greased 12-inch pizza pan overlapping edges.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Spoon the apple pie filling over the rolls to within 1/2 inch of the edge.
Combine the brown sugar and butter; sprinkle over pie filling.
Bake 6-8 minutes longer or until the crust is golden brown.
Cool.
Drizzle with the reserved icing.
Yield 10-12 servings.

title: baked chicken
directions: In a large flat casserole, mix sour cream, soup and sherry. Wrap each chicken breast in dried beef, then in bacon.
Secure with toothpick.
Lay chicken in sauce.
Cover tightly with foil. Bake 3 hours at 300°.
Remove foil last 15 minutes to let brown.

title: lime punch
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Add remaining liquids and mix thoroughly. Freeze in 1/2 gallon or 1 gallon jugs.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: creamed cauliflower
directions: Clean cauliflower and break into large pieces.
Steam or boil it until it's tender.
In small saucepan, heat milk and butter. Before the milk reaches boiling, gradually add flour.
Bring to boil and stir continuously until you have a thin cream sauce. Pour cream sauce over the cauliflower and stir until cauliflower is broken up and sauce is evenly stirred in.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: a hearty soup
directions: *Omit fennel if using Italian sausage.

title: rice burger skillet
directions: In skillet, brown beef and cook onion until tender.
Stir to separate meat; pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to boil.
Cover and cook over low heat 10 minutes or until rice is done.
Stir often.
Garnish with sliced cheese.

title: peachy-pink colored punch
directions: Mix well. Place in freezer until partly frozen. Shake well and serve slushy. Makes approximately 40 (3/4 c.) servings (about 2 gallons). You can adjust the amount of food coloring to get the exact color that you want.

title: ripe tomatoes with gravy
directions: Cut tomatoes into 1/3-inch slices; batter with flour.
Set aside 1 tablespoon remaining flour.
Heat oil in large skillet; fry tomatoes until golden brown, turning once.
Arrange tomatoes on serving platter; keep warm.
Add reserved tablespoon of flour to pan drippings, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add whipping cream; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Stir in brown sugar, salt and pepper.
Spoon over tomatoes.
Serves 8.

title: cucumber congealed salad
directions: Dissolve
jello
in hot water;
grate cucumbers and add to jello.
Blend cottage cheese and almonds.
Mix the balance of ingredients together and chill until ready to use.

title: oxtail stew
directions: Roll meat in flour.
Season.
Brown in hot fat.
Simmer together with first 12 ingredients for 3 hours.
Then add vegetables and simmer until tender.
Good family dinner on cold nights.

title: muriel's kapusta
directions: In a large Dutch oven, saute onions and veal in oil.
Add all sauerkraut, kielbasa, peppercorns and bay leaves.
Cook in covered pot for 1 hour.
Add catsup and cook for 45 minutes to 1 hour more with lid on.
Best served with Russian rye bread and pork chops.

title: baked stuffed trout
directions: A large whiting may be used in this recipe instead of trout.

title: crispy chicken
directions: Mix together and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove and sprinkle with potato chips.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: spinach savoy
directions: Combine drained spinach, soup mix and sour cream.
Put in greased casserole.
Mix margarine, bread crumbs and cheese. Sprinkle on top of spinach mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain. Add onion, corn, rice, garlic salt, salt, pepper and half the tomato sauce; mix well.
Slice tops from peppers; discard seed. Spoon ground beef mixture into peppers.
Place in baking dish.
Top with cheese and remaining tomato sauce.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 50 minutes.
Yield:
5 servings.

title: lemon pies
directions: Combine juice and rind. Gradually stir into Eagle Brand milk. Add egg yolks and stir well. Pour into crust.
Add cream of tartar to egg whites.
Beat until stiff enough to hold peak.
Add sugar gradually, beating until stiff but not dry.
Pile on top of filling.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 12 1/2 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Empty can of peaches in dish, mix flour, sugar, vanilla, and milk.
Pour into dish with peaches, and swirl through peaches.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown, about 45 minutes.

title: stuffed cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage into bite size pieces. Put half in bottom of pan. Crumble hamburger over the cabbage. Add onion, rice and tomatoes. Cover with remaining cabbage. Pour soup and water over top.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake covered for 1 1/2 hours at 400°.

title: egg breakfast
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with bread.
Cook bacon; crumble.
Beat eggs and milk; add other ingredients.
Season with salt and pepper or lemon and pepper.
Pour mixture over bread, cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry delite
directions: *Use low-fat milk when preparing pudding.

title: waldorf astoria stew
directions: Place first 6 ingredients in order given in bottom of roasting pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together; pour over meat and vegetables.
Put cover on roasting pan.
Bake 5 hours in 250° oven.
Don't peek!

title: hot fudge sundaes
directions: Slowly melt chocolate pieces in the milk.
Blend well.
Beat in Marshmallow Creme until well blended.
Serve warm or cold over vanilla ice cream.

title: astabula specials
directions: Cream brown sugar and butter.
Add egg.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Alternate dry ingredients with coffee.
Add raisins, nuts and vanilla.
(Raisins can be cut with scissors or knife.) Bake on a 10 1/2 x 12 1/2-inch cookie sheet with sides for 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: macaroni with shrimp salad
directions: Prepare shrimp the evening before.
Place shrimp in boiling water. When the water comes to a boil the second time, turn off heat, cover and let stand in water not more than 2 minutes. Drain, peel and devein shrimp.
Refrigerate.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Mix and spread on bottom of hamburger buns.
Put under broiler until hot and bubbly.
Butter top of buns and heat under broiler. Put together.
Great and fast.

title: tijuana train wreck
directions: Combine and simmer ingredients
for 2 1/2 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
To serve, place 1 large handful of tortilla chips on plate.
Cover with sauce, chopped lettuce, tomatoes, grated cheese, onions, olives and sour cream.

title: woodstove venison stew
directions: Fry bacon in large heavy skillet.
Add stew meat that has been rolled in seasoned flour.
Brown meat; add garlic (minced) and cook 1 minute.
Add water, bouillon cube, steak sauce, tomato juice, Port wine, lemon juice and thyme.
Cover and cook on woodstove about 1 hour.
Add vegetables and water if needed. Simmer about 1 hour.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Thicken stew slightly with flour.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 2 large cookie sheets; set aside.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
In mixer bowl, cream sugars, butter, shortening, vanilla and water until fluffy, scraping bowl occasionally.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour mixture.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheets.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes about 5 1/2 dozen.

title: sticky quickies
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour and yeast.
Heat milk, water, butter, sugar and salt until warm.
Pour into flour mixture.
Add egg and beat on high for 3 minutes.
Switch to dough hook or by hand, stir in 1 3/4 cups flour.
Cover and let rise for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed snow peas
directions: Mix until soft the brie, milk and Nature's Seasons.
Set aside.
Top and tail the peas and blanch in boiling water for 3 minutes, then rinse in cold water immediately.
Drain and pat dry. With sharp vegetable parer, split snow peas on curved side. Place cheese in a pastry bag and squeeze in pea pod.
Serve chilled.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, saute the onions in the butter until soft.
Add the carrots.
Cook over medium heat for about 3 minutes.
Add broccoli, bell pepper, garlic and rice.
Stir to blend.
Add the chicken broth.
Bring to a boil.
Cover with tight fitting lid.
Cook over low to medium heat for about 20 minutes or just until rice is done.
Add parsley and salt and pepper.

title: potted chicken
directions: Clean whole roasting chicken and rub inside with salt.
Season outside with salt, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Brown chicken in Dutch oven on all sides in hot shortening.
Saute onions in pot with chicken.
Dissolve chicken bouillon cubes in boiling water and pour over chicken and onions.
Simmer until chicken is tender. Make gravy.
Serve over rice.

title: bread and apple pudding
directions: Remove crusts from bread and cut in quarters.
Peel and slice apples.
Combine apples with the water and let simmer on low heat until barely tender.
Add 1/2 cup sugar.
Stir gently (don't break apples).
Place bread in buttered casserole dish packing closely together.
Cover bread with the apples and juice.
Beat egg yolks until light.
Add milk and vanilla.
Mix well and pour over pudding.
Dot with bits of butter.
Bake 20 minutes.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar.
Spread over pudding and brown in oven.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain fruit.
Mix all ingredients until creamy.
Let sit overnight.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix cheese, flour, salt and red pepper.
Add melted butter to make a soft dough.
Roll.
Cut in small rounds.
Bake in hot oven.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Beat until smooth. Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sneaky pete
directions: Don't dilute.
Mix all together well.
Freeze.
Best when done the day before use.

title: yummy ice cream topper
directions: Spread pie filling on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine dry cake mix and nuts.
Sprinkle on top of pie filling.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until golden.
Serve on top of ice cream.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Saute celery, onion and bell pepper in butter.
Add soup and tomatoes.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add shrimp, green onions, parsley and Worcestershire sauce and cook raw shrimp 8 minutes or precooked shrimp 3 minutes.
Add rice and turn into casserole dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix oil and sugar well.
Add beaten egg.
Stir in molasses. Add dry ingredients.
Roll into ball (1-inch).
Roll in 1/2 cup sugar and flatten with bottom of glass.

title: holiday eggnog
directions: Combine first eight ingredients in container of electric blender; cover and process until smooth.
Pour into small glasses and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Serve immediately.
Makes 5 cups.

title: cinnamon-crusted apples
directions: Coat an 11 x 7 x 2-inch casserole dish with cooking spray. Pour water in dish.
Peel, core and slice apples; arrange apples in dish.
Coat apples lightly with cooking spray.
Combine the brown sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg; cut in margarine with blender until mixture is coarse like corn meal.
Sprinkle evenly over apples.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes, or until apples are tender.

title: baked indian pudding(makes 8 portions)
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients for about 15 minutes. Beat the egg.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into a baking pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours. Stir every 20 minutes. Top serving of Indian Pudding with vanilla ice cream.

title: dieter's pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Whisk in yogurt.
Fold in topping and transfer to pie crust.
Refrigerate overnight or at least 2 hours.
You may use any flavor: raspberry, lemon, etc.

title: favorite pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add one egg at a time, mixing well with each one.
Add flavoring.
Slowly add flour, a small amount at a time, until well mixed. Grease and flour a Bundt pan. Add mixture and bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with cooking spray; remove crust from bread.
Cover bottom of pan.
Place layer of American cheese to your liking and layer of bread.
Top with diced ham, pepper and onion.
Beat together the eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Pour over bread.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Great if made the night before.
Set in fridge overnight; bake in morning.

title: giant birthday cookie
directions: Beat together margarine, peanut butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into cookie sizes.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Combine flour and salt in a large bowl, cut in shortening. Combine egg, water and vinegar; mix well.
Pour liquid ingredients into dry ones.
Mix until flour is moistened and dough is easy to handle.
Divide into 3 equal parts.
Roll out one part at a time on a floured board.
Dough may be covered and refrigerated for up to 1 week.
Dough may also be frozen.
Makes pastry for three 9-inch pies.

title: banana fritters
directions: Sift flour, measure and resift with baking powder, salt and sugar.
Set aside.
Beat egg well; add milk and pour into dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Peel bananas and cut each in half lengthwise, then once across.
Dip pieces into batter and fry in oil heated to 375 degrees until they are golden brown.
Drain and serve hot with maple syrup or flavored syrup.

title: microwave basic brownies
directions: In small bowl, mix with mixer on medium speed, eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla, about 1 minute until light.
Add melted butter. Continue beating.
Mix in flour and cocoa at low speed.
Stir in nuts.

title: cheese log
directions: Combine cheeses, margarine, wine, chives and horseradish with electric mixer.
Beat until fluffy.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour or overnight.

title: hamburger and corn casserole
directions: Brown
hamburger
with chopped green pepper until done; drain. In
a 2-quart casserole dish, layer hamburger mixture, then layer
drained
corn, then layer chopped tomatoes.	Bake about 1 1/2
to
2 hours at 350°.
Remove from oven and grate cheese
and put on top of casserole.
Place in oven just long enough to melt cheese. Serve.

title: brunch egg casserole
directions: Spread croutons in greased 10 x 6-inch pan.
Sprinkle cheese over croutons.
Mix and pour over eggs, milk, salt, mustard and pepper.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain.
Crumble and sprinkle over all.
Bake 50 minutes or until set in a 325° oven.

title: kraut(made in a stone-jar)
directions: Thoroughly scald the churn, then cool well with ice or spring water.
Now, pour in the thick cream; churn fast at first, then as the butter forms, more slowly.
Always with perfect regularity.
In warm weather, pour a little cold water into the churn.
Should the butter form slowly; in winter, if the cream is too cold, add a little warm water to bring it to the proper temperature.

When the butter has "come" rinse the sides of the churn down with cold water, and take the butter up with a perforated dasher or a wooden ladle, turning it dextrously just below the surface of the buttermilk to catch every stray bit.
Have ready some very cold water in a deep wooden tray and into this, plunge the dasher.
When you draw it from the churn, the butter will float off, leaving the dasher free.

When you have collected all the butter, gather behind a wooden butter ladle and drain off the water, squeezing and pressing the butter with the ladle; then, pour on more cold water and work the butter with the ladle to get the milk out; drain off the water.

Sprinkle salt over the butter, a tablespoonful to a pound; work it in a little and set in a cool place for an hour to harden; then, work and knead until not another drop of water exudes, and the butter is perfectly smooth and close in texture and polish; then, with the ladle make up into little rolls, little balls, stamped pats, etc.
The churn, dasher, tray and ladle should be well scalded before using, so that the butter will not stick to them and then cooled with very cold water.

title: cajun barbecue beans
directions: Brown the meat in a large skillet.
Pour off the grease.
Stir in the onion and bell pepper and saute slightly.
Transfer the ground meat, onion and bell pepper into a 2-quart casserole.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tuna patties for microwave
directions: Mix cornbread batter with tuna.
Make 4 to 6 patties and place on bacon rack (number of patties depends on size of microwave). Optional:
Mix chopped green peppers into batter and tuna.
Cook for 4 to 6 minutes or until done.

title: bran-apple muffins(low-fat)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt in a large bowl.
Mix cereal and milk in another bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Beat margarine and sugar in a large bowl with electric mixer on medium speed until light and fluffy.
Blend in cereal mixture and egg.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir just until moistened.
Stir in apples.
Spoon into greased muffin pan, filling each cup 2/3 full.
Bake 25 minutes.
Makes 18.

title: creamy beef and cheese dip
directions: Unwrap	the cream cheese; put into
quart
microwave bowl. Cook in microwave 45 seconds to 1 minute or until soft. Add all other ingredients and stir until
well blended.
Cover and cook in the microwave oven 3 to 5
minutes,
stirring once during cooking. Serve with Melba toast, chips or crackers.

title: deep dish pizza crust
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; set aside until it bubbles up. Mix flour, salt and sugar in bowl; add yeast and oil.
Knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Place
in greased bowl and let raise to about double size;
punch
down	and
let raise again (about 20 minutes).
Roll out to desired size.

title: date and walnut roll
directions: Combine dates, butter, sugar and water in a pan and stir constantly over heat without boiling until the sugar is dissolved. Bring to a boil and remove from the heat.
Transfer mixture to a large bowl to cool to room temperature.
Grease 2 nut roll tins. Stir soda, egg and nuts into date mixture, then sifted flour. Spoon mixture evenly into prepared tins.
Bake in moderate oven at 180°C for about an hour.
Stand rolls in tins for 10 minutes with lids on.
Remove lids, turn on wire rack to cool.
When cool, serve buttered.

title: plain pound cake
directions: Cream first 2 ingredients.
Mix in remaining ingredients. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: anadama bread
directions: Bring to a boil water and then stir in oatmeal.
Add molasses, oil and salt.
Add alternately yeast mixture and flour.
Knead 8 to 10 minutes until smooth and elastic.
Let rise 1 hour.
Punch down.
Shape loaves.
Let rise one hour.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Makes two loaves.

title: oven swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into bite-sized pieces.
Combine flour and salt and coat meat.
Reserve remaining flour for sauce.
Brown meat in shortening.
Transfer to shallow baking dish.
Blend reserved flour into pan drippings in skillet.
Add cut up tomatoes and Worcestershire sauce to drippings and cook to gravy consistency. Pour over meat.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours or until tender.
Sprinkle cheese over meat.
Return to oven for a few minutes to melt cheese.
Serve over hot rice.

title: sweet-sour salad
directions: Mix the last 5 ingredients and mix with the vegetables.
Let set overnight.

title: do nothing cake
directions: Cook for 1 minute longer and pour over cake.

title: chicken casserole iii
directions: Cook chicken breasts 20 minutes in gently boiling water.
Cook noodles.
Place in layers in 9 x 13-inch pan, first the chicken (cut up into bite size pieces), then noodles, then broccoli (cut up).
In saucepan melt butter; add milk, soup mix and cheese sauce mixes.
Stir until smooth. Pour over casserole.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: perfect peach cobbler
directions: Mix butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine sugar, flour, baking powder and milk in mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Pour melted butter over sugar mixture.
Do not stir.
Arrange peach slices evenly in baking pan.
Bake in preheated (325°) oven for 30 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate pie cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all milk, butter, egg, brown sugar, sugar, molasses, cocoa and cinnamon.
Stir until fully mixed.
Now, add the flour.
Whip until lumps are gone and it is smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Butter and flour cake pan. Cook 20 to 30 minutes or until done.
Cake should be moist.

title: pollo a la reina(serves 8)
directions: Brush chicken with melted
butter
and arrange in glass baking dish.
Blend soup and sour cream together until smooth. Stir in rest of ingredients;
pour	over
chicken
and bake at 350° for 40 to 45
minutes
or	until
fork-tender
and nicely browned.
Serve from dish.

title: eggplant sandwiches
directions: Peel eggplant.
Slice eggplant into 1/2-inch thick slices, then salt each slice to get water out and the salt softens the eggplant.
Let slices stand with salt, while water runs out. While they drain, mix bread crumbs, eggs, Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper and chopped parsley into a paste.
Dry the slices, then fry in oil until browned.
Next, put a teaspoon of the stuffing on one slice of eggplant and cover with another.
Fry these sandwiches. Cover with tomato sauce and bake 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well; pour into an 8-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Reduce temperature to 325° and bake 30 minutes more.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place rice in greased casserole dish.
Lay chicken in casserole dish on top of rice.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix. Gently pour on soup mixed with water.
Cover and bake in 325° oven for about 2 hours.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix milk with lemon juice, then add Cool Whip and blend with mixer.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Pour into crust and chill. (Can top with chopped pecans.) Makes 2 pies.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: miracle pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in container of an electric blender.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour into a lightly greased and floured 10-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Yields 6 servings.

title: pineapple-glazed apple pie
directions: In large saucepan, combine 1 1/2 cups pineapple juice and sugar.
Bring to a boil; add apple wedges.
Simmer covered 3 to 4 minutes, or until apples are tender, but not soft.
With a slotted spoon, take apples from liquid and set aside to drain.
Blend remaining 1/4 cup pineapple juice slowly into the cornstarch; add to hot liquid in saucepan.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles; cook 1 minute more.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter, vanilla and salt.
Cover and cool 30 minutes without stirring.
Pour half the liquid into the baked pie shell, spreading to cover the bottom.
Arrange apples on top.
Cover and refrigerate.
Before serving, garnish with whipped cream and chopped macadamia nuts, if desired.

title: cream wafers
directions: Mix thoroughly butter, cream and flour.
Cover and chill. Heat oven to 375°.
Roll about 1/3 of dough at a time 1/8-inch thick on floured cloth-covered board (keep remaining dough refrigerated until ready to roll).
Cut into 1 1/2-inch circles. Transfer rounds with spatula to piece of waxed paper that is heavily covered with granulated sugar.
Turn each round so that both sides are covered with sugar.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Prick rounds
with fork about 4 times.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes or just until set, but not brown; cool.
Put cookies together in pairs with Cool Whip.

title: mock filet mignon
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix lightly. Shape mixture into 6 patties, 1 1/2-inches thick.
Wrap 1 slice bacon around each patty. Secure with a wooden pick.
Place on a broiler rack. Broil 3 to 6 minutes on each side, depending on desired degree of doneness.
Yields 6 servings.

title: crunchy chews
directions: Combine corn syrup and sugar in large saucepan.
Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; quickly stir in peanut butter.
Add peanuts and cereal, stirring to coat evenly. Turn into a greased 13 1/2 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix peanuts, sugar and Karo.
Using Pyrex bowl, cook 7 1/2 minutes on Full power.
Remove and stir in vanilla and oleo. Return to microwave and cook 2 1/2 minutes longer.
Remove and add soda immediately, stirring and mixing well.
Pour into greased pan or 1 that has been lined with wax paper.
Cut while still warm.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Heat enchilada sauce, tomato sauce and water.
Brown meet with garlic and onion.
Add egg and olives. Add salt and 1/2 cup of sauce.
In a casserole, layer tortillas (dipped first in sauce), meat mixture, and cheese.
Pour over remaining sauce. Top with cheese. Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes. Serves 6.

title: butterscotch pound cake
directions: Blend butter, sugar and cream cheese well.
Add Crisco, eggs, flour and vanilla flavoring one at a time.
Coat pecans and butterscotch chips with flour.
Mix with other ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours in a tube pan.

title: vietnam cookies
directions: Mix oleo, sugar and Pet milk together.
Cook slow for 8 to 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls.
The older they get the better they get.

title: reese's bars
directions: Mix peanut butter, brown sugar, butter and vanilla until smooth.
Add confectioners sugar, a little at a time (you may not need a full pound of sugar), until smooth and spreadable.
Spread in a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt together chocolate chips and butter over hot, but not boiling, water.
Spread over peanut butter mixture. Let set.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: fried potatoes
directions: In a large iron skillet, melt the butter. Add a layer of sliced potatoes, onions and bell pepper. Repeat layers until all vegetables are in the skillet. Add water. Cover and cook over medium heat for 35 minutes. To serve, drain off any liquid or fat; turn out onto a platter and garnish with paprika and bacon, if desired. Yield: 8 servings.

title: swiss steak
directions: Flour, salt and pepper	pieces	of
steak
and brown in cooking oil.
Then pour in the rest of the ingredients.
Cover and cook slow until steak is done.
Pour over rice.

title: swiss steak
directions: Trim excess fat from meat.
Cut into serving pieces.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Place meat on a wooden chopping block. Sprinkle flour mixture on meat.
Pound meat with a mallet.
Turn meat and repeat on other side.
Brown meat in fat in skillet on both sides.
Add onions, tomatoes and garlic.
Cover and simmer over low heat.
Add green pepper and cook 20 minutes.
Skim off fat.
Thicken juice if necessary.
Serves 6.

title: schrafft's hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt butter, chocolate and sugar over hot water.
Add rest of ingredients.
Let cook 2 hours.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla before serving.
Makes 1 pint.
Keep refrigerated.
Easy to reheat in microwave.

title: kahlua
directions: In heavy saucepan, mix together sugar and water. Bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes. Add instant coffee. Cut up vanilla bean and add to liquid.
When cool, add vodka. Age for 30 days. Strain and serve over ice.

title: angel hash
directions: Mix all ingredients well and fold in Cool Whip.
Chill overnight.

title: cherry dream cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cream shortening, milk, lemon and almond extract and egg whites.
Mix dry ingredients and moist ingredients together, scraping bowl and beating after each addition.
Stir in maraschino cherries last. Makes 2 layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Put shortening in a warm place until set.
Set oven at 375°. Sift flour onto paper and measure 1 1/2 cups.
Add soda and salt and sift again.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Greased cookie sheet.

title: texas caviar
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Marinate a minimum of 2 hours.
Drain and serve.

title: carolina raw apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in the order listed and mix well. Bake in loaf pan at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown onion with hamburger.
Mix all ingredients together and simmer 1 hour.
Serve with grated Longhorn or Colby cheese, sour cream and tortilla chips.

title: tender steaks
directions: Flour both sides of meat.
Brown quickly in hot oil.
Mix soup and water.
Pour over meat.
Top with onion.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Makes tender steaks and delicious gravy.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour can crushed pineapple in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Crumble yellow cake mix on top of pineapple.
Place sliced butter on top. Sprinkle nuts over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 55 minutes.

title: date-nut cake
directions: Mix ingredients well and spoon into a lecithin-oiled loaf or Bundt pan.
Bake in moderate oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool before removing from pan.
Delicious topped with lemon sauce.

title: jean's mother's day melange
directions: Place pineapple chunks and juice in large glass serving bowl. Add drained mandarin oranges and pudding; mix thoroughly.
Place in refrigerator to set, about 20 minutes.
Layer with bananas, blueberries and strawberries.
Top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with strawberry slices.

title: million dollar rice salad
directions: Combine marshmallows and pineapple.
Cream the cream cheese with sugar and mayonnaise until smooth.
Add rice and cherries to the marshmallow mixture.
Fold in whipped cream and nuts.
Chill.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix jello with	1
1/2	cups
hot water and let thicken slightly.

title: auntie "m"'s punch bowl cake
directions: First bake the cakes and cool.

In a punch bowl, break one of the cakes into chunks, then put a layer of pudding (one box), then break up 2 candy bars and 1 cup of nuts on top of the pudding. Next, layer 3/4 of a can of cherries, then a layer of Cool Whip. Then start all over with the other cake.
Finish with Cool Whip, cherries and nuts.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cut up fruit.
Put in bowl.
Cook first 5 ingredients.
Cool and then fold in Cool Whip.
Pour over fruit.

title: grandma's banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Grease or Pam 2
9 X 5 loaf pans.
Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until light and thick.
Fold in mashed bananas.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir into mixture.
Add pecans.
Pour batter into loaf pans.
Bake about 40-45 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Cool slightly, remove from pans and cool completely on a rack.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat the eggs until lemon colored.
Slowly stir in the melted butter.
Sift together the flour and sugar.
Add this gradually to the egg mixture, beating well after each addition.
Add the buttermilk and vanilla.
Stir well.
Pour into the pie crust and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy crunchies
directions: Melt chips together; mix well.
Remove from heat.
Stir in noodles and cashews.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Let set and store.
Makes about 4 dozen crunchies.

title: fruit salad
directions: Slice bananas 1/2-inch thick.
Pour lemon juice over and stir. Drain all fruit. Save 1 cup juice.
Follow pudding instructions and substitute the 1 cup fruit juice for milk.
Pour pudding mix over fruit and mix well. Cover and keep refrigerated.
Will keep for days in refrigerator.

title: fruitcake balls
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk with raisins, cherries, coconut and nuts. Roll into balls and chill.
These are pretty in baking cups.

title: split pea soup
directions: If you have a ham bone, this also may be added.
Put split peas with ham bone and vegetables in large pan of water.
Cook until peas are soft.

title: basil bean salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine beans, green pepper and onion. In a small bowl, combine vinegar, oil, sugar, basil, mustard and salt. Pour over bean mixture; toss to coat. Chill for several hours or overnight. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: candied yams
directions: Wash potatoes and boil in their skins, covered for 10 minutes or until nearly tender.
Make up a syrup with remaining ingredients and cook in a small saucepan over high heat until the syrup coats a spoon, about 3 minutes.
Preheat oven to 375°.
When potatoes are cool enough to handle, peel and cut lengthwise.
Lay in buttered baking dish.
Pour hot syrup over potatoes and bake uncovered for 30 to 40 minutes.
Baste during baking.
Serves 4.

title: mexican stuffed shells
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Combine Ortega sauce, water and tomato sauce.
Stir 1/2 cup mixture into chillies (if used).
Mix in 1 cup cheese and 1/2 can of onions.
Mix well.

title: mamie's favorite fudge
directions: Combine milk, butter, sugar and salt. Bring to a boil, vigorously boil. Stir constantly to prevent sticking.
Reduce heat and simmer 6 minutes.
Put remaining ingredients in a large bowl except nuts.
Pour boiling mixture over chocolate and marshmallow cream and beat until chocolate is melted. Stir in nuts.
Pour into buttered pans.
Let stand a few hours before cutting. Store in metal container.

title: crispy parmesan chicken
directions: Combine melted butter and garlic powder in bowl.
Put bread crumbs, cheese and parsley in another bowl.
Roll chicken in butter, then in crumbs.
Place in baking dish.
Microwave on High for 18 to 22 minutes.
Rotate 1/2 turn after 10 minutes.
Or, bake at 350° until chicken is done.

title: crock-pot brunswick stew
directions: Mix all of the listed ingredients in a crock-pot.
Cook on low for at least 4 hours.

title: tomato relish
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, salt and red pepper.
Heat until all is dissolved.
Add tomatoes and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add last 4 ingredients and simmer for 5 minutes.
Pack loosely in jars and cover with boiling juice and seal with hot lids.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except broccoli.
Cook broccoli; drain.
Add to mixture.
Bake in casserole dish 45 minutes at 325°.

title: brownie drop cookies
directions: Melt the chocolate and butter in double boiler or microwave. Beat eggs and sugar until thick.
Blend egg mixture and melted chocolate.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: corn to freeze
directions: Cook 5 to 7 minutes, then cool quick and freeze.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Mix beans, 1/2 cup grated cheese, chicken soup and 1/2 can enchilada sauce.
Stir.
Grease casserole.
Alternate layers of tortilla, meat, cheese and sauce, ending with cheese and sauce.
Cook at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: "turkish pizza"
directions: In a small bowl, mix cheese, mayonnaise, scallions, curry, salt and olives.
Spread mixture on split English muffin halves. Cut into bite size pieces.
Spread out onto a baking sheet and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: smoked duck
directions: Soak ducks in brine solution (Morton Tender Quick) for 24 to 48

title: mexican chicken soup
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small bowl; stir well.
Heat oil in a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat.
Add cumin mixture, chicken, onion and garlic; saute 5 minutes.
Add broth and next 6 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Ladle into soup bowls; top with cheese.
Yields 15 cups.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown diced bacon and ground beef; drain well.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Place 2 layers of Rich's yeast rolls in generously greased Bundt pan.
Bring to boil next 5 ingredients.
Pour over yeast rolls.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Let rise overnight in refrigerator. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Brown chuck roast in hot fat.
Mix remaining ingredients for sauce.
Cover roast with sauce.
Cover and bake at 325° for 3 to 4 hours or until tender.
Pull meat apart in slivers and return to sauce.
Serve over hamburger buns.

title: red rice
directions: Cook bacon and saute onion.
Combine the rest of ingredients. Pour into a 1-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: play dough
directions: Place all ingredients in medium size saucepan.
Mix with wire whisk.
Place over medium-low heat and cook, stirring occasionally, until consistency of mashed potatoes.
Do not boil. Knead until cool.
Dust with flour if dough is sticky.
Add water if stiff.
Store in airtight container.
Have fun!!

title: granola bars
directions: Line an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan with foil.
Grease the foil; set aside.
Combine granola, oats, nuts, flour and raisins; mix well.
Stir in the egg, honey, oil, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Mix well and press evenly into the lined and greased baking pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown.
Cut into bars.
Makes 24 bars.

title: snickers style dessert bars
directions: Let ice cream and whipped topping soften at room temperature about 10 minutes.
In a bowl with electric beater, whip together ice cream, whipped topping, peanut butter and dry pudding until smooth, about 5 minutes.
Freeze in 8 x 8-inch square dish until solid, about 2 hours; cut into 8 servings.

title: apricot slush
directions: Cook sugar and 7 cups water until dissolved, then steep tea bags in the 2 cups boiling water.
Add the mixtures together and mix in the frozen orange juice, lemonade and brandy.
Stir until dissolved.
Freeze in containers.
Scoop out and fill small glasses 3/4 full.
Pour over 7-Up or Sprite.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar, salt, cinnamon, eggs and milk.
Sift together flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix the two groups of ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoon and flatten with glass bottom dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Grease pie plate, 1 1/2 x 10-inches.
Cook and stir beef and onion in 10-inch skillet until brown; drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread in pie plate.
Beat baking mix, milk and eggs with wire whisk or hand beater until almost smooth.
Pour into pie pan. Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Bake until knife in center comes out clean.
Bake 5 minutes; top with lettuce and pickles.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: quick easy banana pudding
directions: Make your pudding.
Cut your bananas up and soak them in orange juice, then drain.
Mix your bananas, pudding, Eagle Brand milk, Cool Whip and vanilla wafers (save some vanilla wafers to top the dish with).
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Melt chocolate chips in double boiler.
Beat eggs until fluffy.
Dissolve gelatine in cold water and add to beaten eggs. Add vanilla, salt and melted chocolate.
Fold in 1 carton of Cool Whip.
Slice cake in thin slices.
Line a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan with 1/2 the slices.
Pour half of chocolate mix and half the pecans over cake.
Repeat layer of cake, chocolate mix and pecans. Chill until firm.
Remove and spread Cool Whip on top.
Top with drizzled syrup and cherries.
Chill and serve.
It can be made day before.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, margarine and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift powder and flour together.
Add this to cream mixture with milk (1/2 flour, then milk).
Add remaining flour and vanilla.
Stir in crushed pineapple and juice; blend well.
Use greased 10-inch tube pan. Cook at 325° for 1 1/2 hours until cake springs back.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until browned.
Remove from oven.
Immediately pour 1 cup chocolate chips on cookies.
Let set 5 minutes.
Spread chocolate over cookies.
Pour Peanut Butter Glaze over top and swirl around.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburg, onion, celery and green pepper for 10 minutes in a large kettle.
Add the rest of ingredients and simmer for 2 hours.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Put all ingredients together before beating.
Do not stir until all have been added.
Bake in loaf pan or cake pans in 350° oven about one hour.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Make sure potatoes are completely thawed.

title: russian chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and trim off any loose fat.
Pat dry and set aside in shallow dish.
Combine dressing, apricot preserves and onion soup mix.
Pour over chicken.
Marinate in refrigerator for 2 hours or overnight. Bake, uncovered, in a 300° oven until tender (2 hours).

title: potluck casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Place in a greased casserole and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
It is more flavorful if baked and refrigerated the day before served.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well. Roll into small balls.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: faye's chocolate pie filling
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Combine milk and egg yolks.
Add this slowly to dry ingredients.
Cook over medium-low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Boil sugar and Karo.
Add peanut butter and Rice Krispies. Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt together chocolate chips and butterscotch chips and spread on top.
This is a family favorite.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and place in well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: homemade wine
directions: You will need 1-gallon glass jar.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Blend pumpkin, eggs, and oil in mixing bowl.
Blend all the dry ingredients together and fold into the pumpkin mixture.
Pour into well greased square pan and bake at 350 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool to room temperature.

title: baby limas and sausage
directions: Pick and wash beans.
Cover with water and bring to a boil. Turn off heat and let stand 1 hour.
Add chopped onions, bacon and salt.
Cover and cook until tender, adding water, if needed.

title: fresh cucumber salad
directions: Wash cucumber, score with tines of fork (all around and length); slice thinly.
Mix rest of ingredients and add to cucumber.
Press slices with back of spoon to make crisp and delicious.
Always make this fresh.
Don't re-use vinegar mixture.

title: florence's roast beef
directions: Line roasting pan with foil.
Place rack on top (if rack is not like a cooling rack, cover it also with foil and cut appropriate slits).
Completely cover roast with Ah So sauce. Place on roasting rack. Put in oven.
Roast at 425° for 1 hour. Also roast baking potatoes and acorn squash for a complete dinner. Do not overcook.
Roast will be medium to medium rare.
Do not increase cooking time for larger roast or decrease for smaller roast; 1 hour only cooking time.

title: sunshine salad
directions: In a small bowl combine gelatins and water; stir until gelatins are dissolved.
Combine pineapple and bananas with gelatin.
Top with marshmallows and chill until set.

title: marinated beef or venison(sauerbraten)
directions: Place roast into a large 3 to 4- quart bowl; set aside. Combine in saucepan and heat to boiling the vinegar, water and spices.
Pour hot mixture over meat; allow to cool.
Add lemon. Cover and set in refrigerator.
Marinate for 4 days, turning meat once each day.
Remove meat from marinade; drain thoroughly. Strain and reserve marinade.

title: vegetable surprise
directions: Thaw vegetables, broccoli and cauliflower and spread in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with a stick of melted margarine, Velveeta cheese and Hi Ho cracker crumbs.
Drizzle another stick of melted margarine over top of crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt Hershey bars in microwave or on top of double boiler. Stir into Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell and refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: french toast
directions: Beat together first 4 ingredients. Dip bread in mixture and brown on each side in hot griddle.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Put grated cheese on top. Then onion rings on top of cheese.
Cook at 350° 30 to 40 minutes until vegetables are tender.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in an unbaked pie shell for 35 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: jalapeno potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes 5 minutes; drain.
Combine all ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into deep dish to avoid bubbling over.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: munching onion dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and salad dressing, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill.

title: pie crust
directions: Put into large Tupperware bowl.
Do not burp bowl.
Shake until you hear a thump.
If need be, stir pie crust into round ball.

title: alice's corn bread
directions: Mix together and have moist corn bread.
Bake at 350°.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter generously an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Melt butter and chocolate.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: homemade bread
directions: Put yeast in lukewarm water with 2 teaspoons sugar; stir good. Let set while milk is scalding.
Add lard to milk to melt while scalding milk.
Add to sugar and salt; stir.
Add enough cold water to make lukewarm.
Add yeast and stir until yeast is well dissolved, then add flour, a few cups at a time.
Knead down.
Put in bowl with a little oil rubbed to bottom of bowl.
Also rub oil on top of dough.
Let rise until double.
Cut out into loaves and shape.
Put in bread tins.
Let rise until doubled in size.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Butter loaves after removed from oven.

title: jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Add raisins to water and boil for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Cream shortening, then add sugar.
Add beaten eggs, vanilla, raisins with water mixture and nuts.
Add dry ingredients to raisin mixture.
Drop by full teaspoon on greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 60 cookies.

title: polynesian shrimp
directions: Thaw shrimp, if frozen.
In saucepan, cook carrots in small amount of boiling salted water 5 to 7 minutes or until just tender; drain well.
Blend 2/3 cup cold water into cornstarch; stir in pineapple juice, soy sauce and chicken bouillon granules.
Set aside.
Preheat wok or large skillet over high heat; add oil. Stir-fry ginger root and garlic in hot oil for 30 seconds.
Add the carrots, pea pods and green onions; stir-fry 1 minute or until heated thoroughly.
Remove the vegetables.
Stir-fry the shrimp in hot oil 7 to 8 minutes or until shrimp are done.
Push shrimp away from center of wok or skillet.
Stir the soy mixture and add to center of the wok or skillet.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in vegetables; cover and cook 1 minute.
Serve shrimp mixture at once with hot cooked rice.
If desired, sprinkle rice with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo; add eggs and buttermilk.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add boiling water and mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: flan de pescado(fish flan salad - cuban cookery)
directions: Put the gelatin in the water, heat the soup (without any water added) and dissolve the gelatin there.
Add the rest of the ingredients, and pour them into an oil-greased mold.
Refrigerate until hard, take out of the mold and serve over lettuce leaves. Decorate with red pimentos, small sweet peas and olives.
Makes 12 servings.
Good for buffets and can be also used as a spreader.

title: almost red lobster cheese biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick, water and cheese.
Place by the tablespoonful onto baking sheet and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes until golden.
Melt butter and mix with spices.
Brush onto biscuits and serve.
Yields 12 servings.

title: makes its own crust coconut pie
directions: Melt butter and mix in sugar.
Add eggs, then add in all the remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Pour into two (8-inch) greased pie pans.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, approximately 35 minutes.

title: jeanne's chocolate chippers(makes 4 dozen cookies)
directions: In the large bowl of an electric mixer, cream the butter and brown sugar until smooth.
Add the egg and vanilla and beat well. Stir in the dates and let the mixture set 5 minutes to soften the dates.
Then beat at high speed for 3 minutes or until very light brown and creamy.
Combine the flour, baking soda, salt and baking powder in a small bowl, breaking up any lumps.
Stir into creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir in the coconut, granola, walnuts and chocolate chips.
Drop the batter by tablespoons onto a lightly greased cookie sheet about 1 1/2-inches apart.
Bake in a 350° oven until lightly browned, about 10 to 15 minutes.
With a spatula, immediately remove cookies from cookie sheet and cool on a wire rack.
Store in an airtight container.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, salt, eggs, 3 tablespoons margarine and milk.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.

title: ricotta cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Pour into 11 x 15-inch greased and floured cake pan.
(Exact pan size is important!). Mix Ricotta cheese, 1/2 cup sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat very well until creamy.
Pour over unbaked cake mix batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix together and roll into small balls.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Salt and pepper meat.
Place beef in a roasting pan, uncovered.
Put in oven at 375° for 1 hour.
Turn off oven.
Do not open door!
Let set.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Combine sour cream and half and half.
Add to dry mix until moist.
Turn dough out and knead gently.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and mandarin oranges and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° until center comes out clean, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix rice, meat, salt and chili sauce.
Shape into balls of medium size.
Pour tomatoes over the top.
Cover.
Bake 60 to 80 minutes in 350° oven and see your little porcupines.
(This can also be made into a loaf.)

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: walnut fudge pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add flour, sugars and beat until well blended.
Blend in oleo.
Stir in nuts and chips.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 1 hour.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: coconut pompons
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter or margarine, sugar and vanilla, then add flour and salt.
(Can be refrigerated for easier handling.)
Shape dough around piece of nut or half a cherry to form 1-inch balls.
Roll in shredded coconut.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 18 minutes.

title: sherry's favorite swiss steak
directions: Heat oil in pan.
Cut steak into serving size pieces and lightly flour.
Lightly brown meat in hot oil and remove from pan; place on paper towels to absorb oil.
Add onion, pepper, garlic and celery to pan; fry until clear stirring to prevent sticking. Add sugar, tomato sauce, water and seasonings.
Cook stirring constantly for about 5 minutes.
Put steak in single layer in 9x13 pan, pour sauce over meat.
Add additional water if sauce does not completely cover all meat.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Serve over rice.

title: pork chops
directions: Slice onions.
Heat oil in frying pan over medium-high heat. Add chops and cook them until well browned, about 5 minutes per side.
Remove chops.
Reduce heat to low.
Add onions to pan drippings.
Cover and cook until the onions soften, about 10 minutes.
Add beer, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper, marjoram and pork chops.
Cover and cook about 1 hour until chops are tender.
Remove chops and keep warm.
Raise heat to high. Bring pan juices to a boil and continue boiling until slightly thickened, about 5 minutes.
Spoon onions and sauce over chops and serve.

title: vegetable sandwiches
directions: Chop all vegetables very fine.
Heat V-8 juice (a metal measuring cup works well).
Dissolve gelatin in juice.
Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate 24 to 48 hours (a must).
White bread makes the best sandwiches.

title: bread pudding
directions: Pour into buttered casserole; reserve 1/2 cup for sauce.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: harvest cranberry sauce
directions: Boil cranberries until they pop.
Add sugar and raisins.
Boil 10 minutes more.
Stir in nuts.
Add cinnamon sticks.
Remove and refrigerate.

title: strawberry glazed ham
directions: Trim skin from ham.
With sharp knife, score fat surface, making uniform diagonal cuts about 1/8-inch deep and 3/4-inch apart.
Place ham fat side up on a rack in a shallow roasting pan. Bake in 325° oven 1 3/4 to 2 1/2 hours.
Meanwhile in a small saucepan, combine fruit spread, mustard and lemon juice.
Cook over low heat, stirring until blended.
During last 20 minutes of baking time, brush ham with about 1/4 cup strawberry glaze.
Let ham stand 10 minutes for easier slicing.
Heat remaining glaze and serve as a sauce for the ham.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Place eggplant slices on a cookie sheet.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with salt.
Broil 6 inches from heat for 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Turn slices over and broil until brown.
Set aside.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook and drain vegetables.
Put in greased 2 quart flat casserole.	Mix onion, cheese and mayonnaise.
Spread over the vegetables.
Melt	 margarine
and
mix
with
the
crackers. Sprinkle over top.	Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream and Cheddar cheeses.
Add remaining ingredients. Chill.
Shape into ball and roll in finely chopped pecans.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat slowly.
Spoon off excess fat.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles in large amount of boiling salted water until tender.
Drain and rinse.
Combine remaining ingredients, except Mozzarella.

title: m&m party cookies(6 dozen)
directions: Blend shortening and brown and granulated sugars in a large bowl.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together; add to sugar-egg mixture, blending well.
Stir in 1/2 of candies (reserve remaining for decoration).
Drop from teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet; decorate tops with remaining candies.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove cookies with spatula to wire racks.
Cool completely.
After baking, some candies may be slightly cracked.
This adds texture and interest to cookies, still the same delightful flavor.

title: pizza butter
directions: Melt margarine; add rest of ingredients.
Mix well. Refrigerate up to a month.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat in large skillet.
Season with Greek seasoning. Cover with tight lid, turn heat down to low and cook until meat is very tender.
Cut pepper and onions; add to meat.
Cook until peppers and onions are done but not real soft.
Serve with baked potato, salad and hot rolls.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Preheat the oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar until light.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together the flour, salt and cocoa; stir into creamed mixture.
Add pecans, coconut and vanilla; beat well. Turn the batter into prepared pan, smooth the top.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Test with a wooden pick.
Remove from oven; sprinkle top with marshmallows.

title: five can casserole
directions: Mix together the soups, noodles, milk and chicken.
Place in a lightly greased casserole dish.
Top with potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pickled beets and eggs
directions: Heat vinegar and sugar.
Pour over beets.
When cool, put eggs, beets and mixture in a jar with a tight lid.
Be sure liquid covers eggs.
Best if made 24 hours before serving.
One tablespoon pickling spice may be added if desired.

title: cranberry butter
directions: Mix chopped cranberries with sugar and lemon peel in processor, using on/off turns. Add butter and blend until mixture is combined, but slightly chunky.

title: lemon pepper cabbage
directions: Spread oleo in the bottom of a 9x13-inch baking pan.
Cut up cabbage and place into the baking pan.
Bake covered at 350° until tender.
Season with lemon pepper.
Bake uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip kiss cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Remove wrapper from chocolate pieces. In a large bowl, beat butter, sugars and vanilla until well blended. Add flour; blend until smooth. Stir in small chocolate chips. Mold scant tablespoon dough around each chocolate piece, covering completely. Shape into balls; place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake mix in 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Combine pineapple and sugar; boil for 10 minutes and cool.
Pierce holes in cake.
Pour cooled mixture over top of cake; cool.
Prepare pudding mix and spread on top; chill.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: tighanites(fritters)
directions: Sift flour, baking powder
and	sugar.	Beat
egg
with milk; stir into flour mixture.
Heat
cups
oil
in a large frying pan.
When oil is hot, drop in batter from large spoon. Cook fritters until golden brown
on one side, then turn over. Drain on kitchen paper
towel.
Serve
at
once
with
sugar, cinnamon or honey and cinnamon.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chocolate chips and paraffin.
Roll into small balls the size of a walnut.
Place on cookie sheets lined with waxed paper.
Let stand until set in refrigerator.
Then melt chocolate and paraffin.
Dip candy in chocolate.
Cool on waxed paper.
Store in cool place.

title: peanut butter cup cakes
directions: Mix well until smooth.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: cream soup
directions: In large pan, heat onion, bouillon, water and salt to boiling. Reduce heat; cover and simmer about 10 minutes.
Add milk; stir in instant potatoes.
Beat until fluffy.
Gradually stir in 1 1/2 cups milk.
Heat to boiling.

title: fluffy pudding frosting
directions: Pour the cold milk into bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended, about 2 minutes.
Stir whipped topping into pudding very gently with rubber scraper until mixture is all the same color.
Place about a spoonful of frosting on each cupcake.
Spread frosting around top of cupcake with the back of teaspoon.
Sprinkle with candy decorations.
Put cupcakes into refrigerator to chill until serving time.
Store any leftover cupcakes in refrigerator.

title: italian baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in shallow baking dish that has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Spread mushrooms over chicken.
Pour spaghetti sauce evenly over chicken and mushrooms.
Bake uncovered 50 to 55 minutes.
Sprinkle dish with cheese.
Return to oven and bake until cheese melts.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut beef
across
grain
into
thin strips.
Combine soy sauce, garlic and
ginger;
add beef.
Toss and set aside while preparing vegetables.
Heat
oil
in
large frypan or wok.
Add beef and toss over high heat until brown; lower heat and simmer for 30 or 40 minutes, then turn heat up.
Add vegetables.
Toss vegetables until
tender
and
crisp,
about
minutes.
Mix cornstarch with water.
Add
to pan; stir and cook until thick. Add tomatoes and heat thoroughly.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve the jello and sugar in the hot water. Cool.
Mix the remaining ingredients except the sour cream in the cool jello. Blend in the sour cream. Let stand until jelled.

title: blueberry and banana pie
directions: Line regular or graham cracker crust with bananas.
Then add mixture of Cool Whip, cream cheese, sugar and blueberry pie filling.
Chill several hours before serving.
