title: foolproof dark chocolate fudge
directions: Melt chips and condensed milk over low heat with salt.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and walnuts.
Spread evenly into 8-inch square pan (paper lined).
Chill 2 hours, then cut into squares.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda in bowl.
Set aside.
Combine brown sugar, white sugar, softened butter and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Add eggs and beat.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 100 (2-inch) cookies.

title: pizza subs
directions: Split buns and lay out on counter.
Mix butter and garlic. Spread thin layer on each bun.
Place thin layer of ham on bottom of each sub, then Cheddar cheese, then pepperoni, then pizza sauce, mushrooms, olives and peppers.
Top with Mozzarella; close subs. Rub olive oil on outside of buns.
Wrap in foil individually.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, then pig out!

title: cranberry salad sweet and sour
directions: Dissolve gelatin in the boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce. Stir until completely mixed.
Add the orange juice and grated rind.
Chill until partially set.
Grate the apple.
Pare the grapefruit.
Remove all membrane and cut into small segments. Fold apples and the grapefruit sections into gelatin.
Turn into oiled one-quart mold.
Chill.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: banana nut bread #2
directions: Mix all this together, putting in bananas and nuts last. Divide into 2 loaf pans. Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: batter for fish and vegetables
directions: Place ingredients in mixing bowl and mix.
Dip fish or vegetables into batter and deep fry.

title: tortellini - vegetable appetizers
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a saucepan; gradually stir in water and vinegar.
Bring to boil; cook 30 seconds.
Let cool. Alternate tortellini, cherry tomatoes and artichokes on 24 (6-inch) skewers.
Lay in baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inches).
Pour cooled mixture over skewers.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator 4 hours, turning occasionally.
Drain and place on serving platter.

title: applesauce spice cake
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in large bowl; beat at medium speed until well blended.
Combine flour and the next 3 ingredients; stir well.
Add to applesauce mixture, stirring until well blended.
Pour batter into a Bundt pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes; remove from pan and cool completely on wire rack.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Bring to boil all ingredients and cook 1 minute.
You can add 2 tablespoons peanut butter, if desired.

title: peanut butter cookies(simple recipe, a child can make)
directions: Mix; drop by spoonful on greased baking pan.
Smash with fork. Bake at 350° for 12 to 16 minutes.

title: snack time molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg, molasses and dry ingredients.
Drop dough by level teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from baking sheets.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: chili sauce
directions: For a mild sauce, omit the red pepper.
Chop onions and peppers fine; prepare tomatoes as for canning and cook down.
When done, add other ingredients and put in jars; seal tight.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Put in jar with tight fitting lid.
Shake well until blended. Refrigerate.
Will keep for 1 week.

title: cream cheese quiche
directions: Beat cream cheese, cream, egg yolks, egg, salt and pepper together.
Arrange 1-inch slices of bacon at bottom of pan.
Pour cheese mixture over bacon.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 10 minutes longer or until puffed and golden brown.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Blend soup and milk together.
Stir in cheese and heat, stirring constantly until cheese melts.
Serve over vegetables. Yields 2 quarts.

title: orange delight
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Gently fold in whipped topping. Cover and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion until slightly brown; drain.
Mix all ingredients and put in a baking dish.
Bake 25 minutes in a 370° oven.

title: baked grits and cheese casserole
directions: Bring water to a boil in a large saucepan. Stir the grits in, stirring constantly, until completely mixed. Cook, stirring, until thickened.
Mix eggs, slightly and add a small amount of grits to the eggs, stirring constantly, to prevent overcooking eggs.
Add to grits. Add seasonings, cheese and butter, mixing well.
Pour mixture into a buttered 2-quart casserole and bake 45 minutes in a preheated oven at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: pudding cheesecake
directions: Stir cream cheese until very soft.
Gradually blend in 1/2 cup of milk until mixture is smooth.
Add remaining milk and the pudding mix.
Beat slowly until blended, about 1 minute. Immediately pour into crust.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: eggy veggie pies
directions: In a 6-inch skillet, cover bottom with oil and fry potatoes and onions until onions are soft and potatoes crusting.
Beat eggs in a small bowl.
Add pepper.
Pour over top of potatoes and onions and cook until top is set.
Slide onto plate and reverse into skillet again for mixture to set completely.
Serve with large green salad.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Combine Sourdough Starter, water, corn oil and sugar in bowl. Mix well. Stir in flour.
Brush surface with additional oil.
Let rise, loosely covered with waxed paper, for 8 hours to overnight.

title: grandma's cheatin' cobbler
directions: Use an 8-inch square pan or double recipe and use a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients in a pan.
Bring to rolling boil. Pour over the next 3 ingredients, stir and drop on waxed paper.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat 4 egg yolks and 1 egg white together until light colored and thick.
Add milk and beat thoroughly.
Add lime juice and rind and stir until mixture thickens.
Fold in remaining egg whites which have been beaten stiff.
Turn into baked pie shell.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Put on medium heat and cook until it starts to boil.
Remove from heat and cool for 1 minute.
Add vanilla, salt, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Stir well. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes and stir in mayonnaise.
Melt cheese and stir in.
Place in 8 x 12-inch baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Top with bacon bits.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana icing
directions: Mix all ingredients together; stir well.
Spread between layers.
It may be runny.
If so, place in refrigerator for a while before icing cake.
Keep cake in refrigerator.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Mix berries and 3/4 cup sugar with 1 cup water and cornstarch; boil for 1 minute.
Pour berries into baking dish; dot with butter and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Drop dough with spoon on top of fruit.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream raisin bars
directions: Combine oatmeal, sugar, flour and soda and add melted margarine.
Pat 2/3 of mix in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix well and form into balls.
Brown in 2 tablespoons oil in a heavy skillet.
Remove meat balls from pan and add 2 tablespoons flour to skillet; blend well.
Add 1 (10 1/2 ounce) can consomme or beef broth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Return meat balls to gravy.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Saute onion and ground beef together; drain, then add the tomato sauce or soup.
Add chili powder and salt.
Spread Tater Tots over top, then spread grated cheese over Tots.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: diet maple syrup(sugarless)
directions: Mix water, cornstarch and salt in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add maple flavoring and artificial sweetener.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add onion, pepper, both cans of soup, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Let simmer about 15 minutes.

title: doodle cake
directions: Mix together:
sugar, flour, soda, eggs and crushed pineapple.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Boil milnot, butter and sugar for 3 minutes.
Add nuts and coconut.
Pour on cake while hot.

title: reese's cup candy
directions: Mix together margarine, peanut butter, vanilla, confectioners sugar and graham cracker crumbs and make into balls.

title: radish dip
directions: Place all ingredients in food processor and blend. Refrigerate.
Great with relish tray and veggies.

title: iona's buttermilk pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, eggs and butter, mixing well.
Add buttermilk, vanilla and food coloring.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 1 hour or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: pineapple-plus cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine peanut butter, milk, sugar and cream cheese.
Beat until well blended.
Add Cool Whip, folded in.
Pour into pie shell and freeze at least 2 hours.

title: carrot-raisin salad
directions: Toss carrots and raisins together; blend remaining ingredients together to make dressing.
Mix with carrots and raisins. Refrigerate for 30 minutes.

title: pickled beets
directions: Keep mixing and adding until the amount covers beets in pot. May add pickling spice.
Bring to boil, put in jars and seal.

title: mississippi rice
directions: Mix all above in covered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy barbecue chicken
directions: Place chicken in pan; salt and pepper to taste.
Pour ketchup and Pepsi over chicken.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mini pita pizzas
directions: Cut pita bread in quarters.
Brush with Pizza Quick sauce or Italian dressing.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Add a dash of Italian seasoning and garlic powder.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. (Can be served as an hors d'oeuvre or a snack.)

title: bran-oatmeal muffin mix
directions: Pour boiling water over bran; set aside.
Mix together rest of ingredients.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, buttermilk, flour, baking soda and salt.
Add water bran mixture to oatmeal mixture.
Bake at 375° in muffin pan, 20 to 25 minutes.
Will keep in refrigerator in airtight container for 3 months.
Yields 8 dozen medium muffins.

title: mallow sweet potatoes
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup marshmallows to sprinkle on top and broil lightly.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Spoon into 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill until set.
Frost top with Cool Whip.

title: mini-cheese cake(great for parties or cookouts)
directions: Line muffin tin.
Place one vanilla wafer in each liner.
Mix cream cheese, vanilla and sugar until well blended.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Pour over wafers to 3/4 full.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°. Remove when cool.
Top with whipped nondairy topping, chocolate, nuts or any fruit pie filling.

title: a good casserole dish
directions: Cook 1 cup of rice.
Brown meat in butter or shortening with onion, cut fine.
When done, add catsup, barbecue sauce and Worcestershire sauce. Add eggs and sage. Mix thoroughly with rice. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Place in a buttered casserole dish and dot with butter.
Bake for about 20 minutes in oven at 400°.
This dish may be made with leftover rice and leftover meat.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: Boil rice with slightly less water.
Beat eggs, adding salt. When oil starts to smoke, add eggs and scramble into 2 tablespoons and put them on a plate.

title: oyster gumbo
directions: In a heavy pan, make a roux with shortening and flour.
When quite brown, add chopped onion and parsley.
Cook slowly until onion is well browned and very soft.
Add bay leaf, thyme and hot oyster liquor, then add hot water.
Simmer about 15 minutes.
Add drained oysters and continue cooking 5 minutes more.
Remove from heat and gradually stir in 2 tablespoons file.
Serve immediately over cooked rice in soup bowl.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cranberry mold salad
directions: Dissolve gelatine in hot water.
Add sugar, lemon and pineapple juice.
Set partially.
Add remaining ingredients. Chill in oiled pan until set.
Should be made a day or two before serving.
May be kept (refrigerated) for several weeks.

title: christmas bread
directions: Let rise 3/4 hour.
Knead down 3 times.
Put into bread pans. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
This is a very large batch.
I only make half.

title: strawberry punch bowl cake
directions: Make cake in 2 round pans and set aside to cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Stir all ingredients together in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture, alternately with milk.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: tofu patties
directions: Saute onion and celery in oil.
Add cubed tofu to pan, then rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Form into patties (add more bread crumbs if too wet).
Bake on Pam-sprayed (patties stick if not careful) cookie sheet at 375° for about 40 minutes.
Place in casserole dish and cover with mushroom soup gravy or ladle over as served.

title: chocolate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a spoon.
Spoon heaping tablespoonfuls (walnut size) on sprayed cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: english tea cakes
directions: Mix together thoroughly: shortening, sugar, egg and milk. Sift together and stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix in citron and currants or raisins.
Chill dough.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Dip tops in slightly beaten egg white, then sugar.
Place sugar-side up, 2-inches apart, on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until delicately browned.
The balls flatten some in baking and become glazed.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes about 3 dozen, 1 1/2-inch cookies.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half lengthwise; remove seeds and white part. Sprinkle with salt.
Combine beef, crumbs, salt, eggs, onion and pepper.
Fill cavities of peppers with meat mixture.
Place in roasting pan; pour oil in pan.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes to brown.
Dilute tomato sauce with water in saucepan; heat on top of stove.
Pour over browned peppers.
Bake 45 minutes longer. Baste several times with sauce.
Serves 12.

title: strawberry rhubarb pie
directions: Stew rhubarb and 3/4 cup sugar.
Mix up rest of ingredients and add to rhubarb mixture.
Put in pie shell and bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Turn down oven; bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Stir well.
Heat until becomes thickened.
Remove from heat and place in baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Place in 350° oven until meringue is golden brown.

title: depression days soup
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add butter, salt, pepper and parsley. In another pot, cook pasta until tender.
Add drained pasta to water mixture.
Bring to boil again.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix margarine, cocoa and milk.
Boil 1 minute.
Add peanut butter, vanilla, oats and nuts (if using nuts).
Mix and drop from spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: grandma faye's turkey dressing
directions: Mix corn bread and broken bread or biscuits.
Add enough broth to get it to desired consistency.
(This should be very watery as it will thicken as it cooks).
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add pieces of turkey or chicken.
Bake uncovered in a 350° oven until sides are slightly brown and dressing seems set.
(Grandma would usually buy a hen and cook it for the broth and meat if she baked her turkey in a bag, usually using the turkey broth for the giblet gravy.)

title: miracle cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add lemon juice and cool.
Cream together cheese and sugar.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Mix with jello.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Crush graham crackers.
Add melted margarine to make a crust.
Pour in cake mixture.
Chill 3 hours or until firm.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix and place in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: western salad
directions: Mix chopped avocados, pinto beans, chopped green onions, diced tomatoes and dressing together.
Place in bowl as bottom layer.
Top with lettuce and finish with a layer of corn chips.

title: snickers salad
directions: Cut Snicker bars into little pieces in a large bowl.
Peel and core apples.
Cut into small chunks.
Peel and slice bananas.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix well and cool.

title: chili-roni
directions: Saute ground beef with onion and garlic; drain.
Return to pan; add tomatoes, tomato sauce and spices.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Cook noodles as directed and drain.
Combine with meat sauce and serve.
Serves 6.

title: tater tots and hamburger casserole
directions: You will also need a 9 x 9-inch casserole dish.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook and bone chicken. Set aside.
Mix cream of chicken soup with broth. Add water, if needed. Add salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil, then turn heat down.
Mix flour and water together to make a dough.
Roll and cut in small strips.
Put in broth, a few at a time. Turn on low heat and cook until done. Add chicken.
If too dry, add a little hot water.

title: everyday meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, combine the eggs and milk. Stir in bread crumbs, onion, parsley, salt, sage and pepper. Add ground beef.
Thoroughly mix meat and seasonings. Firmly pat meat into baking pan. Glaze with the last 3 ingredients, blended well. Carefully spread over top. Bake about 50 minutes or until done.

title: spaghetti with clam sauce (white)
directions: Drain clams and save juice; set aside.
In skillet, slowly heat oil and butter.
Add garlic and saute until golden.
Remove from heat.
Stir in clam liquid, parsley and salt and bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer uncovered for 10 minutes.
Add clams; simmer for 3 minutes.
Serve hot over hot spaghetti with Parmesan cheese. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: bacon wraps(microwave)
directions: Cut bacon
and water chestnuts in half.
Roll chestnuts up in bacon; fasten with toothpick and marinate in soy sauce. Put soy sauce (about 1/2-inch) and chestnuts in glass rectangle dish. Cover
with
Saran	Wrap.
Microwave
for
10 to 15 minutes on High.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat dry cake mix, eggs and oil.
(Batter will be very stiff.)
Stir in coconut, chips and nuts.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until a slight indentation remains when lightly touched.
Cool for 2 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Cook on High for 2 minutes the powdered sugar, butter, cocoa and milk.
Stir after 1 minute.
Add vanilla and stir.
Drop by teaspoon in bonbon cups.
Top with pecan half. Makes 40 miniature bonbons.

title: wine pot roast
directions: Brown meat over low heat in a small amount of hot oil. Sprinkle with salt.
Combine vinegar, oil, catsup, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce, garlic and mustard.
Pour over meat, put the lid on and cook for 2 hours.
When done, spoon sauce over meat.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Saute onions in fat until yellow.
Pull pan aside and stir in paprika and red pepper.
Add chicken, washed but not dried, and 1/4 cup water.
Season and simmer until liquid evaporates. Sprinkle flour over chicken and stir constantly to brown flour. Add warm water and cook, covered, slowly until done, about 1 1/2 hours.
Add sour cream during last 5 minutes.
Keep heat low so cream won't curdle.
(One tablespoon of flour may be mixed with the cream.
Serve with egg dumplings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook each package of vegetables separately.
Cut cheeses into small cubes.
In a small skillet, melt butter.
Add soup and milk and blend until smooth.
(Do not boil.)
In a glass baking dish (9 x 13-inch) layer: 1 package of vegetables, 1/2 of the Monterey Jack cubes, 1/2 of the sharp Cheddar cheese cubes, 1/2 of the croutons and 1/2 of the soup mixture.
Repeat the layering once more.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: raspberry dessert salad
directions: Combine butter, sugar and pretzels in a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and egg, folding Cool Whip into mix last.
Carefully spread over pretzel layer.
Dissolve jello and water.
Add frozen raspberries.
Cool until slightly thickened.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Chill overnight.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape in loaf and put in pan. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pineapple turnover
directions: Unfold pastry crust and place on a baking sheet.
Combine the other ingredients in a bowl until thoroughly mixed.
Spoon filling onto half of pastry crust, leaving a 1 inch margin around the edge.
Fold other half of crust over filling and seal the edges with your fingers or fork.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Boil the potatoes and mash as if making mashed potatoes.
Use small amount of milk.
Using an electric mixer, mix all ingredients together.
Put into a casserole dish and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until heated through and the top is browned.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump mixture of cherries and pineapple into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with dry yellow cake mix.
Slice stick of butter into thin slices and place evenly on top of dry cake mix.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: ham and cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients together with half of chopped ham. Roll into ball with remaining chopped Ham.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Generously grease bottom only of 13 x 9-inch pan.

Remove 1/2 cup dry cake mix; reserve. Beat remaining dry cake mix, butter, eggs and sour cream in large bowl. Spread half the batter in pan. Stir together reserved dry cake mix, brown sugar, pecans and cinnamon; sprinkle over batter in pan. Carefully spread remaining batter evenly over pecan mixture. Bake 30 to 33 minutes or until deep golden brown.

title: fresh blueberry cream pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Beat 5 minutes at medium speed. Fold in blueberries.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Combine flour, butter and pecans.
Sprinkle over top. Bake 10 minutes more.
Chill.

title: sinfully chocolate cake
directions: Boil the margarine, water and cocoa for 2 minutes.
Mix the flour,
sugar
and baking soda in a bowl.
Add the buttermilk, eggs
and
vanilla
to
the flour mixture.
Then add the chocolate and
margarine
mixture.
Grease
and
flour
a
9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: sugar carrots
directions: Peel and slice carrots.
Cook until tender and drain.
Put in a medium-size dish.
In microwave-safe bowl, combine butter, brown sugar and mustard.
Microwave on High for 1 minute or until butter and sugar are melted.
Stir well.
Pour over carrots.
Can be reheated when ready to serve.

title: rice salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Chill overnight in covered dish.
To serve, stir lightly and place in single bowls on lettuce leaf.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar and pat into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake in 400° oven for 8 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Mix cream cheese and 1 cup sugar together until sugar is melted.
Fold in Cool Whip.
When pretzel crust has cooled, spread cream cheese mixture over top.
Mix jello and water together.
Add strawberries (frozen).
Let set in refrigerator for 10 minutes.
Spread over cream cheese mixture. Refrigerate overnight.

title: papaya cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into two medium loaf pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pizza
directions: Tack a apple. Put a stick in some wer.
Get some soger from some wer.
Put in a big bolw.
Put some weter in with it.
Bol the soger and weter.
Now dip the apple in the bolw.
Take it out of the bolw.
Put it in the ferig.
Lat it sat in the ferig for 3 1/2 days.
But put some fowol on it.
Then you can eat it.

title: grilled cheese sandwich pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a small mixing bowl, combine egg, flour, salt, pepper and half of milk; beat until smooth.
Add remaining milk; beat until well blended.
Stir in 1/2 of cheese; pour into a well-greased 8-inch pie pan.
Bake for 30 minutes. Sprinkle remaining cheese over top and bake just until cheese is melted (about 2 minutes).
Makes approximately 24 appetizer servings.

title: mountain slaw
directions: Chop first 4 ingredients together.
Bring remaining ingredients to boil.
Let cool completely and pour over cabbage. Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage
and
boil for 5 minutes.
Drain and put in buttered dish;
mix
soup, milk and 1/2 cup cheese.
Pour over cabbage.
Add
cracker
crumbs with the rest of the cheese and mix well.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: three layer dinner(amish)
directions: Brown hamburger, then season with salt and pepper.
Mix in ketchup; set aside.
Shred 1/2 head of raw cabbage into baking dish.
Add half of raw diced potatoes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add all of hamburger mixture.
Cover with slices of cheese.
Shred remaining cabbage and sprinkle over cheese.
Add remaining raw potatoes.
Pour 1 1/2 cups milk over all.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy oven chicken
directions: Mix in paper bag the flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Shake. Pat chicken dry.
Put 2 to 3 pieces in bag and shake with flour mixture until all chicken is floured.
Lay in single layer in oblong pan.
Melt shortening and drizzle over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until tender.

title: cake that won't last
directions: Mix flour, sugar, soda, salt and cinnamon in large bowl.
Make well in dry ingredients and add eggs, oil, pineapple, nuts and vanilla.
Stir, but do not beat.
Pour into greased Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Chop shrimp.
Combine all items and mix well.
Shape into a ball and sprinkle.

title: pea casserole
directions: Drain peas and heat with margarine until margarine is melted. Mix in medium casserole dish with soup, pimento, cheese, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Salt and pepper to taste. Crumble crackers on top of casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix melted butter and corn flakes.
Sprinkle over hash brown mixture.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: judy's vegetable soup
directions: Cook stew beef, tomato juice, tomatoes, bouillon cubes, seasonings, and some water together for 1/2 to 1 hour.
Add carrots, celery and cabbage first and cook for 15 minutes, then add all other vegetables except potatoes, rice and macaroni.
Cook until done.
Then add potatoes, rice and macaroni and cook until done.
(Watch the rice and macaroni; they will stick to the bottom.)

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt margarine in pan to be used (8-inch square pan). In order listed, layer first 4 ingredients.
Pour condensed milk over all. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: garlic snack pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together dry pack of Hidden Valley Ranch dressing and oil.
Add garlic powder and stir well.
Break into bite size pieces the pretzels.
Add pretzels to mixture. Stir well to coat.
Let sit in mixture for 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes on cookie sheet.
Turn pretzels with spatula and bake 7 to 8 minutes more.

title: turnip kraut
directions: Fill glass jar to 1/2 inch from the brim with turnips and water, to which salt has been added.
Screw top of jar down hard, then make a slight turn back.
Mixture will start working in 3 to 4 days.
Keep in a cool place 6 weeks before using.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Combine oil, eggs, flour and other ingredients, except zucchini and nuts.
Mix well.
Then add zucchini and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake one hour at 325°.

title: smoked turkey casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken in 1 tablespoon of butter.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
When chicken is finished boiling, place stuffing evenly in a square pan.
Cover evenly with chicken.
Repeat with broccoli.
Then in mixing bowl, mix together both soups and 2 cans water.
After mixing thoroughly, pour over broccoli.
Spread cheese evenly over mixture.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake for 1 hour.
Remove from oven.
Stir.
Re-cover with foil and bake for 1 additional hour.

title: linguini salad
directions: Cut cucumbers, tomatoes and green onions into small pieces. Mix everything together in a large bowl.
Refrigerate.
Ready to eat.
Makes 24 servings.

title: c and m poppy seed chicken
directions: In casserole dish, put chicken on bottom, then combine soups and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Crumble Ritz crackers and sprinkle over soups.
Pour melted butter over crackers.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peggys meat loaf
directions: Mix all of the above together well.
Put in an ungreased loaf pan; bake at 350° for 1-1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: grandma's pecan pie
directions: Mix as listed.
Mix well, but by hand.
Pour into 9-inch prepared, unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°, then reduce to 325° and bake for 35 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Mix beans and hamburger. Then add 1 cup ketchup and 2 tablespoons mustard.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: scalloped salmon
directions: Combine ingredients and bake uncovered in 9 inch pie shell at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: toll house pan cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and brown sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Mix flour, soda and salt together and add slowly to mixture.
Add chips.
Spread in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan and bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: mexican salad
directions: Layer all ingredients in order given in a 9-inch square pan. Serve with chips or crackers.

title: green pepper coleslaw
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper, paprika and add to cabbage. Let stand 15 minutes, then drain.
Mix green peppers with cabbage.
Add salad dressing and toss.
Serves 100 people.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Heat oven
to
Mix
all ingredients in large bowl and mix with
electric
mixer on low to medium speed for 3 to 5 minutes.
Pour into greased and lightly floured loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes or until wooden toothpick comes out clean.
Note:
Bread
slices
better after totally cooled. Is great with butter.

title: spring punch
directions: Mix lemonades with water as directed on cans.
Add remaining ingredients putting in soda last and topping with sherbet.
This punch is good without the vodka for children.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in a normal fashion.
Roll into small balls and put on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down with a flat-bottom glass, dipped in water (first press) and then dipped in granulated sugar (second press).
Repeat after every couple of cookies.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 15 minutes, depending on how dark you like them.
Undercook and leave on cookie sheet for a few minutes before removing for light color cookies.
Ovens may vary and 350° may be better if they are baking too fast.

title: hawaiian rice
directions: In medium saucepan bring 1 1/2 cups broth to boil over high heat.
Add rice.
Cover and reduce heat to a low setting.
Let rice bubble gently.
Cook for 50 minutes and add green pepper and celery, then stir in green onion until hot.
Then place in serving bowls and serve.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Prepare potatoes and mix other ingredients before guests arrive.
Start to bake about 45 min. before serving.
Arrange potatoes, peel side down in 2 shallow baking pans.
Bake in preheated oven 375°
45 min. or until potatoes are golden brown. Serves 6.

title: cream of broccoli soup(serves 8)
directions: Melt
margarine.
Add
onion, celery and carrots; saute for 3 to	5 minutes.
Add flour.	Stir and cook for 2 minutes. Slowly add
liquid from broccoli.	Add remaining ingredients. Cook on very low heat for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: grand oranges and strawberries
directions: Melt marmalade in a small saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly; remove from heat, and let cool slightly.
Stir together marmalade, white grape juice, and orange liqueur in a large serving dish or bowl until blended.
Add orange sections, and gently stir.
Cover and chill 8 hours.
Add strawberries to oranges in bowl, and gently stir.
Serve with a slotted spoon.

title: seafood newburg
directions: Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet.
Add mushrooms and cook over medium-high heat for 5 to 6 minutes, stirring often, until golden.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Sift together flour, cinnamon and salt.
Cream shortening, sugar, pumpkin and egg and mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients. Drop by spoon on greased cookie sheet and bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 300°.

title: ranch potato crisps
directions: Combine the potato slices, vegetable oil and salad dressing mix in a large sealable plastic bag.
Seal the bag and shake to coat the potatoes.
Arrange potato slices in a single layer on a baking sheet; do not overlap slices.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40-45 minutes or until browned.

title: angel food cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat egg whites, cream of tartar, extracts and salt at high speed.
While beating, gradually add sugar. Beat until sugar is dissolved and mixture forms stiff peaks. Combine confectioners sugar and flour.
Gradually fold into the batter, 1/4 cup at a time.
Gently spoon mixture into an ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
With a metal spatula or knife, cut through the batter to break large air pockets.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched. Immediately invert cake in pan to cool completely.
When cool, remove from pan.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix together and strain. Bake in unbaked pie shell at 400° for 10 minutes; turn oven down to 300° and bake until done.

title: diabetic fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 8-inch square baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In medium sized bowl, stir together sugar, Sweet 'N Low, margarine, eggs, Butter Buds and vanilla.
In small bowl, stir together dry ingredients and stir into liquid ingredients just until blended.
Spread into pan.
Bake 25 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Cut in 2-inch squares.

title: sweet dough filled coffee cakes
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Add the beaten eggs.
Make sure that it is still lukewarm.
Mix all together.
Add flour as needed to make a nice dough; let rise 1 hour.
Work down.
Butter 3 pie pans; drop dough in.
Let rise again before baking.
Put crumbs on top before baking.

title: tahini sauce
directions: A great spread on toast or a garnish on Falafel.

title: chocolate sodas
directions: Place 2 to 3 tablespoons chocolate syrup in each tall glass. Fill each glass 1/2 full with chilled club soda or ginger ale or carbonated lemon-lime beverage.
Serve immediately with a straw.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Prepare your favorite pie crust mix for one crust.
In bowl, mix apples, sugar, salt, 2 tablespoons flour and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Set aside.
In medium bowl with fork, stir brown sugar, 1 cup flour and 3/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
With pastry blender, cut margarine into flour; mix until large crumbs.
Spoon apples mix into pie crust.
Sprinkle flour mix evenly over apples.
Cover top loosely with foil.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Remove foil; bake 20 more minutes.

title: salmon fillets with crabmeat patties
directions: In nonstick pan sprayed with no-fat cooking oil, saute onion, bell pepper and garlic until just limp.
In mixing bowl, crumble crabmeat; add onion mixture, egg white, bouillon, salt, pepper and hot sauce, if desired.
Add crushed saltines and liquid butter as needed to make patties.
Place salmon fillets in baking dish and top with crabmeat patties.
Sprinkle with paprika and top with lemon.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for approximately 15 minutes or until salmon flakes and patties are browned.
Serves 2.

title: extraordinary chocolate brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix salad dressing, eggs and water until well blended.
Stir in brownie mix and stir just until moistened. Coarsely chop 1 chocolate bar and stir into brownie mix.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until it pulls from sides of pan.
Immediately top with other chocolate bar.
Let stand 5 minutes or until melted. When cool, cut into squares.

title: pink lady
directions: Combine 4 ingredients in a bowl.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Press into serving dish.
Freeze overnight.
Cut in squares.

title: capirotada(mexican bread pudding)
directions: Boil water, sugar, stick cinnamon and clove together until syrupy.
Butter a casserole dish generously and put in a layer of bread or cake cubes.
Cover with a layer of banana or apple slices and sprinkle with some of the raisins, peanuts, almonds and cheese cubes.
Repeat the layers until all ingredients are used.
Remove stick of cinnamon and clove from syrup and pour syrup over pudding. Bake in a moderate oven (350°) about 30 minutes.
Serve hot. Serves 8.

title: mint dazzler
directions: Blend crumbs and melted butter and press firmly in greased 7 x 11-inch pan.
Cream butter and powdered sugar.
Add eggs and chocolate.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Spoon over crumbs.
Beat cream and fold in marshmallows.
Spread over chocolate layer. Sprinkle with crushed candy and put in freezer.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: my mother's applesauce cake
directions: Sift together first 8 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 300° to 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: spring salad
directions: For best results, marinate salad for several hours before using, overnight, if possible.

title: chocolate fried pies
directions: In a saucepan, combine granulated sugar, flour and cocoa. Stir in the 1/2 cup milk and butter or margarine.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Cook 1 minute more.
Stir in vanilla.
Cool.

title: corn pudding
directions: Cook corn.
Put flour and milk together and shake.
Beat egg and add to flour and milk.
Pour corn and flour and milk into a baking dish.
Add butter to top, then salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix well and pour in ice cream churn and freeze.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Combine sugar and butter; cream until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour, alternately with milk, beating well after each time.
Stir in extracts.

title: chili
directions: Wash kidney beans.
Place tomatoes with juice, beans, spices, and bouillon cubes in a large pot.
Bring to a boil.
Brown ground beef and sausage.
Drain.
Add onions, bell pepper, and meat to the pot.
Maintain the boil until the chili is at the desired thickness. The beans will soften when the chili is done.

title: ham roll
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water in large bowl.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour, the sugar and salt.
Beat on low speed until moistened.
Beat on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally, until smooth.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface; knead 3 minutes.
Shape into ball; cover.

title: hershey's chocolate cake
directions: Mix ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured.

title: french fried okra
directions: Wash okra; drain well and cut into 1-inch slices.
Sprinkle with salt.
Add buttermilk, stirring until well coated.
Let stand for 15 minutes; drain and dredge in flour.
Deep fry.

title: armenian casserole
directions: Combine the lentils and rice and set aside.
Brown the ground meat and onion. Drain off fat. Add raisins, cloves and cinnamon to meat.
In a Dutch oven or heavy deep kettle, greased, alternate layers of the lentil-rice mix and the meat mixture. Gently pour hot broth over layered casserole.
Cover and simmer for 1/2 hour or cook in a 300° to 325° oven.

title: lazy lasagna
directions: Cook the noodles and drain.
Mix everything together except for 1/3 cup of Mozzarella cheese and spaghetti sauce.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with spaghetti sauce and remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
